ogress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T19:02:30.140772+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"stalled\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-reset to backlog: dispatched but no agent ever picked up the task. currentStep was \\\"None\\\" with no progress after 41min. Dispatcher-agent handoff gap.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastActivity\": \"2026-06-02T18:21:02.843Z\",\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-02T19:02:30.140772+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": null,\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-06-02T18:21:02.843Z\",\n    \"progress\": 0,\n    \"stalledAt\": \"2026-06-02T19:02:30.140772+00:00\",\n    \"dispatchCount\": 0\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-kanban-fix-001\",\n    \"title\": \"Kanban layout: 4-col grid, remove Awaiting Review, add Reviewed badge\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T17:22:08.620963Z\",\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-02T17:22:08.620963Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-06-02T17:22:08.620963Z\",\n    \"summary\": \"Removed unused Awaiting Review column from Kanban. Changed grid from 3 to 4 cols (md:grid-cols-4). Added reviewed? boolean to Task type and REVIEWED badge on Done tasks. Review toggle button in TaskDetailPanel. All routes verified 200.\",\n    \"currentStep\": \"Completed\",\n    \"lastActivity\": \"2026-06-02T17:22:08.620963Z\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T17:22:08.620963Z\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Kanban layout fix complete\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"tags\": [\n      \"ui\",\n      \"kanban\",\n      \"ux\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-mp7d3s9w-1lmf\",\n    \"title\": \"Task Completion — summary and visibility improvement.\",\n    \"assignee\": \"archivist\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Task Completion — summary and visibility improvement.\\n\\nThe auto-move from In Progress to Done works well. But when a task \\nmoves to Done, I can't tell WHAT was actually done. The card just \\nsays \\\"Done\\\" with no context.\\n\\nFix:\\n\\n1. When a task completes and auto-moves to Done, the card must \\n   include a brief summary of what was accomplished. This summary \\n   should be:\\n   - Written by the agent that completed the task\\n   - 1-3 sentences describing the actual outcome\\n   - Stored on the task card itself, visible in the Kanban view\\n   - Also visible when I click \\\"More Details\\\" on the card\\n\\n2. The \\\"More Details\\\" view on any Done card should show:\\n   - Original task description\\n   - Completion summary (what was actually done)\\n   - Which agent completed it\\n   - Timestamp of completion\\n   - Any relevant links or artifacts produced (files changed, \\n     commits made, etc.)\\n\\n3. In the Kanban view, a Done card should show at minimum:\\n   - Task title\\n   - One-line completion summary (truncated if needed)\\n   - \\\"Done by [Agent] • [time]\\\"\\n\\n4. If the task was created manually by me (not auto-generated from \\n   an error or cron job), the agent who picks it up should write \\n   the completion summary before moving it to Done. If no summary \\n   is written, the task should NOT auto-move — it should stay In \\n   Progress with a flag: \\\"Awaiting completion summary.\\\"\\n\\nThis applies to ALL tasks going forward. Retroactively fixing old \\nDone tasks is optional — only if quick.\\n\\nReport your approach before implementing.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T20:20:43.364Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Task created\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T20:20:45.084Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T20:36:50.973Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from done to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T08:00:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (started 2026-05-15T20:36 with no progress)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:44:48.696Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"archivist\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-02T14:44:48.696Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"stalledAt\": \"2026-06-02T11:48:33.545348+00:00\",\n    \"lastActivity\": \"2026-06-02T16:48:18.319703+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": \"OPS-002 Incident→Task Linking complete\",\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-06-02T14:44:48.696Z\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-06-02T16:48:18.319703+00:00\",\n    \"summary\": \"OPS-002: Incident → Task Linking implemented. Task.linkedIncidentId is source of truth. Auto-detect creates linked triage tasks. Task status changes push to incident timeline. Triage column added. Linked Incident section in task detail. Derived linked tasks in IncidentDetailsDrawer.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-mp7cbyxz-0ztq\",\n    \"title\": \"Error Feed — behaviour review and fix.\",\n    \"assignee\": \"lifesupport\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Error Feed — behaviour review and fix.\\n\\nThe error feed currently has Investigate / Resolved / Skip buttons but \\nthe workflow is confusing. Here's how it should actually work:\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nCORRECT ERROR FEED WORKFLOW\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\n1. A cron job fails → error appears in the Error Feed tab with a \\n   \\\"NEW\\\" badge\\n\\n2. I click \\\"Investigate\\\" → \\n   - The error status changes to \\\"IN PROGRESS\\\" \\n   - A corresponding task is automatically created in the Tasks \\n     section under \\\"In Progress\\\" so the crew knows to work on it\\n   - The error stays visible in the feed with an in-progress indicator\\n   - The button changes to show \\\"Resolved\\\" and \\\"Skip\\\"\\n\\n3. The crew fixes the underlying issue. The cron job runs successfully \\n   on its next scheduled run →\\n   - The error automatically clears from the Error Feed\\n   - The linked task in the Tasks section moves to \\\"Done\\\"\\n   - No manual \\\"Resolved\\\" click needed — the system verified the fix\\n\\n4. If I click \\\"Resolved\\\" manually →\\n   - For when I've verified the fix myself\\n   - Error disappears from the feed\\n   - Linked task moves to Done\\n\\n5. If I click \\\"Skip\\\" →\\n   - For known non-critical issues I'm choosing to ignore\\n   - Error disappears from the feed\\n   - No task is created\\n\\n6. If the same job fails again later →\\n   - A NEW error appears (not the old one reopened)\\n   - Fresh timestamp, fresh status\\n   - Does NOT resurrect the old skipped/resolved error\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nKEY RULES\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\n- Errors should NOT show \\\"Completed\\\" with an \\\"In Progress\\\" flag \\n  at the same time (current bug)\\n- When a cron job succeeds after being in error state, the error \\n  should auto-clear — the system verified the fix\\n- The \\\"Investigate\\\" button creates a task in the Tasks board so \\n  work is tracked\\n- The error feed reflects REALITY: if the job is still failing, \\n  the error stays. If it succeeds, the error goes away.\\n- The cron job entry in the Scheduler list should show an error \\n  badge ONLY while there's an active unresolved error\\n\\n═══════════════════════════════\\nWHAT TO FIX NOW\\n═══════════════════════════════\\n\\n1. Fix the double-status bug (no more \\\"Completed\\\" + \\\"In Progress\\\" \\n   showing simultaneously)\\n2. Wire Investigate button to auto-create a task in the Tasks board\\n3. Wire cron job success to auto-clear the corresponding error\\n4. Wire cron job error badge to auto-clear when error is resolved\\n5. Confirm Skip behaviour works as described above\\n6. Test the full flow end-to-end\\n\\nReport what the current behaviour actually is, then fix it to \\nmatch this spec.  [auto-dispatched 2026-06-01 11:53] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-02 11:59] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-02 12:29] [HEARTBEAT 2026-06-02 12:47: Task has been auto-dispatched 6+ times with zero progress. Setting stalledAt to prevent further re-dispatch. Needs human triage.] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-02 12:59] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-02 14:29]\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T19:59:05.639Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Task created\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-15T19:59:07.177Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T08:00:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (started 2026-05-15T20:36 with no progress)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T09:00:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — stale (started May 15, no progress)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T09:43:21.368763+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — stalled (397h with no progress update)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T11:00:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — task was stuck in in_progress with no startedAt, likely from incomplete prior dispatch\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-01T11:30:00.000Z\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset to backlog — task has been stalled since May 15 with no progress. Note: keeps flipping back to in_progress when MC frontend saves stale state.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T10:38:39.308375+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — task keeps flip-flopping. Needs human triage.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T11:15:25.630285+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog - 10th flip-flop. Dispatcher keeps re-picking. Needs human triage.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T11:47:40.689677+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog. Task has been auto-dispatched 6+ times with zero progress. stalledAt set to prevent re-dispatch loop. Needs human triage.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T13:29:36.701419+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — flip-flopped again. Frontend save-tasks overwrote stalledAt. Protected fields now added to merge logic.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:25:57.494365+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset to backlog. Stalled. Protected from re-dispatch.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:44:31.229Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"lifesupport\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T15:05:08.950571+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"HARD STALLED — dispatchCount set to 99. This task requires human triage, not automated dispatch. Do not re-dispatch without human clearance.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-06-02T14:44:31.229Z\",\n    \"lastActivity\": \"2026-06-02T15:05:08.950571+00:00\",\n    \"stalledAt\": \"2026-06-02T15:05:08.950571+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": \"Agent starting…\",\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-06-02T14:44:31.229Z\",\n    \"progress\": 5,\n    \"dispatchCount\": 99\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-mpwfiydb-6khn\",\n    \"title\": \"Opencode Coding Buddy\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"OpenCode was tested and has native OpenRouter support. It lists all\\nOpenRouter models including free tier options. The login command had\\na bug but we can likely configure the API key directly.\\n\\nInvestigate OpenCode as our coding tool:\\n\\n1. OpenCode is already installed. Check: which opencode\\n2. It supports non-interactive mode: opencode run --model [model] \\\"[prompt]\\\"\\n3. It has native OpenRouter model support — no custom endpoint config needed\\n4. Check if we can set the API key directly via env var or config file\\n5. If it works, this becomes our coding tool for complex multi-file work.\\n6. Free coding models available:\\n   - openrouter/qwen/qwen3-coder:free (best for coding)\\n   - openrouter/moonshotai/kimi-k2.6:free (fallback)\\n   - openrouter/openrouter/free (emergency)\\n\\nDo NOT add to FRAMEWORK.md yet. Just test and report if it works.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T12:34:22.170179+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Task created\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T13:19:16.441487+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"progress\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Investigation: OpenCode v1.15.13 installed at ~/.opencode/bin/opencode. OPENROUTER_API_KEY picked up automatically. kimi-k2.6:free works for simple prompts. qwen3-coder:free and kimi-k2.6:free both hit 429 rate limits on free tier after a few calls. Title generation uses claude-haiku-4.5 (paid) and fails with 402 — no credits remaining. Config format not yet figured out. Need: 1) add OpenRouter credits for title gen, 2) wait for rate limit cooldown, 3) figure out opencode.json schema for setting small model.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:25:57.494365+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"progress\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Config opencode.json created with model=qwen/qwen3-coder:free, title/small=moonshotai/kimi-k2.6:free. Config validates successfully (opencode debug config). openrouter/free works for simple prompts. qwen3-coder:free and kimi-k2.6:free both hit rate limits (sessions run >2min then SIGTERM). File editing test with qwen3-coder timed out. Root cause: free tier rate limits are too aggressive for sustained multi-turn coding sessions. Viable for simple Q&A, not for file editing workflows. Recommendation: add $5-10 OpenRouter credits for reliable coding use, or use openrouter/free as primary.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:35:40.024471+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Investigation complete. Config works, rate limits block production use on free tier.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastActivity\": \"2026-06-02T14:35:40.024471+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": \"Testing complete — config working, models rate-limited\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-06-02T14:35:40.024471+00:00\",\n    \"summary\": \"OpenCode v1.15.13 works with OpenRouter. Config at ~/.config/opencode/opencode.json sets model=qwen/qwen3-coder:free, title/small=kimi-k2.6:free (eliminates 402 error). openrouter/free works for simple prompts. All free coding models hit aggressive rate limits making sustained file-editing unreliable. Recommendation: add $5-10 OpenRouter credits for production use.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-106\",\n    \"title\": \"Integrate new pixel-art sprite sheets\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"1h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"1h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-109\",\n    \"title\": \"Settings page broken — investigate and fix\",\n    \"assignee\": \"engineer\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"1h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"1h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-110\",\n    \"title\": \"Add task detail view (click to expand/edit)\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"1h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"1h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-111\",\n    \"title\": \"Rename Calendar to Scheduler\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"1h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"1h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"err-err-3249748f-ac97-487d-812e-9a0509572c8f\",\n    \"title\": \"[Investigate] Dreaming Status Check: cron: job execution timed out\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"