the backup target isn't available, or does it fail \\nsilently?\\n\\nIf it fails silently, add a check to the backup script that alerts \\nif the target isn't mounted — write to mount-alert.txt so Telegram \\npicks it up.\\n\\nAfter that, the Settings page audit is complete. Station is stable.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-29T21:28:41.124Z\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Task created\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-29T21:28:42.219Z\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Status changed from backlog to in_progress\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-05-29T22:44:02.954998+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Settings page audit complete. All 5 fixes applied: version from CLI status, gateway status from CLI, active crons from cron list, port 3000, restart gateway via launchctl. Backup script now checks for mounted target and returns friendly error.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-05-29T22:44:02.954998+00:00\",\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-05-29T21:28:42.219Z\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-05-29T22:44:02.954998+00:00\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-104\",\n    \"title\": \"Create app shortcut for Mission Control\",\n    \"assignee\": \"engineer\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"system\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"acknowledged\": true\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"T-105\",\n    \"title\": \"Fix task persistence — saveTasks not writing to disk\",\n    \"assignee\": \"engineer\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"ts\": \"2h ago\",\n    \"note\": \"Fixed with direct fetch API to /api/save-tasks endpoint\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"history\": [\n    