{"type":"message","id":"b894020d","parentId":"6aab3b7a","timestamp":"2026-06-03T15:52:51.638Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK so there are **two Vite processes** but both are serving port **3000** (the second one, PID 67081, grabbed 3001 as an ephemeral port — \"redwood-broker\" is just the service name for 3001, but it's not intentionally serving the dev site there).\n\nThe curl to 3001 earlier was probably hitting a cached response or redirect. Let me verify:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"e9eb2d9c-ecb4-484a-abe0-176bbc3621cc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Actually check what 3001 serves\ncurl -s -I http://localhost:3001/ 2>/dev/null | head -5\necho \"===\"\n# And 3000\ncurl -s -I http://localhost:3000/ 2>/dev/null | head 5\necho \"===\"\n# Check git status on both branches\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard\necho \"main:\" && git log --oneline main -1\necho \"dev:\" && git log --oneline dev -1\necho \"---\"\ngit diff main dev --stat 2>/dev/null","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Actually check what 3001 serves\\ncurl -s -I http://localhost:3001/ 2>/dev/null | head -5\\necho \\\"===\\\"\\n# And 3000\\ncurl -s -I http://localhost:3000/ 2>/dev/null | head 5\\necho \\\"===\\\"\\n# Check git status on both branches\\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard\\necho \\\"main:\\\" && git log --oneline main -1\\necho \\\"dev:\\\" && git log --oneline dev -1\\necho \\\"---\\\"\\ngit diff main dev --stat 2>/dev/null\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":652,"output":258,"cacheRead":19456,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":20366,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780501922367,"responseId":"gen-1780501922-yK0Zfv5k030GHdg3hD9k"}}
