": \"Auto-Incident Creation from System Errors\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P1\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"P1/P2 errors in the Error Feed should automatically create an Incident AND a linked Task on the Kanban board. When a cron job fails with a P1/P2 classification, the system creates both records and links them. The incident captures the error context; the task tracks resolution work. [auto-dispatched 2026-06-03 07:02]\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T06:13:03.324521+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"stalled\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-reset: no timestamp no activity\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"stalledAt\": \"2026-06-03T06:13:03.324521+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": null,\n    \"progress\": 0,\n    \"dispatchCount\": 1\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-fd625713\",\n    \"title\": \"Incident → Task Linking\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P1\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"When an incident is created, a corresponding task must appear in the Kanban board automatically. Bidirectional linking: incident shows linked tasks, task shows parent incident. Status changes propagate (task done → incident check for auto-resolution).\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-9e4f3ebc\",\n    \"title\": \"Response Action Lifecycle\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P1\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Implement full lifecycle for incident response actions: NEW → INVESTIGATING → MITIGATING → RESOLVED. Each action tracks assignee, timestamps, and state transitions. Actions are visible in the Incident Details panel and update the incident's overall status.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-ac75ac7b\",\n    \"title\": \"Operational Work Panel\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Add a filtered view that shows only incident and operational tasks, visually distinct from feature work. Different color coding, separate section in the Kanban, and a toggle to show/hide operational vs. feature work.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-488e7676\",\n    \"title\": \"Awaiting Review Incident Flow\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Incidents require review before closure — same pattern as task completion but with an explicit 'awaiting review' gate. Once all response actions are resolved, the incident moves to AWAITING_REVIEW. A reviewer must approve closure before it moves to DONE. [auto-dispatched 2026-06-03 08:02]\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T07:13:17.843045+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"stalled\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-reset: dispatched but no agent to work on planning task\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"stalledAt\": \"2026-06-03T07:13:17.843045+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": null,\n    \"progress\": 0,\n    \"dispatchCount\": 1\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-efcd3558\",\n    \"title\": \"Runbook Data Model\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Design and implement a structured data model for runbooks: incident type, severity, response steps (ordered list), estimated time, required roles, success criteria, and escalation path. Runbooks are stored as structured data, not free text.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-d7b9c364\",\n    \"title\": \"Runbook UI\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Display runbook steps when viewing an incident. Show the relevant runbook based on incident type, progress through steps, and allow agents to mark steps as complete. Clean, scannable layout — not a wall of text.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-f9f8c7ce\",\n    \"title\": \"Incident Type Mapping\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Classify incidents into types (e.g., cron failure, rate limit, service down, dependency break). Auto-suggest incident type based on error patterns and history. Each type maps to a default runbook and severity.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-718a0d19\",\n    \"title\": \"Suggested Action Generation\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"AI suggests response actions based on incident type and resolution history. When an incident is created, the system proposes actions from the matching runbook and similar past incidents. Suggestions appear as pre-filled action cards. [auto-dispatched 2026-06-03 12:03]\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T11:13:14.442600+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"stalled\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-reset: no timestamp no activity\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"stalledAt\": \"2026-06-03T11:13:14.442600+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": null,\n    \"progress\": 0,\n    \"dispatchCount\": 1\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-f2727327\",\n    \"title\": \"Task Creation From Runbooks\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Convert runbook steps into actionable tasks on the Kanban board. Each step becomes a trackable task with assignee, priority, and due date. Progress on runbook steps is visible both in the incident view and the Kanban.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-94ca8faa\",\n    \"title\": \"Asset Schema\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Track systems, services, and agents as first-class assets. Schema: name, type (service/agent/cron/infra), status, owner, health check endpoint, dependencies, last check timestamp. Assets are the things incidents happen TO. [auto-dispatched 2026-06-03 15:33]\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T14:43:04.400124+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"stalled\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Auto-reset: no timestamp no activity\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"stalledAt\": \"2026-06-03T14:43:04.400124+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": null,\n    \"progress\": 0,\n    \"dispatchCount\": 1\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-e8a74157\",\n    \"title\": \"Asset View\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Dedicated view showing all assets and their health status at a glance. Group by type, sort by health, show status indicators. Click an asset to see its incident history, dependencies, and current state.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning — created from strategic roadmap\"\n      }\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-45e26f79\",\n    \"title\": \"Asset Health Monitoring\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    