{"type":"message","id":"c5e827d8","parentId":"d54dca61","timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:02:18.321Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Here's my analysis and fix plan:\n\n**Root cause:** The `work-dispatcher.sh` script has two fundamental problems:\n\n1. **It only flips task status** — it changes `backlog → in_progress` in the JSON file, but doesn't actually spawn an agent (sub-agent or cron job) to do the work. It just tags the note with `[auto-dispatched]` and writes to a log. No agent ever sees these tasks.\n\n2. **Stall detection threshold is too lenient** — the 2-hour auto-reset means a task can sit with \"Agent starting…\" for 120+ minutes before being caught. The work-dispatcher's own stall check uses 1 hour (`age_h > 1`), but only resets — it doesn't re-dispatch properly.\n\n**The fix:** The heartbeat (main agent) should be the only dispatcher. It already has the context to pick tasks and spawn sub-agents. The shell script should be removed or simplified to just do stall detection.\n\nLet me fix this properly:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"247fc636-b1fc-4183-9a7e-bef79d359a62","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Task Pickup\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- For each backlog task, spawn a sub-agent (or work directly if simple) to complete it\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- Write completion summary before marking done (see task details)\n- Only pick up one task per heartbeat to avoid overloading","newText":"## Task Pickup\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- ONLY pick tasks that are truly dispatchable: no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\n- Sort by priority (P1 > P2 > P3), then by age (oldest first)\n- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` every 5-10 min with specific actions (NOT \"Agent starting…\")\n- Write completion summary before marking done\n- Only pick up ONE task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n- The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents\n- Crew task routing: infra → lifesupport, code → engineer, knowledge → archivist, unknown → monkey"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"## Task Pickup\\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \\\"backlog\\\"`\\n- For each backlog task, spawn a sub-agent (or work directly if simple) to complete it\\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\\n- Write completion summary before marking done (see task details)\\n- Only pick up one task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\", \"newText\": \"## Task Pickup\\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \\\"backlog\\\"`\\n- ONLY pick tasks that are truly dispatchable: no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\\n- Sort by priority (P1 > P2 > P3), then by age (oldest first)\\n- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\\n- The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` every 5-10 min with specific actions (NOT \\\"Agent starting…\\\")\\n- Write completion summary before marking done\\n- Only pick up ONE task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\\n- The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents\\n- Crew task routing: infra → lifesupport, code → engineer, knowledge → archivist, unknown → monkey\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":263,"output":583,"cacheRead":58624,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":59470,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780506093269,"responseId":"gen-1780506093-pKXNRL2BdxbJQHHxEabo"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1ba9abef","parentId":"c5e827d8","timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:02:18.343Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"247fc636-b1fc-4183-9a7e-bef79d359a62","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  3 # Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n  4 \n  5 ## Task Pickup\n  6 - Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- 7 - For each backlog task, spawn a sub-agent (or work directly if simple) to complete it\n+ 7 - ONLY pick tasks that are truly dispatchable: no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\n+ 8 - Sort by priority (P1 > P2 > P3), then by age (oldest first)\n+ 9 - Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n  8 - Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- 9 - Write completion summary before marking done (see task details)\n-10 - Only pick up one task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n+11 - The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` every 5-10 min with specific actions (NOT \"Agent starting…\")\n+12 - Write completion summary before marking done\n+13 - Only pick up ONE task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n+14 - The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents\n+15 - Crew task routing: infra → lifesupport, code → engineer, knowledge → archivist, unknown → monkey\n 11 \n 12 ## Stall Detection (CRITICAL — check EVERY heartbeat)\n 13 - For EVERY task with `status: \"in_progress\"`, calculate staleness:\n 14   - Use `lastActivity` if set and is a valid ISO timestamp\n    ...","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n@@ -3,12 +3,17 @@\n # Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n \n ## Task Pickup\n - Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n-- For each backlog task, spawn a sub-agent (or work directly if simple) to complete it\n+- ONLY pick tasks that are truly dispatchable: no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\n+- Sort by priority (P1 > P2 > P3), then by age (oldest first)\n+- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n - Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n-- Write completion summary before marking done (see task details)\n-- Only pick up one task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n+- The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` every 5-10 min with specific actions (NOT \"Agent starting…\")\n+- Write completion summary before marking done\n+- Only pick up ONE task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n+- The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents\n+- Crew task routing: infra → lifesupport, code → engineer, knowledge → archivist, unknown → monkey\n \n ## Stall Detection (CRITICAL — check EVERY heartbeat)\n - For EVERY task with `status: \"in_progress\"`, calculate staleness:\n   - Use `lastActivity` if set and is a valid ISO timestamp\n","firstChangedLine":7},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780506138342}}
{"type":"message","id":"228bec96","parentId":"1ba9abef","timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:02:55.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me also tighten the stall detection thresholds:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"49585a1c-6ce6-4ef8-91e6-4d47b86b14e0","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"- If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning but don't reset yet","newText":"- If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning. If currentStep is still \"Agent starting…\" or null, reset immediately — the task was never actually picked up by an agent"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"- If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning but don't reset yet\", \"newText\": \"- If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning. If currentStep is still \\\"Agent starting…\\\" or null, reset immediately — the task was never actually picked up by an agent\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":630,"output":130,"cacheRead":58880,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":59640,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780506138349,"responseId":"gen-1780506138-jskejJIE0g0QCTlBKiVm"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1167a28d","parentId":"228bec96","timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:02:55.353Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"49585a1c-6ce6-4ef8-91e6-4d47b86b14e0","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 21   - Else use the most recent `history[].ts` entry\n 22   - If NO valid timestamp can be found at all, treat as stalled (it's broken data)\n 23 - If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the work-dispatcher from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n 24 - ALSO increment `dispatchCount` by 1 (set to at least 1 if not present). If `dispatchCount >= 3`, the dispatcher will skip the task entirely via its `dispatchCount < 3` filter. This is a secondary guard against the race condition where `stalledAt` gets cleared by the save-tasks merge logic.\n-25 - If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning but don't reset yet\n+25 - If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning. If currentStep is still \"Agent starting…\" or null, reset immediately — the task was never actually picked up by an agent\n 26 - The `startedAt` field is NOT reliable — do not use it for stall detection\n 27 - After resetting, commit the change so the Kanban reflects reality immediately\n 28 \n 29 ## Task Archive Maintenance\n    ...","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n@@ -21,9 +21,9 @@\n   - Else use the most recent `history[].ts` entry\n   - If NO valid timestamp can be found at all, treat as stalled (it's broken data)\n - If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the work-dispatcher from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n - ALSO increment `dispatchCount` by 1 (set to at least 1 if not present). If `dispatchCount >= 3`, the dispatcher will skip the task entirely via its `dispatchCount < 3` filter. This is a secondary guard against the race condition where `stalledAt` gets cleared by the save-tasks merge logic.\n-- If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning but don't reset yet\n+- If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning. If currentStep is still \"Agent starting…\" or null, reset immediately — the task was never actually picked up by an agent\n - The `startedAt` field is NOT reliable — do not use it for stall detection\n - After resetting, commit the change so the Kanban reflects reality immediately\n \n ## Task Archive Maintenance\n","firstChangedLine":25},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780506175352}}
