{"type":"message","id":"b222d9b0","parentId":"dff5228c","timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:15:24.961Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Health check complete. Summary:\n\n- **MC:** ✅ 200 on port 3000\n- **In Progress:** ✅ 0 tasks (reset the one the work-dispatcher silently flipped)\n- **Backlog:** 43 tasks — 15 dispatchable, 28 protected/stalled\n- **Dispatchable P1:** 1 task — \"Incident → Task Linking\" (assignee=monkey)\n- **Work-dispatcher script:** Not actively running (no cron/LaunchAgent), but the script file still exists at `scripts/work-dispatcher.sh` — should probably be removed to prevent future accidents\n- **Stale protected task:** \"Error Feed — behaviour review and fix\" has been stalled for 26h with dispatchCount=99 — needs human triage\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":221,"output":183,"cacheRead":64640,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":65044,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780506893921,"responseId":"gen-1780506894-gBA8eksJx5gtcFh1RZN4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"dea4bb1d","parentId":"b222d9b0","timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:17:14.231Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Good investigation. The work-dispatcher shell script is the root cause \n— it flips JSON fields without spawning any actual work. Here's the plan:\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nIMMEDIATE FIXES\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. DISABLE THE WORK-DISPATCHER SCRIPT\n   - Remove the cron job or LaunchAgent that calls it\n   - Delete or rename scripts/work-dispatcher.sh so it can't run\n   - The heartbeat is now the ONLY dispatcher\n\n2. CLEAN UP THE 28 PROTECTED/STALLED TASKS\n   These have been dispatched multiple times with zero progress.\n   For each one, decide:\n   - Still relevant? Clear stalledAt and dispatchCount, put back in backlog\n   - No longer needed? Mark as Done with note \"Obsolete — cleaned up\"\n   - Can't decide? Leave stalled, I'll review manually\n   \n   Show me a summary list — don't just process them silently.\n\n3. VERIFY THE HEARTBEAT DISPATCH LOGIC\n   - Confirm the heartbeat picks up P1 tasks first, then P2, then P3\n   - Confirm sub-agents update currentStep every 5-10 min\n   - Confirm stall detection fires at 30 min for \"Agent starting…\" \n     with no real step change\n   - Run a manual dispatch of ONE task to verify end-to-end\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nFOR THE 16 DISPATCHABLE TASKS\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nThese are planning/design tasks (Incident → Task Linking, Runbook \nData Model, etc.). They need my input before an agent can build them.\nDo NOT dispatch these — they're placeholders from the strategic \nbacklog planning. Leave them in backlog.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nTHE ONE TASK I WANT DISPATCHED\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nPick ONE small, well-defined task from the dispatchable list — \nsomething an agent can complete without my input. Dispatch it, \nmonitor it, and prove the system works end-to-end:\n- Task picked up → currentStep updates → progress increases → \n  moves to Done with completion summary\n- If it stalls, the stall detection fires and moves it back\n\nThis is the proof that the task system is operational.","timestamp":1780507034122,"idempotencyKey":"f60b048c-5338-44ba-b975-26c3ce19c5c1:user"}}
