{"type":"message","id":"cc3d2e0c","parentId":"b7230201","timestamp":"2026-06-03T17:57:40.085Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Andre, here's the confirmation:\n\n**Work-dispatcher:** Dead and buried.\n- Original file: gone\n- `.disabled` file: non-executable (`rw-` only)\n- No cron jobs, no LaunchAgents, no scripts reference it\n- The ghost dispatch you caught was the last gasp — nothing can trigger it now\n\n**Sub-agent timestamp discipline:** Updated HEARTBEAT.md with explicit instructions that every sub-agent must:\n1. Set `currentStep` to a specific action *before* starting work (not \"Agent starting…\")\n2. Update `lastActivity` with an ISO timestamp at every step\n3. Update `progress` to reflect actual completion\n4. Write a `summary` before marking done\n\nThe Move Incident ShortCut task's timestamps were actually fine (completedAt and lastActivity matched), but the sub-agent didn't update `currentStep` *during* work — it jumped from \"Agent starting…\" straight to \"Completed\". That gap is what stall detection would miss. The new instructions close that gap.\n\nSystem is clean. 🐒"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":191,"output":223,"cacheRead":77824,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":78238,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780509440221,"responseId":"gen-1780509440-EIbh3gdm8flxkf75d4F0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d8c7d7d2","parentId":"cc3d2e0c","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:01:53.992Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The task system is now clean — work-dispatcher dead, heartbeat is the \nonly dispatcher, end-to-end test passed. Now I want the system to work \nautonomously while I sleep instead of sitting idle.\n\nDesign a \"Night Shift\" mode. Do NOT build it yet — design only.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nTHE NIGHT SHIFT CONCEPT\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nWhen I'm asleep (01:00-07:00) and there are dispatchable backlog tasks, \nthe system should work through them autonomously rather than doing nothing.\n\nTRIGGER: At 01:00, the heartbeat checks if Night Shift should activate.\n- Are there dispatchable backlog tasks?\n- Are rate limits healthy (no recent 429s)?\n- Is Andre marked as \"away\" (no recent chat activity)?\n- If all three are true → enter Night Shift mode\n\nBEHAVIOUR:\n- Pick ONE task at a time (P1 first, then P2, then P3)\n- Spawn a sub-agent to work on it\n- Complete it → move to Done → pick the next\n- Continue until: no more dispatchable tasks, OR rate limits spike, \n  OR 07:00 arrives\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Maximum 5 tasks per night (don't burn through the entire backlog)\n- Stop immediately if rate limit warnings appear (429 errors)\n- Only work on tasks that don't need my input — skip tasks tagged \n  \"needs-human-input\" or marked as planning/design\n- Don't start a new task after 06:30 (time to wrap up and report)\n- Each completed task must have: completion summary, currentStep \n  history, progress tracking\n\nMORNING REPORT (07:00):\nSend a Telegram sitrep:\n\"🌙 Night shift complete. X tasks done. Y remaining in backlog. \n ~Z tokens used.\n Completed: [task titles with one-line summaries]\"\n\nSAFETY RULES:\n- Never auto-dispatch tasks that have stalledAt set\n- Never re-dispatch a task attempted 3+ times (dispatchCount ≥ 3)\n- If a task fails, move it back to backlog with failure note\n- Never modify openclaw.json, LaunchAgents, or system config\n- Never touch the gateway or cron jobs\n- Shell-only infrastructure checks only — no model calls for monitoring\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nDESIGN QUESTIONS TO ANSWER\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. How would Night Shift integrate with the existing heartbeat?\n   - Should it be a separate cron job, or part of the heartbeat cycle?\n   - How does it coexist with Dreaming (3am) and Daily Station Check (23:00)?\n\n2. What changes to HEARTBEAT.md are needed?\n   - New section for Night Shift rules?\n   - Modified dispatch logic during 01:00-07:00 window?\n\n3. What changes to tasks.json schema are needed?\n   - New field like `nightShiftEligible: true/false`?\n   - Or use existing tags/priority to determine eligibility?\n\n4. What are the risks?\n   - Token exhaustion before morning?\n   - Sub-agent runaway (tool-call loops)?\n   - Corrupted tasks.json from rapid-fire saves?\n   - How do we mitigate each one?\n\n5. How do we test this safely?\n   - Manual trigger for a single task first?\n   - Dry-run mode that logs what it WOULD do?\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nDELIVERABLE\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nA design document (add to MEMORY.md or a new NIGHT_SHIFT.md) covering:\n- Architecture: how it integrates with heartbeat/cron\n- Eligibility rules: which tasks qualify for night work\n- Safety constraints: what it must never do\n- Morning report format\n- Test plan\n\nNo code. No implementation. Design only.","timestamp":1780509713882,"idempotencyKey":"f11a625e-b49e-4ba2-8d23-11b3e8b10bda:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"755aa931","parentId":"d8c7d7d2","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:02:27.575Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood brief. Let me design this properly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"f6e7d86e-02fb-4ad5-af1d-e7a95de0149b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"6f527aa0-34c8-4802-ac84-912d8ca8e3d9","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list","includeDisabled":true},"partialArgs":"{\"action\": \"list\", \"includeDisabled\": true}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":68966,"output":62,"cacheRead":10240,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":79268,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780509713995,"responseId":"gen-1780509714-SJzAUefCcj9dVe8MB34I"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9cca1d5a","parentId":"755aa931","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:02:27.650Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"f6e7d86e-02fb-4ad5-af1d-e7a95de0149b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Task Pickup\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- ONLY pick tasks that are truly dispatchable: no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\n- Sort by priority (P1 > P2 > P3), then by age (oldest first)\n- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- **The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` (ISO timestamp) every 5-10 min with specific actions** — NOT \"Agent starting…\". Example: \"Reading AppSidebar.tsx\", \"Editing nav order\", \"Verifying app loads\". Without `lastActivity` updates, stall detection cannot function.\n- Write completion summary before marking done\n- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\n  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action before starting work\n  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at each step\n  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 50% midway, 100% done)\n  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\n  - Commit and push code changes when complete\n- Only pick up ONE task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n- The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents\n- Crew task routing: infra → lifesupport, code → engineer, knowledge → archivist, unknown → monkey\n\n## Stall Detection (CRITICAL — check EVERY heartbeat)\n- For EVERY task with `status: \"in_progress\"`, calculate staleness:\n  - Use `lastActivity` if set and is a valid ISO timestamp\n  - Else use the `ts` field if it's a valid ISO timestamp (skip if it's \"just now\" or non-parseable)\n  - Else use the most recent `history[].ts` entry\n  - If NO valid timestamp can be found at all, treat as stalled (it's broken data)\n- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the heartbeat from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n- ALSO increment `dispatchCount` by 1 (set to at least 1 if not present). If `dispatchCount >= 3`, the dispatcher will skip the task entirely via its `dispatchCount < 3` filter. This is a secondary guard against the race condition where `stalledAt` gets cleared by the save-tasks merge logic.\n- If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning. If currentStep is still \"Agent starting…\" or null, reset immediately — the task was never actually picked up by an agent\n- The `startedAt` field is NOT reliable — do not use it for stall detection\n- After resetting, commit the change so the Kanban reflects reality immediately\n\n## Task Archive Maintenance\n- **Done tasks live in the Kanban Done column** — never remove them just because they're complete\n- Only archive done tasks older than 30 days to `data/tasks-archive.json`\n- When archiving: append to existing archive, remove from `tasks.json`, commit + push\n- The Done column should always show recent completions (last 30 days minimum)\n- Archive is for long-term storage only — the Kanban is the source of truth\n\n## Rule: Sub-agent Timeout\n- If a sub-agent runs for >5 minutes with no resolution, kill it and add the task to backlog\n- If the main agent spends >10 minutes debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n- Always report what was tried and what the blocker is when adding to backlog\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780509747650}}
{"type":"message","id":"85efaf9b","parentId":"9cca1d5a","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:02:27.653Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"6f527aa0-34c8-4802-ac84-912d8ca8e3d9","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"jobs\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"6f823429-453b-4db5-a5c9-51472f1693b3\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"name\": \"Sessions Cleanup\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1779373498843,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 2 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"main\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"systemEvent\",\n        \"text\": \"openclaw sessions cleanup\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1780538400000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1780452000006,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 12,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n        \"lastFailureNotificationDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"consecutiveSkipped\": 0\n      },\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1780452000018\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"c52ff1a0-0936-48f9-8247-3711020824ca\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"name\": \"Session Auto‑Expiry\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1779373821493,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 4 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"main\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"systemEvent\",\n        \"text\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/session-expiry.sh\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1780545600000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1780459200010,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 11,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n        \"lastFailureNotificationDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"consecutiveSkipped\": 0\n      },\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1780459200021\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"e9be709d-ca66-463a-8499-9adb21d13645\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:telegram:direct:7507878944\",\n      \"name\": \"Auto-update FreeRide\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1779882063149,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 6 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Europe/London\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the daily maintenance check. Do the following:\\n\\n1. **FreeRide auto-update:** Run ~/.freeride/auto-update.sh\\n2. **Gateway status:** Check if the OpenClaw gateway is running (openclaw status or similar)\\n3. **OpenClaw update check:** Run `openclaw --version` to get the installed version, then check the latest release at https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/releases (use curl/web_fetch to get the page). Report if a newer version is available. Do NOT auto-install — just report.\\n\\nThen report all three in a concise summary:\\n- FreeRide version (before/after if upgraded)\\n- Gateway status (running/DOWN)\\n- OpenClaw version (current vs latest, up-to-date or update available)\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"to\": \"telegram:7507878944\",\n        \"channel\": \"telegram\",\n        \"accountId\": \"default\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1780549200000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1780462800008,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 51901,\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"lastFailureNotificationDeliveryStatus\": \"not-requested\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"consecutiveSkipped\": 0\n      },\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1780462851909\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total\": 3,\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"limit\": 3,\n  \"hasMore\": false,\n  \"nextOffset\": null,\n  \"deliveryPreviews\": {\n    \"6f823429-453b-4db5-a5c9-51472f1693b3\": {\n      \"label\": \"not requested\",\n      \"detail\": \"not requested\"\n    },\n    \"c52ff1a0-0936-48f9-8247-3711020824ca\": {\n      \"label\": \"not requested\",\n      \"detail\": \"not requested\"\n    },\n    \"e9be709d-ca66-463a-8499-9adb21d13645\": {\n      \"label\": \"announce -> telegram:7507878944\",\n      \"detail\": \"explicit\"\n    }\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"jobs":[{"id":"6f823429-453b-4db5-a5c9-51472f1693b3","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"Sessions Cleanup","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1779373498843,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 2 * * *","tz":"UTC"},"sessionTarget":"main","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"systemEvent","text":"openclaw sessions cleanup"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1780538400000,"lastRunAtMs":1780452000006,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":12,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-requested","lastFailureNotificationDeliveryStatus":"not-requested","consecutiveErrors":0,"consecutiveSkipped":0},"updatedAtMs":1780452000018},{"id":"c52ff1a0-0936-48f9-8247-3711020824ca","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"Session Auto‑Expiry","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1779373821493,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 4 * * *","tz":"UTC"},"sessionTarget":"main","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"systemEvent","text":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/session-expiry.sh"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1780545600000,"lastRunAtMs":1780459200010,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":11,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-requested","lastFailureNotificationDeliveryStatus":"n