— 2026-06-01 23:00\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:119:## 2026-05-21 23:00 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:129:## 2026-05-30 21:37 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:136:## 2026-05-30 21:38 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:143:## 2026-05-30 21:39 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:155:## 2026-05-30 21:41 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:165:## 2026-05-30 21:48 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:175:## 2026-05-30 23:00 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:185:## 2026-05-30 23:43 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:204:## 2026-05-31 22:33 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/health-log.md:214:## 2026-05-31 23:00 (Europe/London) — Daily Station Check","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780509772247}}
{"type":"message","id":"e017af39","parentId":"3f33df63","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:04:39.453Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the full picture. Let me write the design document."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"3c438747-95aa-4c6c-8df4-d80d253ae7f1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md","content":"# NIGHT SHIFT — Design Document\n\n_Autonomous task processing during 01:00-07:00 when Andre is asleep._\n\n**Status:** Design only — not yet implemented\n**Created:** 2026-06-03\n\n---\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### Integration with Heartbeat\n\nNight Shift is **not a separate cron job**. It's a mode within the existing heartbeat cycle.\n\n**Why heartbeat, not cron:**\n- The heartbeat already has the context to pick tasks, spawn sub-agents, and update task state\n- A separate cron would compete with the heartbeat for tasks.json access (race conditions)\n- The heartbeat already runs every ~15 min — that's the right cadence for dispatching one task at a time\n\n**How it works:**\n1. At 01:00, a cron job fires a `systemEvent` to the main session: `\"Night Shift check — evaluate and activate if conditions met\"`\n2. The heartbeat handler checks Night Shift activation conditions\n3. If active, the heartbeat enters Night Shift mode for that cycle\n4. Subsequent heartbeats during 01:00-07:00 continue Night Shift until it completes or hits a stop condition\n5. A `night-shift-state.json` file persists state across heartbeat cycles (current task, count, tokens used)\n\n### Coexisting with Existing Nighttime Jobs\n\nCurrent nighttime cron jobs:\n- **02:00 UTC (03:00 BST)** — Sessions Cleanup (systemEvent, 12ms, lightweight)\n- **04:00 UTC (05:00 BST)** — Session Auto-Expiry (shell script, 11ms, lightweight)\n- **06:00 Europe/London** — Auto-update FreeRide (agentTurn, ~52s, isolated)\n\nThese are all lightweight infrastructure tasks. Night Shift is the only one that dispatches work tasks. No conflict — they operate on different concerns.\n\n**Key timing:**\n- 01:00 BST → Night Shift activation check\n- 02:00 UTC (03:00 BST) → Sessions Cleanup runs (no conflict)\n- 04:00 UTC (05:00 BST) → Session Auto-Expiry runs (no conflict)\n- 06:00 BST → FreeRide update runs (no conflict)\n- 06:30 BST → Night Shift stops starting new tasks\n- 07:00 BST → Night Shift sends morning report\n\n---\n\n## 2. Activation Conditions\n\nALL must be true to enter Night Shift:\n\n| Condition | How to check |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| **Time is 01:00-07:00 BST** | Current hour in Europe/London timezone |\n| **Dispatchable backlog exists** | Count tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`, no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, `wasStalled: false`, AND `nightShiftEligible: true` |\n| **Rate limits healthy** | No 429 errors in the last 30 min (check gateway log or error feed) |\n| **Andre is away** | No messages from Andre in the last 2 hours (check session activity) |\n\nIf any condition fails → skip Night Shift this cycle, log reason.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Task Eligibility\n\nNot all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\n\n**Must have:**\n- `status: \"backlog\"`\n- `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\n- `stalledAt` not set\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\n- `wasStalled: false`\n\n**Must NOT have:**\n- `priority: \"P1\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\n- Tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n- `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\n\n**Sort order for pickup:**\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Safety Constraints\n\n### Hard Limits\n- **Max 5 tasks per night** — prevents burning through backlog\n- **No new tasks after 06:30** — wrap-up window\n- **Stop at 07:00 sharp** — even if a task is mid-work (move back to backlog)\n- **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded\n\n### Rate Limit Protection\n- Before each task dispatch, check for recent 429 errors\n- If 429s detected → pause Night Shift, log reason, send alert\n- Never retry a failed task more than once per night\n\n### Forbidden Actions\n- Never modify `openclaw.json`\n- Never modify LaunchAgents or LaunchDaemons\n- Never modify cron jobs\n- Never modify the gateway config\n- Never touch `work-dispatcher.sh.disabled`\n- Never delete tasks — only move to Done with summary\n- Never dispatch P1 tasks at night\n\n### Sub-agent Constraints\n- Each sub-agent gets a 15-minute timeout\n- Sub-agent must update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5 min\n- Sub-agent must write a completion summary before marking done\n- If a sub-agent fails, the task goes back to backlog with failure note — no retry\n\n---\n\n## 5. State Persistence\n\nA `data/night-shift-state.json` file tracks Night Shift across heartbeat cycles:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"active\": true,\n  \"date\": \"2026-06-03\",\n  \"startedAt\": \"2026-06-03T01:00:00+01:00\",\n  \"tasksCompleted\": [],\n  \"tasksAttempted\": 0,\n  \"tasksFailed\": [],\n  \"tokensUsed\": 0,\n  \"currentTask\": null,\n  \"stoppedReason\": null\n}\n```\n\nThis file is:\n- Created when Night Shift activates\n- Updated after each task completes or fails\n- Read at each heartbeat during Night Shift hours\n- Reset when Night Shift ends (moved to `data/night-shift-archive/`)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Morning Report\n\nSent via Telegram at 07:00 BST:\n\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\n✅ Completed: X tasks\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n\nFailed:\n• [Task title] — [reason]\n\nBacklog remaining: N tasks\n```\n\nIf zero tasks were completed, the report is still sent (so Andre knows the system is working):\n\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\nNo tasks completed.\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\nBacklog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 7. Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| **Token exhaustion** | Run out of tokens before morning, Andre wakes to dead system | 50K token hard limit. Check token usage before each dispatch. |\n| **Sub-agent runaway** | Tool-call loop burns tokens on one task | 15-min timeout per sub-agent. Max 1 retry per task. |\n| **tasks.json corruption** | Rapid-fire saves from multiple heartbeats | Only ONE task transition per heartbeat. Atomic read-modify-write. |\n| **Rate limit cascade** | Night Shift triggers 429s that affect morning work | Check 429s before each dispatch. Stop immediately on detection. |\n| **Andre wakes up mid-shift** | Andre sends a message while Night Shift is working | Check for recent Andre activity each heartbeat. If detected, pause Night Shift gracefully. |\n| **Sub-agent produces bad code** | Night Shift commits broken code | Sub-agents must verify app loads (port 3000 returns 200) before marking done. |\n| **P1 task gets dispatched** | Important task worked on without Andre's awareness | P1 tasks are explicitly excluded from Night Shift eligibility. |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Testing Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Dry Run (no actual dispatch)\n- Manually trigger Night Shift logic at a non-night hour\n- Log what it WOULD do without spawning sub-agents\n- Verify eligibility filtering works correctly\n- Verify activation conditions evaluate correctly\n\n### Phase 2: Single Task Test\n- At a convenient hour, manually trigger Night Shift with a limit of 1 task\n- Use a small, well-defined task (like the \"Move Incident ShortCut\" test)\n- Verify: dispatch → work → completion → summary → state file update\n- Verify: morning report format (trigger manually)\n\n### Phase 3: Full Night Test\n- Enable the 01:00 activation cron\n- Let it run overnight with real tasks\n- Review morning report\n- Check tasks.json for proper state transitions\n- Verify no forbidden actions were taken\n\n### Phase 4: Edge Cases\n- Test with 0 eligible tasks (should report \"no tasks\")\n- Test with rate limit active (should pause and report)\n- Test with Andre sending a message at 03:00 (should pause gracefully)\n- Test at 06:30 boundary (should stop starting new tasks)\n\n---\n\n## 9. Changes Needed\n\n### New files:\n- `NIGHT_SHIFT.md` — this document\n- `data/night-shift-state.json` — runtime state\n- `data/night-shift-archive/` — historical reports\n\n### Modified files:\n- `HEARTBEAT.md` — add Night Shift section with activation logic, dispatch rules, and stop conditions\n- `data/tasks.json` — add `nightShiftEligible` field to task schema (default: true)\n\n### New cron job:\n- `0 1 * * *` Europe/London — Night Shift activation check (systemEvent to main session)\n\n### No changes to:\n- `openclaw.json`\n- LaunchAgents / LaunchDaemons\n- Existing cron jobs\n- Gateway config\n\n---\n\n## 10. Open Questions\n\n1. **Should Night Shift use crew agents or generic sub-agents?**\n   - Proposal: Generic sub-agents. Crew agents (lifesupport, engineer, archivist) are named personas without separate sessions. The sub-agent brief can include role context.\n\n2. **What if a task takes longer than the 06:30 cutoff?**\n   - Proposal: The in-progress task gets moved back to backlog with a note \"Night Shift partial — resumed by Andre.\" No penalty to dispatchCount.\n\n3. **Should Night Shift run every night or only on weekdays?**\n   - Proposal: Every night. Andre can disable by setting a `nightShiftEnabled: false` flag in tasks.json.\n\n4. **What about the existing \"Dreaming\" concept?**\n   - Dreaming was a periodic self-reflection cron (now removed). Night Shift replaces it with productive work. No conflict.\n\n---\n\n_Design version 1.0 — 2026-06-03_\n_Ready for Andre's review before implementation._\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\", \"content\": \"# NIGHT SHIFT — Design Document\\n\\n_Autonomous task processing during 01:00-07:00 when Andre is asleep._\\n\\n**Status:** Design only — not yet implemented\\n**Created:** 2026-06-03\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 1. Architecture\\n\\n### Integration with Heartbeat\\n\\nNight Shift is **not a separate cron job**. It's a mode within the existing heartbeat cycle.\\n\\n**Why heartbeat, not cron:**\\n- The heartbeat already has the context to pick tasks, spawn sub-agents, and update task state\\n- A separate cron would compete with the heartbeat for tasks.json access (race conditions)\\n- The heartbeat already runs every ~15 min — that's the right cadence for dispatching one task at a time\\n\\n**How it works:**\\n1. At 01:00, a cron job fires a `systemEvent` to the main session: `\\\"Night Shift check — evaluate and activate if conditions met\\\"`\\n2. The heartbeat handler checks Night Shift activation conditions\\n3. If active, the heartbeat enters Night Shift mode for that cycle\\n4. Subsequent heartbeats during 01:00-07:00 continue Night Shift until it completes or hits a stop condition\\n5. A `night-shift-state.json` file persists state across heartbeat cycles (current task, count, tokens used)\\n\\n### Coexisting with Existing Nighttime Jobs\\n\\nCurrent nighttime cron jobs:\\n- **02:00 UTC (03:00 BST)** — Sessions Cleanup (systemEvent, 12ms, lightweight)\\n- **04:00 UTC (05:00 BST)** — Session Auto-Expiry (shell script, 11ms, lightweight)\\n- **06:00 Europe/London** — Auto-update FreeRide (agentTurn, ~52s, isolated)\\n\\nThese are all lightweight infrastructure tasks. Night Shift is the only one that dispatches work tasks. No conflict — they operate on different concerns.\\n\\n**Key timing:**\\n- 01:00 BST → Night Shift activation check\\n- 02:00 UTC (03:00 BST) → Sessions Cleanup runs (no conflict)\\n- 04:00 UTC (05:00 BST) → Session Auto-Expiry runs (no conflict)\\n- 06:00 BST → FreeRide update runs (no conflict)\\n- 06:30 BST → Night Shift stops starting new tasks\\n- 07:00 BST → Night Shift sends morning report\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. Activation Conditions\\n\\nALL must be true to enter Night Shift:\\n\\n| Condition | How to check |\\n|-----------|-------------|\\n| **Time is 01:00-07:00 BST** | Current hour in Europe/London timezone |\\n| **Dispatchable backlog exists** | Count tasks with `status: \\\"backlog\\\"`, no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, `wasStalled: false`, AND `nightShiftEligible: true` |\\n| **Rate limits healthy** | No 429 errors in the last 30 min (check gateway log or error feed) |\\n| **Andre is away** | No messages from Andre in the last 2 hours (check session activity) |\\n\\nIf any condition fails → skip Night Shift this cycle, log reason.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. Task Eligibility\\n\\nNot all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\\n\\n**Must have:**\\n- `status: \\\"backlog\\\"`\\n- `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\\n- `stalledAt` not set\\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\\n- `wasStalled: false`\\n\\n**Must NOT have:**\\n- `priority: \\\"P1\\\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\\n- Tags: `\\\"needs-human-input\\\"`, `\\\"planning\\\"`, `\\\"design\\\"`, `\\\"roadmap\\\"`\\n- `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\\n\\n**Sort order for pickup:**\\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 4. Safety Constraints\\n\\n### Hard Limits\\n- **Max 5 tasks per night** — prevents burning through backlog\\n- **No new tasks after 06:30** — wrap-up window\\n- **Stop at 07:00 sharp** — even if a task is mid-work (move back to backlog)\\n- **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded\\n\\n### Rate Limit Protection\\n- Before each task dispatch, check for recent 429 errors\\n- If 429s detected → pause Night Shift, log reason, send alert\\n- Never retry a failed task more than once per night\\n\\n### Forbidden Actions\\n- Never modify `openclaw.json`\\n- Never modify LaunchAgents or LaunchDaemons\\n- Never modify cron jobs\\n- Never modify the gateway config\\n- Never touch `work-dispatcher.sh.disabled`\\n- Never delete tasks — only move to Done with summary\\n- Never dispatch P1 tasks at night\\n\\n### Sub-agent Constraints\\n- Each sub-agent gets a 15-minute timeout\\n- Sub-agent must update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5 min\\n- Sub-agent must write a completion summary before marking done\\n- If a sub-agent fails, the task goes back to backlog with failure note — no retry\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 5. State Persistence\\n\\nA `data/night-shift-state.json` file tracks Night Shift across heartbeat cycles:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"active\\\": true,\\n  \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-06-03\\\",\\n  \\\"startedAt\\\": \\\"2026-06-03T01:00:00+01:00\\\",\\n  \\\"tasksCompleted\\\": [],\\n  \\\"tasksAttempted\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"tasksFailed\\\": [],\\n  \\\"tokensUsed\\\": 0,\\n  \\\"currentTask\\\": null,\\n  \\\"stoppedReason\\\": null\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis file is:\\n- Created when Night Shift activates\\n- Updated after each task completes or fails\\n- Read at each heartbeat during Night Shift hours\\n- Reset when Night Shift ends (moved to `data/night-shift-archive/`)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 6. Morning Report\\n\\nSent via Telegram at 07:00 BST:\\n\\n```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\n✅ Completed: X tasks\\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n\\nFailed:\\n• [Task title] — [reason]\\n\\nBacklog remaining: N tasks\\n```\\n\\nIf zero tasks were completed, the report is still sent (so Andre knows the system is working):\\n\\n```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\nNo tasks completed.\\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\\nBacklog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 7. Risks and Mitigations\\n\\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\\n|------|--------|------------|\\n| **Token exhaustion** | Run out of tokens before morning, Andre wakes to dead system | 50K token hard limit. Check token usage before each dispatch. |\\n| **Sub-agent runaway** | Tool-call loop burns tokens on one task | 15-min timeout per sub-agent. Max 1 retry per task. |\\n| **tasks.json corruption** | Rapid-fire saves from multiple heartbeats | Only ONE task transition per heartbeat. Atomic read-modify-write. |\\n| **Rate limit cascade** | Night Shift triggers 429s that affect morning work | Check 429s before each dispatch. Stop immediately on detection. |\\n| **Andre wakes up mid-shift** | Andre sends a message while Night Shift is working | Check for recent Andre activity each heartbeat. If detected, pause Night Shift gracefully. |\\n| **Sub-agent produces bad code** | Night Shift commits broken code | Sub-agents must verify app loads (port 3000 returns 200) before marking done. |\\n| **P1 task gets dispatched** | Important task worked on without Andre's awareness | P1 tasks are explicitly excluded from Night Shift eligibility. |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 8. Testing Plan\\n\\n### Phase 1: Dry Run (no actual dispatch)\\n- Manually trigger Night Shift logic at a non-night hour\\n- Log what it WOULD do without spawning sub-agents\\n- Verify eligibility filtering works correctly\\n- Verify activation conditions evaluate correctly\\n\\n### Phase 2: Single Task Test\\n- At a convenient hour, manually trigger Night Shift with a limit of 1 task\\n- Use a small, well-defined task (like the \\\"Move Incident ShortCut\\\" test)\\n- Verify: dispatch → work → completion → summary → state file update\\n- Verify: morning report format (trigger manually)\\n\\n### Phase 3: Full Night Test\\n- Enable the 01:00 activation cron\\n- Let it run overnight with real tasks\\n- Review morning report\\n- Check tasks.json for proper state transitions\\n- Verify no forbidden actions were taken\\n\\n### Phase 4: Edge Cases\\n- Test with 0 eligible tasks (should report \\\"no tasks\\\")\\n- Test with rate limit active (should pause and report)\\n- Test with Andre sending a message at 03:00 (should pause gracefully)\\n- Test at 06:30 boundary (should stop starting new tasks)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 9. Changes Needed\\n\\n### New files:\\n- `NIGHT_SHIFT.md` — this document\\n- `data/night-shift-state.json` — runtime state\\n- `data/night-shift-archive/` — historical reports\\n\\n### Modified files:\\n- `HEARTBEAT.md` — add Night Shift section with activation logic, dispatch rules, and stop conditions\\n- `data/tasks.json` — add `nightShiftEligible` field to task schema (default: true)\\n\\n### New cron job:\\n- `0 1 * * *` Europe/London — Night Shift activation check (systemEvent to main session)\\n\\n### No changes to:\\n- `openclaw.json`\\n- LaunchAgents / LaunchDaemons\\n- Existing cron jobs\\n- Gateway config\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 10. Open Questions\\n\\n1. **Should Night Shift use crew agents or generic sub-agents?**\\n   - Proposal: Generic sub-agents. Crew agents (lifesupport, engineer, archivist) are named personas without separate sessions. The sub-agent brief can include role context.\\n\\n2. **What if a task takes longer than the 06:30 cutoff?**\\n   - Proposal: The in-progress task gets moved back to backlog with a note \\\"Night Shift partial — resumed by Andre.\\\" No penalty to dispatchCount.\\n\\n3. **Should Night Shift run every night or only on weekdays?**\\n   - Proposal: Every night. Andre can disable by setting a `nightShiftEnabled: false` flag in tasks.json.\\n\\n4. **What about the existing \\\"Dreaming\\\" concept?**\\n   - Dreaming was a periodic self-reflection cron (now removed). Night Shift replaces it with productive work. No conflict.\\n\\n---\\n\\n_Design version 1.0 — 2026-06-03_\\n_Ready for Andre's review before implementation._\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1475,"output":2510,"cacheRead":81536,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":85521,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780509772249,"responseId":"gen-1780509772-dzsqFMioEHdaCZOBE6Fl"}}
