{"type":"message","id":"26718c95","parentId":"a2865099","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:10:14.948Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"5c672f5e-99a2-400a-9944-7daf8f302888","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 2 block(s) in /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  60 ---\n  61 \n  62 ## 3. Task Eligibility\n  63 \n- 64 Not all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\n+ 64 Not all backlog tasks qualify. Eligibility is determined **automatically** by the system at dispatch time — no manual tagging required.\n  65 \n- 66 **Must have:**\n+ 66 **Automatically eligible:**\n  67 - `status: \"backlog\"`\n- 68 - `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\n  69 - `stalledAt` not set\n  70 - `dispatchCount < 3`\n  71 - `wasStalled: false`\n+ 71 - Priority is P2 or P3 (P1 excluded)\n+ 72 - No exclusion tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n  72 \n- 73 **Must NOT have:**\n- 74 - `priority: \"P1\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\n- 75 - Tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n- 76 - `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\n+ 74 **Manual override:**\n+ 75 - `nightShiftEligible: false` — Andre can opt out a specific task\n+ 76 - This is the exception, not the rule. Most tasks never need this field.\n  77 \n  78 **Sort order for pickup:**\n  79 1. Priority: P2 before P3\n  80 2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\n     ...\n  86 ### Hard Limits\n  87 - **Max 5 tasks per night** — prevents burning through backlog\n  88 - **No new tasks after 06:30** — wrap-up window\n  89 - **Stop at 07:00 sharp** — even if a task is mid-work (move back to backlog)\n- 90 - **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded\n+ 90 - **Max 100K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit)\n  91 \n  92 ### Rate Limit Protection\n  93 - Before each task dispatch, check for recent 429 errors\n  94 - If 429s detected → pause Night Shift, log reason, send alert\n     ...","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\n@@ -60,21 +60,21 @@\n ---\n \n ## 3. Task Eligibility\n \n-Not all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\n+Not all backlog tasks qualify. Eligibility is determined **automatically** by the system at dispatch time — no manual tagging required.\n \n-**Must have:**\n+**Automatically eligible:**\n - `status: \"backlog\"`\n-- `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\n - `stalledAt` not set\n - `dispatchCount < 3`\n - `wasStalled: false`\n+- Priority is P2 or P3 (P1 excluded)\n+- No exclusion tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n \n-**Must NOT have:**\n-- `priority: \"P1\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\n-- Tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n-- `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\n+**Manual override:**\n+- `nightShiftEligible: false` — Andre can opt out a specific task\n+- This is the exception, not the rule. Most tasks never need this field.\n \n **Sort order for pickup:**\n 1. Priority: P2 before P3\n 2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\n@@ -86,9 +86,9 @@\n ### Hard Limits\n - **Max 5 tasks per night** — prevents burning through backlog\n - **No new tasks after 06:30** — wrap-up window\n - **Stop at 07:00 sharp** — even if a task is mid-work (move back to backlog)\n-- **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded\n+- **Max 100K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit)\n \n ### Rate Limit Protection\n - Before each task dispatch, check for recent 429 errors\n - If 429s detected → pause Night Shift, log reason, send alert\n","firstChangedLine":64},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780510214947}}
{"type":"message","id":"e526be79","parentId":"26718c95","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:10:47.766Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update the morning report section:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"4081458a-47e7-440d-b9f9-c34324a286bf","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":40,"offset":115,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 40, \"offset\": 115, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":650,"output":54,"cacheRead":88192,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":88896,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780510214953,"responseId":"gen-1780510215-b7aB4YUc7XCO8fsPbZVo"}}
{"type":"message","id":"09ea651e","parentId":"e526be79","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:10:47.784Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"4081458a-47e7-440d-b9f9-c34324a286bf","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nA `data/night-shift-state.json` file tracks Night Shift across heartbeat cycles:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"active\": true,\n  \"date\": \"2026-06-03\",\n  \"startedAt\": \"2026-06-03T01:00:00+01:00\",\n  \"tasksCompleted\": [],\n  \"tasksAttempted\": 0,\n  \"tasksFailed\": [],\n  \"tokensUsed\": 0,\n  \"currentTask\": null,\n  \"stoppedReason\": null\n}\n```\n\nThis file is:\n- Created when Night Shift activates\n- Updated after each task completes or fails\n- Read at each heartbeat during Night Shift hours\n- Reset when Night Shift ends (moved to `data/night-shift-archive/`)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Morning Report\n\nSent via Telegram at 07:00 BST:\n\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\n✅ Completed: X tasks\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n\n[103 more lines in file. Use offset=155 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780510247784}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ef9bd61","parentId":"09ea651e","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:11:20.390Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ce90654e-1f78-4211-a5fa-20642bdfd477","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\n✅ Completed: X tasks\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n\nFailed:\n• [Task title] — [reason]\n\nBacklog remaining: N tasks\n```\n\nIf zero tasks were completed, the report is still sent (so Andre knows the system is working):\n\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\nNo tasks completed.\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\nBacklog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n```","newText":"```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\n✅ Completed: X tasks\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n\nFailed:\n• [Task title] — [reason]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n```\n\nIf zero tasks were completed:\n\n```\n🟥 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\nNo tasks completed.\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n```"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\n✅ Completed: X tasks\\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n\\nFailed:\\n• [Task title] — [reason]\\n\\nBacklog remaining: N tasks\\n```\\n\\nIf zero tasks were completed, the report is still sent (so Andre knows the system is working):\\n\\n```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\nNo tasks completed.\\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\\nBacklog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\\n```\", \"newText\": \"```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\n✅ Completed: X tasks\\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n\\nFailed:\\n• [Task title] — [reason]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\\n```\\n\\nIf zero tasks were completed:\\n\\n```\\n🟥 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\nNo tasks completed.\\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\\n```\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":360,"output":553,"cacheRead":88832,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":89745,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780510247791,"responseId":"gen-1780510247-xAUZHTKW6UiPpzWn0Npl"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fda7ce15","parentId":"4ef9bd61","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:11:20.413Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ce90654e-1f78-4211-a5fa-20642bdfd477","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 155 \n 156 Failed:\n 157 • [Task title] — [reason]\n 158 \n-159 Backlog remaining: N tasks\n+159 ── Station Status ──\n+160 💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n+161 🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n+162 ⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n+163 📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n 160 ```\n 161 \n-162 If zero tasks were completed, the report is still sent (so Andre knows the system is working):\n+166 If zero tasks were completed:\n 163 \n 164 ```\n-165 🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n+169 🟥 Night Shift Report — [date]\n 166 \n 167 No tasks completed.\n 168 Reason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\n-169 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n+173 \n+174 ── Station Status ──\n+175 💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n+176 🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n+177 ⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n+178 📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n 170 ```\n 171 \n 172 ---\n 173 \n     ...","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\n@@ -155,19 +155,28 @@\n \n Failed:\n • [Task title] — [reason]\n \n-Backlog remaining: N tasks\n+── Station Status ──\n+💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n+🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n+⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n+📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n ```\n \n-If zero tasks were completed, the report is still sent (so Andre knows the system is working):\n+If zero tasks were completed:\n \n ```\n-🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n+🟥 Night Shift Report — [date]\n \n No tasks completed.\n Reason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\n-Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n+\n+── Station Status ──\n+💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n+🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n+⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n+📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n ```\n \n ---\n \n","firstChangedLine":159},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780510280410}}
{"type":"message","id":"319b0e3b","parentId":"fda7ce15","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:11:54.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Also update the open questions to reflect the eligibility decision:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"367e1d4a-b007-4b9f-9f4c-a49259f4d930","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## 10. Open Questions\n\n1. **Should Night Shift use crew agents or generic sub-agents?**\n   - Proposal: Generic sub-agents. Crew agents (lifesupport, engineer, archivist) are named personas without separate sessions. The sub-agent brief can include role context.\n\n2. **What if a task takes longer than the 06:30 cutoff?**\n   - Proposal: The in-progress task gets moved back to backlog with a note \"Night Shift partial — resumed by Andre.\" No penalty to dispatchCount.\n\n3. **Should Night Shift run every night or only on weekdays?**\n   - Proposal: Every night. Andre can disable by setting a `nightShiftEnabled: false` flag in tasks.json.\n\n4. **What about the existing \"Dreaming\" concept?**\n   - Dreaming was a periodic self-reflection cron (now removed). Night Shift replaces it with productive work. No conflict.","newText":"## 10. Resolved Design Decisions\n\n1. **`nightShiftEligible` field:** Not a manual tagging requirement. Eligibility is auto-determined from existing fields (priority, tags, dispatch status). The field exists only as a manual override (`false`) for edge cases.\n\n2. **Token limit:** 100K total per night (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit).\n\n3. **Morning report includes station status:** Disk usage, overnight incidents, gateway uptime — not just task summaries.\n\n4. **Dry run test:** Can be executed immediately in any session — no code changes needed. Simulates full Night Shift logic and logs what it WOULD do.\n\n5. **Sub-agents vs crew agents:** Generic sub-agents. Crew personas are context, not separate sessions.\n\n6. **06:30 cutoff task handling:** In-progress task moved back to backlog with \"Night Shift partial\" note. No dispatchCount penalty.\n\n7. **Frequency:** Every night. Andre can disable via `nightShiftEnabled: false` in tasks.json.\n\n8. **Dreaming concept:** Superseded by Night Shift. No conflict — different purpose (productive work vs reflection)."}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"## 10. Open Questions\\n\\n1. **Should Night Shift use crew agents or generic sub-agents?**\\n   - Proposal: Generic sub-agents. Crew agents (lifesupport, engineer, archivist) are named personas without separate sessions. The sub-agent brief can include role context.\\n\\n2. **What if a task takes longer than the 06:30 cutoff?**\\n   - Proposal: The in-progress task gets moved back to backlog with a note \\\"Night Shift partial — resumed by Andre.\\\" No penalty to dispatchCount.\\n\\n3. **Should Night Shift run every night or only on weekdays?**\\n   - Proposal: Every night. Andre can disable by setting a `nightShiftEnabled: false` flag in tasks.json.\\n\\n4. **What about the existing \\\"Dreaming\\\" concept?**\\n   - Dreaming was a periodic self-reflection cron (now removed). Night Shift replaces it with productive work. No conflict.\", \"newText\": \"## 10. Resolved Design Decisions\\n\\n1. **`nightShiftEligible` field:** Not a manual tagging requirement. Eligibility is auto-determined from existing fields (priority, tags, dispatch status). The field exists only as a manual override (`false`) for edge cases.\\n\\n2. **Token limit:** 100K total per night (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit).\\n\\n3. **Morning report includes station status:** Disk usage, overnight incidents, gateway uptime — not just task summaries.\\n\\n4. **Dry run test:** Can be executed immediately in any session — no code changes needed. Simulates full Night Shift logic and logs what it WOULD do.\\n\\n5. **Sub-agents vs crew agents:** Generic sub-agents. Crew personas are context, not separate sessions.\\n\\n6. **06:30 cutoff task handling:** In-progress task moved back to backlog with \\\"Night Shift partial\\\" note. No dispatchCount penalty.\\n\\n7. **Frequency:** Every night. Andre can disable via `nightShiftEnabled: false` in tasks.json.\\n\\n8. **Dreaming concept:** Superseded by Night Shift. No conflict — different purpose (productive work vs reflection).\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":653,"output":527,"cacheRead":89088,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":90268,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780510280417,"responseId":"gen-1780510280-MLuVuboKeCLRHvBEZrln"}}
{"type":"message","id":"77794958","parentId":"319b0e3b","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:11:54.357Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"367e1d4a-b007-4b9f-9f4c-a49259f4d930","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 244 - Gateway config\n 245 \n 246 ---\n 247 \n-248 ## 10. Open Questions\n+248 ## 10. Resolved Design Decisions\n 249 \n-250 1. **Should Night Shift use crew agents or generic sub-agents?**\n-251    - Proposal: Generic sub-agents. Crew agents (lifesupport, engineer, archivist) are named personas without separate sessions. The sub-agent brief can include role context.\n+250 1. **`nightShiftEligible` field:** Not a manual tagging requirement. Eligibility is auto-determined from existing fields (priority, tags, dispatch status). The field exists only as a manual override (`false`) for edge cases.\n 252 \n-253 2. **What if a task takes longer than the 06:30 cutoff?**\n-254    - Proposal: The in-progress task gets moved back to backlog with a note \"Night Shift partial — resumed by Andre.\" No penalty to dispatchCount.\n+252 2. **Token limit:** 100K total per night (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit).\n 255 \n-256 3. **Should Night Shift run every night or only on weekdays?**\n-257    - Proposal: Every night. Andre can disable by setting a `nightShiftEnabled: false` flag in tasks.json.\n+254 3. **Morning report includes station status:** Disk usage, overnight incidents, gateway uptime — not just task summaries.\n 258 \n-259 4. **What about the existing \"Dreaming\" concept?**\n-260    - Dreaming was a periodic self-reflection cron (now removed). Night Shift replaces it with productive work. No conflict.\n+256 4. **Dry run test:** Can be executed immediately in any session — no code changes needed. Simulates full Night Shift logic and logs what it WOULD do.\n 261 \n+258 5. **Sub-agents vs crew agents:** Generic sub-agents. Crew personas are context, not separate sessions.\n+259 \n+260 6. **06:30 cutoff task handling:** In-progress task moved back to backlog with \"Night Shift partial\" note. No dispatchCount penalty.\n+261 \n+262 7. **Frequency:** Every night. Andre can disable via `nightShiftEnabled: false` in tasks.json.\n+263 \n+264 8. **Dreaming concept:** Superseded by Night Shift. No conflict — different purpose (productive work vs reflection).\n+265 \n 262 ---\n 263 \n 264 _Design version 1.0 — 2026-06-03_\n 265 _Ready for Andre's review before implementation._","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\n@@ -244,22 +244,26 @@\n - Gateway config\n \n ---\n \n-## 10. Open Questions\n+## 10. Resolved Design Decisions\n \n-1. **Should Night Shift use crew agents or generic sub-agents?**\n-   - Proposal: Generic sub-agents. Crew agents (lifesupport, engineer, archivist) are named personas without separate sessions. The sub-agent brief can include role context.\n+1. **`nightShiftEligible` field:** Not a manual tagging requirement. Eligibility is auto-determined from existing fields (priority, tags, dispatch status). The field exists only as a manual override (`false`) for edge cases.\n \n-2. **What if a task takes longer than the 06:30 cutoff?**\n-   - Proposal: The in-progress task gets moved back to backlog with a note \"Night Shift partial — resumed by Andre.\" No penalty to dispatchCount.\n+2. **Token limit:** 100K total per night (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit).\n \n-3. **Should Night Shift run every night or only on weekdays?**\n-   - Proposal: Every night. Andre can disable by setting a `nightShiftEnabled: false` flag in tasks.json.\n+3. **Morning report includes station status:** Disk usage, overnight incidents, gateway uptime — not just task summaries.\n \n-4. **What about the existing \"Dreaming\" concept?**\n-   - Dreaming was a periodic self-reflection cron (now removed). Night Shift replaces it with productive work. No conflict.\n+4. **Dry run test:** Can be executed immediately in any session — no code changes needed. Simulates full Night Shift logic and logs what it WOULD do.\n \n+5. **Sub-agents vs crew agents:** Generic sub-agents. Crew personas are context, not separate sessions.\n+\n+6. **06:30 cutoff task handling:** In-progress task moved back to backlog with \"Night Shift partial\" note. No dispatchCount penalty.\n+\n+7. **Frequency:** Every night. Andre can disable via `nightShiftEnabled: false` in tasks.json.\n+\n+8. **Dreaming concept:** Superseded by Night Shift. No conflict — different purpose (productive work vs reflection).\n+\n ---\n \n _Design version 1.0 — 2026-06-03_\n _Ready for Andre's review before implementation._\n","firstChangedLine":248},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780510314355}}
