{"type":"message","id":"ef54c235","parentId":"fe9c95fa","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:38:35.198Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"As expected — the sub-agent didn't update `currentStep` or `lastActivity` during work. It completed in 9.6 minutes so stall detection wouldn't have fired, but for longer tasks this would be a problem. The HEARTBEAT.md instructions are clear; I need to make the sub-agent spawn template even more explicit. Let me update it:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"18016a62-d413-4fa4-81ee-7a6f6b0306cc","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\n  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action before starting work\n  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at each step\n  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 50% midway, 100% done)\n  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\n  - Commit and push code changes when complete","newText":"- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\n  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action BEFORE starting work (e.g. \"Reading tasks.tsx\")\n  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at EACH step\n  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 25% early, 50% midway, 75% late, 100% done)\n  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\n  - Commit and push code changes when complete\n  - **Use a Python script to update tasks.json — do NOT edit manually. Example:**\n    ```python\n    import json\n    from datetime import datetime, timezone\n    with open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\n        tasks = json.load(f)\n    for t in tasks:\n        if t['id'] == 'TASK_ID_HERE':\n            t['currentStep'] = 'Specific action'\n            t['progress'] = 50\n            t['lastActivity'] = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n            break\n    with open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json', 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\n    ```\n  - Run this update at EVERY meaningful step — not just at start and completion"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\\n  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action before starting work\\n  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at each step\\n  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 50% midway, 100% done)\\n  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\\n  - Commit and push code changes when complete\", \"newText\": \"- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\\n  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action BEFORE starting work (e.g. \\\"Reading tasks.tsx\\\")\\n  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at EACH step\\n  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 25% early, 50% midway, 75% late, 100% done)\\n  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\\n  - Commit and push code changes when complete\\n  - **Use a Python script to update tasks.json — do NOT edit manually. Example:**\\n    ```python\\n    import json\\n    from datetime import datetime, timezone\\n    with open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\\n        tasks = json.load(f)\\n    for t in tasks:\\n        if t['id'] == 'TASK_ID_HERE':\\n            t['currentStep'] = 'Specific action'\\n            t['progress'] = 50\\n            t['lastActivity'] = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\\n            break\\n    with open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json', 'w') as f:\\n        json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\\n    ```\\n  - Run this update at EVERY meaningful step — not just at start a