{"type":"message","id":"8b6a2a2a","parentId":"29e45622","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:45:06.450Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"b24f6aaa-cb23-461f-97f7-f64691527214","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"fd0cb885-4912-46e5-bedb-47de3c43b0a7\",\n  \"agentId\": \"main\",\n  \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n  \"name\": \"Night Shift Activation\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1780512210401,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"0 1 * * *\",\n    \"tz\": \"Europe/London\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"main\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"systemEvent\",\n    \"text\": \"Night Shift activation check — evaluate conditions and activate if met. Read NIGHT_SHIFT.md for rules. Max 2 tasks tonight (first night trial).\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1780531200000\n  },\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1780512210401\n}"}],"details":{"id":"fd0cb885-4912-46e5-bedb-47de3c43b0a7","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:main","name":"Night Shift Activation","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1780512210401,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 1 * * *","tz":"Europe/London"},"sessionTarget":"main","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"systemEvent","text":"Night Shift activation check — evaluate conditions and activate if met. Read NIGHT_SHIFT.md for rules. Max 2 tasks tonight (first night trial)."},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1780531200000},"updatedAtMs":1780512210401},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780512306449}}
{"type":"message","id":"4046dbe3","parentId":"8b6a2a2a","timestamp":"2026-06-03T18:45:21.193Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is set up. Heartbeat clean — MC 200, 0 in_progress, 14 backlog, 67 done.\n\n**Night Shift is enabled for tonight:**\n\n- **Activation:** 01:00 BST via cron (`fd0cb885`)\n- **Max tasks:** 2 (first night trial)\n- **Eligible tasks:** 13 from the dry run (P2 operational work items)\n- **State file:** `data/night-shift-state.json` created\n- **Morning report:** Telegram at 07:00 with task summaries + station status\n\nAndre, you'll get the first morning report tomorrow at 07:00. If the first 2 nights go well, we bump to 5 tasks max.\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":412,"output":170,"cacheRead":101888,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":102470,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780512306455,"responseId":"gen-1780512306-Mlw0fGJ5UZPPNNPjuseO"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c50a93a9","parentId":"4046dbe3","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:02:00.449Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Night Shift is configured. For tomorrow's report: include not just \nwhat was done, but also whether agents updated progress during work. \nThe Phase 2 test showed agents only logging start and completion — \nno intermediate steps. This needs to improve.\n\nAlso: the currentProgress issue from earlier — tasks sitting In Progress \nfor hours with no movement. Make sure Night Shift tasks don't have the \nsame problem. If a Night Shift task stalls, it should return to Backlog \nbefore morning, not sit frozen for hours.","timestamp":1780513320330,"idempotencyKey":"a9067e24-cf73-4f77-823d-52792ab4c0dd:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"75e38090","parentId":"c50a93a9","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:02:14.899Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGot it. Two specific fixes for the morning report and stall handling. Let me update things now while it's fresh."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ee4723db-6882-4da8-bf24-3667ef3afadf","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":94047,"output":55,"cacheRead":9344,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":103446,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780513320453,"responseId":"gen-1780513320-tuYtptEg1P2ytxZtF6Og"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f490059c","parentId":"75e38090","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:02:14.945Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ee4723db-6882-4da8-bf24-3667ef3afadf","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Task Pickup\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- ONLY pick tasks that are truly dispatchable: no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\n- Sort by priority (P1 > P2 > P3), then by age (oldest first)\n- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- **The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` (ISO timestamp) every 5-10 min with specific actions** — NOT \"Agent starting…\". Example: \"Reading AppSidebar.tsx\", \"Editing nav order\", \"Verifying app loads\". Without `lastActivity` updates, stall detection cannot function.\n- Write completion summary before marking done\n- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\n  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action BEFORE starting work (e.g. \"Reading tasks.tsx\")\n  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at EACH step\n  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 25% early, 50% midway, 75% late, 100% done)\n  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\n  - Commit and push code changes when complete\n  - **Use a Python script to update tasks.json — do NOT edit manually. Example:**\n    ```python\n    import json\n    from datetime import datetime, timezone\n    with open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\n        tasks = json.load(f)\n    for t in tasks:\n        if t['id'] == 'TASK_ID_HERE':\n            t['currentStep'] = 'Specific action'\n            t['progress'] = 50\n            t['lastActivity'] = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n            break\n    with open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json', 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\n    ```\n  - Run this update at EVERY meaningful step — not just at start and completion\n- Only pick up ONE task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n- The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents\n- Crew task routing: infra → lifesupport, code → engineer, knowledge → archivist, unknown → monkey\n\n## Stall Detection (CRITICAL — check EVERY heartbeat)\n- For EVERY task with `status: \"in_progress\"`, calculate staleness:\n  - Use `lastActivity` if set and is a valid ISO timestamp\n  - Else use the `ts` field if it's a valid ISO timestamp (skip if it's \"just now\" or non-parseable)\n  - Else use the most recent `history[].ts` entry\n  - If NO valid timestamp can be found at all, treat as stalled (it's broken data)\n- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the heartbeat from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n- ALSO increment `dispatchCount` by 1 (set to at least 1 if not present). If `dispatchCount >= 3`, the dispatcher will skip the task entirely via its `dispatchCount < 3` filter. This is a secondary guard against the race condition where `stalledAt` gets cleared by the save-tasks merge logic.\n- If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning. If currentStep is still \"Agent starting…\" or null, reset immediately — the task was never actually picked up by an agent\n- The `startedAt` field is NOT reliable — do not use it for stall detection\n- After resetting, commit the change so the Kanban reflects reality immediately\n\n## Task Archive Maintenance\n- **Done tasks live in the Kanban Done column** — never remove them just because they're complete\n- Only archive done tasks older than 30 days to `data/tasks-archive.json`\n- When archiving: append to existing archive, remove from `tasks.json`, commit + push\n- The Done column should always show recent completions (last 30 days minimum)\n- Archive is for long-term storage only — the Kanban is the source of truth\n\n## Night Shift (01:00-07:00 BST)\n\nAutonomous task processing when Andre is asleep. Design doc: `NIGHT_SHIFT.md`.\n\n### Activation (triggered by cron at 01:00)\nALL conditions must be true:\n- Time is 01:00-07:00 BST\n- Dispatchable backlog tasks exist (see eligibility below)\n- No 429 rate limit errors in last 30 minutes\n- No Andre activity in last 2 hours\n\nIf any condition fails → log reason, skip Night Shift this cycle.\n\n### Task Eligibility\n- `status: \"backlog\"`, no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\n- Priority P2 or P3 only (P1 excluded)\n- No exclusion tags: `needs-human-input`, `planning`, `design`, `roadmap`\n- Sort: P2 before P3, then oldest first\n- **Max 2 tasks tonight** (first night trial — increase after 2 successful nights)\n- No new tasks after 06:30. Hard stop at 07:00.\n- Token limit: 100K total per night\n\n### Dispatch\n- Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\n- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min\n- On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\n- On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\n- Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message\n\n### Forbidden\n- Never modify openclaw.json, cron jobs, LaunchAgents, or gateway config\n- Never delete tasks — only move to Done with summary\n- Never dispatch P1 tasks\n- Max 5 min per sub-agent (kill if exceeded)\n\n### State\n- Track progress in `data/night-shift-state.json`\n- Archive to `data/night-shift-archive/` after each night\n\n### Morning Report (07:00)\nSend Telegram sitrep:\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task] — [one-line summary]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n```\n\n## Rule: Sub-agent Timeout\n- If a sub-agent runs for >5 minutes with no resolution, kill it and add the task to backlog\n- If the main agent spends >10 minutes debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n- Always report what was tried and what the blocker is when adding to backlog\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780513334944}}
{"type":"message","id":"0c6c45f6","parentId":"f490059c","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:02:46.071Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me update the Night Shift section with the two fixes:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"1c297f58-90a2-474b-90bc-17301b0645a8","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### Dispatch\n- Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\n- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min\n- On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\n- On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\n- Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message","newText":"### Dispatch\n- Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\n- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min — this is CRITICAL. Without intermediate updates, stall detection cannot function and the morning report cannot assess agent behavior.\n- **Night Shift stall rule:** If a task has been in_progress for >30 min with no `lastActivity` update (or currentStep still shows \"Agent starting…\"), reset it to backlog immediately. Do NOT let Night Shift tasks sit frozen. The 07:00 morning report should never show a task that's been stuck for hours.\n- On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\n- On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\n- Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message"},{"oldText":"### Morning Report (07:00)\nSend Telegram sitrep:\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task] — [one-line summary]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n```","newText":"### Morning Report (07:00)\nSend Telegram sitrep:\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task] — [one-line summary]\n  ↳ Progress updates: [N] intermediate steps logged — [good/needs improvement]\n\n── Agent Behavior ──\n📈 Tasks with intermediate progress updates: X/Y\n⚠️ Tasks that went straight start→complete with no steps: [list or \"None\"]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n```\n\n**Progress update assessment:** For each completed task, check its history. If there are no `progress` or `step_update` entries between `started` and `completed`, flag it. The goal is at least 2-3 intermediate updates per task."}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"### Dispatch\\n- Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\\n- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min\\n- On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\\n- On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\\n- Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message\", \"newText\": \"### Dispatch\\n- Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\\n- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min — this is CRITICAL. Without intermediate updates, stall detection cannot function and the morning report cannot assess agent behavior.\\n- **Night Shift stall rule:** If a task has been in_progress for >30 min with no `lastActivity` update (or currentStep still shows \\\"Agent starting…\\\"), reset it to backlog immediately. Do NOT let Night Shift tasks sit frozen. The 07:00 morning report should never show a task that's been stuck for hours.\\n- On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\\n- On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\\n- Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message\"}, {\"oldText\": \"### Morning Report (07:00)\\nSend Telegram sitrep:\\n```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task] — [one-line summary]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\\n```\", \"newText\": \"### Morning Report (07:00)\\nSend Telegram sitrep:\\n```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task] — [one-line summary]\\n  ↳ Progress updates: [N] intermediate steps logged — [good/needs improvement]\\n\\n── Agent Behavior ──\\n📈 Tasks with intermediate progress updates: X/Y\\n⚠️ Tasks that went straight start→complete with no steps: [list or \\\"None\\\"]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\\n```\\n\\n**Progress update assessment:** For each completed task, check its history. If there are no `progress` or `step_update` entries between `started` and `completed`, flag it. The goal is at least 2-3 intermediate updates per task.\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1804,"output":731,"cacheRead":103296,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":105831,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780513334950,"responseId":"gen-1780513335-h5GhM9MxtjNvFGIeZtii"}}
