{"type":"message","id":"6e8baf89","parentId":"5211974f","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:04:00.331Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"a6e60b93-cc66-4240-9c3c-c9b2f3ac90dc","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[main 3b38295] Night Shift: add progress tracking to morning report + strict stall rule for frozen tasks\n 2 files changed, 21 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":58,"aggregated":"[main 3b38295] Night Shift: add progress tracking to morning report + strict stall rule for frozen tasks\n 2 files changed, 21 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780513440330}}
{"type":"message","id":"0ce8adbc","parentId":"6e8baf89","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:04:18.695Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's what changed:\n\n**1. Morning report now has an Agent Behavior section:**\n- Shows how many tasks had intermediate progress progress updates\n- Names any tasks that went straight from start→complete with no steps\n- Includes an assessment of whether agents are properly logging their work\n\n**2. Night Shift stall rule is now strict:**\n- If a Night Shift task has been in_progress for >30 min with no `lastActivity` update → reset to backlog immediately\n- Frozen task (currentStep still \"Agent starting…\") → reset on the very next heartbeat\n- The morning report will never show a task that sat frozen for hours\n\n**3. Sub-agent briefs for Night Shift now include an explicit warning:** \"The morning report will flag tasks with no intermediate progress updates.\" This gives the sub-agent a concrete reason to run the Python update script at every step.\n\nEverything is set for tonight. The 01:00 cron will fire, Night Shift will activate if conditions are met, and I'll send you the first morning report at 07:00. 🌙"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":175,"output":225,"cacheRead":107392,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":107792,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780513440334,"responseId":"gen-1780513440-SrlVvEo7yjYDfEMCLgdk"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3618c100","parentId":"0ce8adbc","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:04:18.870Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"I want the system to work through the backlog autonomously, but with \nclear rules for when it gets stuck.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nRULES FOR PROCESSING BACKLOG\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. PICK UP THE NEXT TASK from Backlog based on priority (P1 first, \n   then P2, then P3) and age (oldest first within same priority).\n\n2. WORK ON IT until one of these happens:\n   ✅ COMPLETED — task is done, move to Done with full summary\n   ⚠️ BLOCKED — needs something you can't provide (my approval, \n      external access, a decision, clarification). Move to TRIAGE \n      with a clear note explaining what's needed.\n   ❓ UNCLEAR — the task description is ambiguous or too vague to \n      execute. Move to TRIAGE with specific questions.\n\n3. DO NOT leave a task In Progress indefinitely. If you hit a wall \n   after genuinely trying, move it to Triage. Don't let it sit \n   frozen for hours.\n\n4. ONE TASK AT A TIME per agent. Finish or triage the current task \n   before picking up the next.\n\n5. UPDATE PROGRESS at every step. The Kanban card must show:\n   - currentStep: what you're doing RIGHT NOW\n   - progress: 0-100 as you advance\n   - lastActivity: timestamp updated at least every 5-10 minutes\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nTRIAGE RULES\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nWhen moving a task to Triage, the Kanban card MUST include:\n- What was attempted\n- What's blocking progress\n- What specific action I need to take (approve? clarify? provide access?)\n- Any relevant context so I don't have to re-investigate\n\nThe Triage column is NOT a graveyard. It's where tasks go when they \nneed human input. I check Triage regularly and will move approved \ntasks back to Backlog.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nSTART NOW\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. Audit the current Backlog — what's the highest priority task?\n2. Pick it up, update currentStep, and start working\n3. If you complete it: Done with summary, pick up the next\n4. If you hit a wall: Triage with clear notes, pick up the next\n5. Keep going until you've processed as many as you can in this session\n\nReport: how many tasks did you complete, and how many went to Triage?","timestamp":1780513458790,"idempotencyKey":"811a0cf1-1c0a-4b5d-8d15-976a11b70a3a:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"228bb7a9","parentId":"3618c100","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:04:40.574Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood. This is the general backlog processing system — broader than Night Shift. Let me implement it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"56c12537-bb8e-4617-89e0-2cfdd444b482","name":"update_plan","arguments":{"plan":[{"step":"Audit backlog and set up Triage column","status":"in_progress"},{"step":"Process backlog tasks one at a time","status":"pending"},{"step":"Report results","status":"pending"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"plan\": [{\"step\": \"Audit backlog and set up Triage column\", \"status\": \"in_progress\"}, {\"step\": \"Process backlog tasks one at a time\", \"status\": \"pending\"}, {\"step\": \"Report results\", \"status\": \"pending\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":98490,"output":88,"cacheRead":10112,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":108690,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780513458874,"responseId":"gen-1780513459-X4tBMYbbMoYcYC68wMD8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"633741bf","parentId":"228bb7a9","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:04:40.617Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"56c12537-bb8e-4617-89e0-2cfdd444b482","toolName":"update_plan","content":[],"details":{"status":"updated","plan":[{"step":"Audit backlog and set up Triage column","status":"in_progress"},{"step":"Process backlog tasks one at a time","status":"pending"},{"step":"Report results","status":"pending"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780513480616}}
{"type":"message","id":"ec5679aa","parentId":"633741bf","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:05:08.605Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"First, let me check the current backlog and see if there's a Triage column in the Kanban:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"4d338455-a7d7-417e-a6a9-2e72591417f7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\n\ntasks_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'backlog']\nin_progress = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'in_progress']\ndone = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'done']\n\n# Check if any tasks have 'triage' status\ntriage = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'triage']\nprint(f\"Backlog: {len(backlog)}, In Progress: {len(in_progress)}, Done: {len(done)}, Triage: {len(triage)}\")\n\n# Sort backlog by priority then age\ndef sort_key(t):\n    prio = {'P1': 0, 'P2': 1, 'P3': 2}.get(t.get('priority', 'P3'), 3)\n    return (prio, t.get('ts', ''))\n\nbacklog.sort(key=sort_key)\n\nprint(f\"\\n=== BACKLOG (sorted by priority, then age) ===\")\nfor i, t in enumerate(backlog, 1):\n    notes_preview = (t.get('note','') or '')[:100].replace('\\n', ' ')\n    stalled = ' [STALLED]' if t.get('stalledAt') else ''\n    dc = t.get('dispatchCount', 0)\n    print(f\"{i:2}. [{t.get('priority','?')}] {t['id']}{stalled} (dc={dc})\")\n    print(f\"    {t['title'][:70]}\")\n    print(f\"    {notes_preview}\")\n    print()\n\n# Check Task type fields\nprint(\"=== TASK SCHEMA CHECK ===\")\nsample = backlog[0] if backlog else {}\nprint(f\"Fields in task: {list(sample.keys())}\")\nprint(f\"Has 'triage' status? {any(t.get('status') == 'triage' for t in tasks)}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\n\\ntasks_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\\\"\\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'backlog']\\nin_progress = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'in_progress']\\ndone = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'done']\\n\\n# Check if any tasks have 'triage' status\\ntriage = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'triage']\\nprint(f\\\"Backlog: {len(backlog)}, In Progress: {len(in_progress)}, Done: {len(done)}, Triage: {len(triage)}\\\")\\n\\n# Sort backlog by priority then age\\ndef sort_key(t):\\n    prio = {'P1': 0, 'P2': 1, 'P3': 2}.get(t.get('priority', 'P3'), 3)\\n    return (prio, t.get('ts', ''))\\n\\nbacklog.sort(key=sort_key)\\n\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n=== BACKLOG (sorted by priority, then age) ===\\\")\\nfor i, t in enumerate(backlog, 1):\\n    notes_preview = (t.get('note','') or '')[:100].replace('\\\\n', ' ')\\n    stalled = ' [STALLED]' if t.get('stalledAt') else ''\\n    dc = t.get('dispatchCount', 0)\\n    print(f\\\"{i:2}. [{t.get('priority','?')}] {t['id']}{stalled} (dc={dc})\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"    {t['title'][:70]}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"    {notes_preview}\\\")\\n    print()\\n\\n# Check Task type fields\\nprint(\\\"=== TASK SCHEMA CHECK ===\\\")\\nsample = backlog[0] if backlog else {}\\nprint(f\\\"Fields in task: {list(sample.keys())}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Has 'triage' status? {any(t.get('status') == 'triage' for t in tasks)}\\\")\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":164,"output":495,"cacheRead":108544,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":109203,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780513480623,"responseId":"gen-1780513480-Tw37BsDr1EOaMiE5Qa68"}}
