{"type":"message","id":"27a33609","parentId":"00a1c83a","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:05:35.914Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There's already 1 in_progress task (`task-fd625713` \"Incident → Task Linking\" — the P1 that was stalled earlier). And there's no `triage` status yet. I need to:\n\n1. Add `triage` to the task status options\n2. Process the backlog starting with the highest priority task\n\nLet me first check what the in_progress P1 task looks like — it was stalled earlier, let me reset it and start working through the backlog:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"b3a09377-9db7-445e-9a25-8f952f160919","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\ntasks_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n\n# Reset the stalled P1 task back to backlog — it's been sitting from earlier\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-fd625713' and t['status'] == 'in_progress':\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\n        t['stalledAt'] = now.isoformat()\n        t['dispatchCount'] = t.get('dispatchCount', 0) + 1\n        t['lastActivity'] = now.isoformat()\n        if 'history' not in t:\n            t['history'] = []\n        t['history'].append({\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\n            'action': 'stalled',\n            'actor': 'monkey',\n            'details': 'Reset from in_progress to backlog — ghost dispatch from work-dispatcher. Will be picked up in backlog processing.'\n        })\n        print(f\"Reset {t['id']} to backlog\")\n        break\n\nwith open(tasks_file, 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\\ntasks_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\\\"\\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\\n    tasks = jso