{"type":"message","id":"8b021c40","parentId":"4968e6f9","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:32:30.929Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Backlog Processing Report\n\n**✅ Completed: 7 tasks → Done**\n\n| # | Task | What was built |\n|---|------|----------------|\n| 1 | Incident → Task Linking | Already implemented — verified existing code |\n| 2 | Runbook Data Model | `runbooks.ts` — 5 runbooks (cron-failure, rate-limit, vite-cache, service-down, disk-space) with typed schema |\n| 3 | Runbook UI | IncidentDetailsDrawer panel showing matched runbook steps, escalation info |\n| 4 | Incident Type Mapping | `classifyIncident()` + `suggestRunbook()` — keyword-based auto-detection integrated into incident creation |\n| 5 | Task Creation From Runbooks | Extended incidents-create API — creates one Kanban task per runbook step |\n| 6 | Asset View | `/assets` route page — filterable grid of services, agents, crons with health status |\n| 7 | Auto Remediation | 4 rules (vite-cache, cron-timeout, rate-limit, disk-cleanup) + `/api/remediate` endpoint |\n\n**⏸ Triaged: 7 tasks → Triage** (need your input)\n\n| # | Task | What's needed |\n|---|------|---------------|\n| 1 | Unified Event Model | What events to track, how they relate to existing data models |\n| 2 | Incident Events in Timeline | Depends on Event Model — clarify scope |\n| 3 | Automation Health States | Health state definitions, display location |\n| 4 | Operational Readiness Dashboard | Specific metrics, layout, \"at a glance\" definition |\n| 5 | Runbook Evolution | What resolution history to track, how to flag outdated steps |\n| 6 | Incident Response Atmosphere | Which visual effects, severity mapping, scope |\n| 7 | Retry Policies with Backoff | Max retries, backoff strategy, which processes it applies to |\n\n**📊 Final state:** 0 backlog, 0 in_progress, 74 done, 7 triaged. Backlog is clear."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":169,"output":436,"cacheRead":145024,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":145629,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780515126739,"responseId":"gen-1780515126-U0SBM566DGd67ntMB3sP"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c7842345","parentId":"8b021c40","timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:32:31.170Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The function of working through backlog autonomously is what the Task \nDispatcher + agents should already be doing. The new part is the Triage \nrule: if a task is blocked or needs my input, move it to Triage with \nclear notes instead of letting it sit In Progress.\n\nAdd to FRAMEWORK.md: \"Operations Engine = Task Dispatcher + Agent \nExecution + Stall Detection + Triage Flow. Agents work backlog \nautonomously. Blocked tasks go to Triage, not left frozen In Progress.\"\n\nDreaming is separate — that's memory consolidation at 3am. The \nOperations Engine is the awake-hours work processing.","timestamp":1780515151018,"idempotencyKey":"a361958f-730a-4381-9791-22f4051604ff:user"}}
