{"type":"message","id":"91f31ad0","parentId":"2b0d42bd","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"`task-INC-042-act-751526` is in_progress but only 1.4 hours since lastActivity — under the 2-hour stall threshold. No action needed.\n\nNo new backlog tasks to pick up. Everything looks healthy.\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":344,"output":62,"cacheRead":50560,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":50966,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780505020680,"responseId":"gen-1780505020-m4JbYteXPormLyedXNCB"}}
{"type":"message","id":"944bfd2a","parentId":"91f31ad0","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"A task has been \"In Progress\" for over an hour with no visible progress. \nThere are many tasks waiting in Backlog. I need to understand if work is \nactually happening and why the backlog isn't being processed.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nINVESTIGATE THE CURRENT TASK\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. What task is currently In Progress? Show: title, assignee, currentStep, \n   progress%, lastActivity timestamp, how long it's been in_progress.\n\n2. Is any agent ACTUALLY working on it right now? Check:\n   - Has the agent updated currentStep or progress in the last 15 minutes?\n   - Is there evidence of real work (file changes, commits, output)?\n   - Or is it just sitting there with \"Agent starting...\"?\n\n3. If it's genuinely being worked on: update currentStep so I can see \n   what's happening. \"Agent starting...\" tells me nothing. Show me: \n   \"Reading file X...\", \"Writing code for Y...\", \"Testing Z...\"\n\n4. If it's stalled (no real activity for 30+ minutes): move it back to \n   Backlog with a note explaining why. The stall detection should have \n   caught this — if it didn't fire, investigate why.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nHOW TASK ASSIGNMENT SHOULD WORK\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nI need to understand the current logic:\n\n1. When there are tasks in Backlog, how does an agent pick up work?\n   - Does the dispatcher assign tasks, or do agents self-assign?\n   - What determines which task gets picked next (priority? age? order?)?\n   - Is there a limit on how many tasks one agent can have In Progress?\n\n2. Space Monkey currently has tasks assigned. The rule should be:\n   - ONE task In Progress at a time per agent\n   - Finish the current task → move to Done → pick up the next\n   - If a task is blocked, move it back to Backlog with a reason\n   - Never sit on a task for hours with no progress\n\n3. If there are multiple agents available, tasks should be distributed:\n   - Infrastructure tasks → Life Support Officer\n   - Code tasks → Systems Engineer\n   - Knowledge tasks → Station Archivist\n   - Coordination/unknown → Space Monkey\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nFIX THE PROGRESS VISIBILITY\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nThe In Progress column must show REAL progress:\n\n1. When an agent starts a task: currentStep = \"Starting...\", progress = 5%\n2. As work happens: currentStep updates with specific actions, \n   progress increments\n3. When complete: progress = 100%, task auto-moves to Done with summary\n4. If no update for 15 minutes: show \"⚠️ No update in X min\" in amber\n5. If no update for 30 minutes: flag as stalled\n\nThe agent MUST update currentStep and progress at least every 5-10 \nminutes while working. If it can't do this, the task isn't really \nbeing worked on.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nREPORT BACK\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. What's the current In Progress task status?\n2. Is work actually happening?\n3. What's the logic for picking up backlog tasks?\n4. Can agents handle multiple tasks or just one at a time?\n5. What fixes are needed to make this reliable?","timestamp":1780505858813,"idempotencyKey":"58c8ba68-fe42-433d-aef3-159542c69d7d:user"}}
