{"type":"message","id":"ac4dc18e","parentId":"75208453","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me check the task dispatcher logic and how tasks get picked up:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"2b2a0729-5a8f-4a79-ad23-e86fd60a9f23","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check if there's a task dispatcher script\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/ 2>/dev/null | grep -i dispatch\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/task-dispatcher.sh 2>/dev/null || echo \"No task-dispatcher.sh\"\necho \"===\"\n# Check the work dispatcher cron\ngrep -rn \"dispatch\\|backlog\\|pick.*task\\|assign.*task\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md 2>/dev/null","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check if there's a task dispatcher script\\nls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/ 2>/dev/null | grep -i dispatch\\ncat ~/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/task-dispatcher.sh 2>/dev/null || echo \\\"No task-dispatcher.sh\\\"\\necho \\\"===\\\"\\n# Check the work dispatcher cron\\ngrep -rn \\\"dispatch\\\\|backlog\\\\|pick.*task\\\\|assign.*task\\\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md 2>/dev/null\", \"timeout\": 5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"0bd11027-4599-441d-b1f6-48d09fe367ac","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":2551,"output":168,"cacheRead":50688,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":53407,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780505891470,"responseId":"gen-1780505891-wkSWZag2SzmhN054ZGA4"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e0b0f3a2","parentId":"ac4dc18e","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"2b2a0729-5a8f-4a79-ad23-e86fd60a9f23","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 1521 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if need"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":28,"aggregated":"-rwx------@  1 spacemonkey  staff   6597 Jun  3 10:17 work-dispatcher.sh\nNo task-dispatcher.sh\n===\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md:6:- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md:7:- For each backlog task, spawn a sub-agent (or work directly if simple) to complete it\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md:10:- Only pick up one task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md:18:- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the work-dispatcher from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md:19:- ALSO increment `dispatchCount` by 1 (set to at least 1 if not present). If `dispatchCount >= 3`, the dispatcher will skip the task entirely via its `dispatchCount < 3` filter. This is a secondary guard against the race condition where `stalledAt` gets cleared by the save-tasks merge logic.\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md:32:- If a sub-agent runs for >5 minutes with no resolution, kill it and add the task to backlog\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md:33:- If the main agent spends >10 minutes debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md:34:- Always report what was tried and what the blocker is when adding to backlog","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":17805059171