{"type":"message","id":"17676fb4","parentId":"1e811df6","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"OK, here's the full report:\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 Investigation Report: Task System Broken\n\n### 1. The In Progress Task\n\n**`task-INC-042-act-751526`** — \"[Dispatch] Apply standard fix\"\n- **Assignee:** monkey\n- **currentStep:** \"Agent starting…\" (never changed)\n- **progress:** 5% (never changed)\n- **lastActivity:** 2026-06-03T15:21:04Z → **98 minutes stale**\n- **Status:** ✅ Reset to backlog. dispatchCount bumped to 2.\n\n**Verdict:** No agent was ever working on this. The work-dispatcher shell script flipped the status from `backlog → in_progress` and tagged the note with `[auto-dispatched]`, but **never spawned an agent to actually do the work**. It just changed a JSON field and logged it.\n\n### 2. Root Cause\n\nThe `work-dispatcher.sh` script (called by cron every 15 min) has a fundamental design flaw:\n\n- **It only manipulates the JSON file** — changes status, appends to note, writes to a log\n- **It does NOT spawn sub-agents, send messages, or trigger any actual work**\n- It's a shell script with no ability to communicate with OpenClaw's agent system\n- The `[auto-dispatched]` tag in the note is meaningless — no agent reads it\n\nMeanwhile, the **heartbeat** (main agent) is the only thing that can actually dispatch work, because it can spawn sub-agents and send messages. But the heartbeat's task pickup was competing with the shell script, creating a race condition.\n\n### 3. Current State of the Backlog\n\n- **44 tasks in backlog**\n- **16 are dispatchable** (clean, never stalled, dispatchCount < 3)\n- **28 are protected** (stalledAt set or dispatchCount ≥ 3)\n- **0 tasks in_progress** (after my reset)\n- **37 tasks done**\n\nThe 16 dispatchable tasks are real work items (Incident → Task Linking, Response Action Lifecycle, Runbook Data Model, Asset View, etc.) that have never been touched.\n\n### 4. What I Fixed\n\n1. ✅ **Reset the stalled task** back to backlog with proper history\n2. ✅ **Updated HEARTBEAT.md** with corrected dispatch logic:\n   - Heartbeat is the **only** dispatcher (no shell script competition)\n   - Clear task routing: P1 → monkey directly, P2/P3 → crew agents\n   - Sub-agents must update `currentStep` every 5-10 min with specific actions\n   - Tightened stall detection: if `currentStep` is still \"Agent starting…\" after 30 min, reset immediately\n   - Priority-based pickup: P1 first, then P2, then P3\n\n### 5. What Still Needs to Happen\n\n**The `work-dispatcher.sh` script should be disabled or removed.** It's doing nothing useful and creates race conditions with the heartbeat. The heartbeat is the only dispatcher that can actually spawn agents.\n\n**The 16 dispatchable backlog tasks need human triage.** They're all P1/P2 operational work items (incident management features, runbooks, asset tracking). These are planning/design tasks that need your input before an agent can work on them effectively.\n\n**The 28 protected tasks** have been dispatched multiple times with no progress — they're stuck in a loop and need human review to either:\n- Clear the `stalledAt` and `dispatchCount` to retry\n- Mark as done if no longer needed\n- Delete if obsolete\n\nWant me to:\n1. Disable the work-dispatcher cron?\n2. Start working through the dispatchable backlog tasks?\n3. Clean up the protected/stalled tasks?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":249,"output":835,"cacheRead":60032,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":61116,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780506329366,"responseId":"gen-1780506329-K1qnr1Itke98rIAetU5w"}}
