{"type":"message","id":"3499a454","parentId":"f995b116","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"e97e4c4b-3a28-4b18-8ad7-b64729c8096c","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 1430 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if need"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1259,"aggregated":"-rwx------@ 1 spacemonkey  staff  6597 Jun  3 10:17 /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/work-dispatcher.sh.disabled\n===\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-06-02.md:28:  1. `work-dispatcher.sh` only checked `IN_PROGRESS > 0` and exited — no staleness logic\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-06-02.md:34:  - Rewrote `work-dispatcher.sh` with proper stall detection (>2h = stale, auto-reset)\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md:23:- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the work-dispatcher from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md:56:- **2026-06-03:** Task system overhaul — removed work-dispatcher.sh (was flipping JSON without spawning agents). Heartbeat is now the only dispatcher. 28 stale/protected tasks cleaned up (6 incident artifacts → obsolete, 22 strategic → deferred). End-to-end test passed: sub-agent dispatched, completed, moved to Done with summary. 16 planning tasks remain in backlog for human triage.\n/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json:1381:        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog — task flipped by work-dispatcher.sh but no agent spawned to do it. No activity timestamp, no progress.\"\n===\nNo dispatch crontab\n---\n---\n---\n===\nOriginal script: GONE","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780509354178}}
