{"type":"message","id":"4df5cf3c","parentId":"3acd6600","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good news on both fronts:\n\n**Work-dispatcher:** The `.disabled` file is still executable (`rwx`) but the original is gone, no cron/LaunchAgent references it, and no other scripts call it. The ghost dispatch Andre caught was likely the last in-flight execution before the rename. It's dead now.\n\n**Task timestamps:** The Move Incident ShortCut task actually looks fine — `completedAt` and `lastActivity` match (0 second diff). But Andre's concern is valid for *future* sub-agents. The sub-agent updated the task at completion but didn't update `currentStep` or `lastActivity` *during* work — there's a 3-minute gap between `startedAt` (17:23) and `completedAt` (17:26) with no intermediate updates.\n\nLet me fix the HEARTBEAT.md to make the sub-agent instructions more explicit, and also update the sub-agent spawn template:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"6433a69b-e8b8-4d88-831b-dd6a4883a718","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1399,"output":229,"cacheRead":74752,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":76380,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780509354180,"responseId":"gen-1780509354-jFAiUrc7NNX0elxX9oQg"}}
