{"type":"message","id":"4e0b3378","parentId":"c5a2ac31","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"f73298be-aff3-4bf2-b783-fb1fed9a319e","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` every 5-10 min with specific actions (NOT \"Agent starting…\")\n- Write completion summary before marking done","newText":"- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- **The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` (ISO timestamp) every 5-10 min with specific actions** — NOT \"Agent starting…\". Example: \"Reading AppSidebar.tsx\", \"Editing nav order\", \"Verifying app loads\". Without `lastActivity` updates, stall detection cannot function.\n- Write completion summary before marking done\n- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\n  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action before starting work\n  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at each step\n  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 50% midway, 100% done)\n  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\n  - Commit and push code changes when complete"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\\n- The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` every 5-10 min with specific actions (NOT \\\"Agent starting…\\\")\\n- Write completion summary before marking done\", \"newText\": \"- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\\n- **The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` (ISO timestamp) every 5-10 min with specific actions** — NOT \\\"Agent starting…\\\". Example: \\\"Reading AppSidebar.tsx\\\", \\\"Editing nav order\\\", \\\"Verifying app loads\\\". Without `lastActivity` updates, stall detection cannot function.\\n- Write completion summary before marking done\\n- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\\n  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action before starting work\\n  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at each step\\n  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 50% midway, 100% done)\\n  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\\n  - Commit and push code changes when complete\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1100,"output":355,"cacheRead":76032,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":77487,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780509371785,"responseId":"gen-1780509371-SVjhpmpge52X4jcYNro3"}}
{"type":"message","id":"299c8324","parentId":"4e0b3378","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"f73298be-aff3-4bf2-b783-fb1fed9a319e","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 88 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if needed"}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  7 - ONLY pick tasks that are truly dispatchable: no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\n  8 - Sort by priority (P1 > P2 > P3), then by age (oldest first)\n  9 - Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n 10 - Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n-11 - The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` every 5-10 min with specific actions (NOT \"Agent starting…\")\n+11 - **The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` (ISO timestamp) every 5-10 min with specific actions** — NOT \"Agent starting…\". Example: \"Reading AppSidebar.tsx\", \"Editing nav order\", \"Verifying app loads\". Without `lastActivity` updates, stall detection cannot function.\n 12 - Write completion summary before marking done\n+13 - **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\n+14   - Update `currentStep` to a specific action before starting work\n+15   - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at each step\n+16   - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 50% midway, 100% done)\n+17   - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\n+18   - Commit and push code changes when complete\n 13 - Only pick up ONE task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n 14 - The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents\n 15 - Crew task routing: infra → lifesupport, code → engineer, knowledge → archivist, unknown → monkey\n 16 \n    ...","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n@@ -7,10 +7,16 @@\n - ONLY pick tasks that are truly dispatchable: no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\n - Sort by priority (P1 > P2 > P3), then by age (oldest first)\n - Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n - Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n-- The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` every 5-10 min with specific actions (NOT \"Agent starting…\")\n+- **The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` (ISO timestamp) every 5-10 min with specific actions** — NOT \"Agent starting…\". Example: \"Reading AppSidebar.tsx\", \"Editing nav order\", \"Verifying app loads\". Without `lastActivity` updates, stall detection cannot function.\n - Write completion summary before marking done\n+- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\n+  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action before starting work\n+  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at each step\n+  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 50% midway, 100% done)\n+  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\n+  - Commit and push code changes when complete\n - Only pick up ONE task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n - The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents\n - Crew task routing: infra → lifesupport, code → engineer, knowledge → archivist, unknown → monkey\n \n","firstChangedLine":11},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780509391985}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0ee841e","parentId":"299c8324","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Also let me clean up the stale reference in the stall detection section:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"b811f4ae-0021-44af-8492-f9662e9f2f6d","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the work-dispatcher from immediately re-dispatching the same task.","newText":"- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the heartbeat from immediately re-dispatching the same task."}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the work-dispatcher from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\", \"newText\": \"- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the heartbeat from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":470,"output":171,"cacheRead":77056,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":77697,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780509391992,"responseId":"gen-1780509392-dd9pu2lJ6oJ5P9oewXdu"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0066d698","parentId":"f0ee841e","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"b811f4ae-0021-44af-8492-f9662e9f2f6d","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 88 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if needed"}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 25   - Use `lastActivity` if set and is a valid ISO timestamp\n 26   - Else use the `ts` field if it's a valid ISO timestamp (skip if it's \"just now\" or non-parseable)\n 27   - Else use the most recent `history[].ts` entry\n 28   - If NO valid timestamp can be found at all, treat as stalled (it's broken data)\n-29 - If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the work-dispatcher from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n+29 - If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the heartbeat from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n 30 - ALSO increment `dispatchCount` by 1 (set to at least 1 if not present). If `dispatchCount >= 3`, the dispatcher will skip the task entirely via its `dispatchCount < 3` filter. This is a secondary guard against the race condition where `stalledAt` gets cleared by the save-tasks merge logic.\n 31 - If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning. If currentStep is still \"Agent starting…\" or null, reset immediately — the task was never actually picked up by an agent\n 32 - The `startedAt` field is NOT reliable — do not use it for stall detection\n 33 - After resetting, commit the change so the Kanban reflects reality immediately\n    ...","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n@@ -25,9 +25,9 @@\n   - Use `lastActivity` if set and is a valid ISO timestamp\n   - Else use the `ts` field if it's a valid ISO timestamp (skip if it's \"just now\" or non-parseable)\n   - Else use the most recent `history[].ts` entry\n   - If NO valid timestamp can be found at all, treat as stalled (it's broken data)\n-- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the work-dispatcher from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n+- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the heartbeat from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n - ALSO increment `dispatchCount` by 1 (set to at least 1 if not present). If `dispatchCount >= 3`, the dispatcher will skip the task entirely via its `dispatchCount < 3` filter. This is a secondary guard against the race condition where `stalledAt` gets cleared by the save-tasks merge logic.\n - If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning. If currentStep is still \"Agent starting…\" or null, reset immediately — the task was never actually picked up by an agent\n - The `startedAt` field is NOT reliable — do not use it for stall detection\n - After resetting, commit the change so the Kanban reflects reality immediately\n","firstChangedLine":29},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780509412665}}
