{"type":"message","id":"1c03bc87","parentId":"5203d6e5","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Andre, here's the confirmation:\n\n**Work-dispatcher:** Dead and buried.\n- Original file: gone\n- `.disabled` file: non-executable (`rw-` only)\n- No cron jobs, no LaunchAgents, no scripts reference it\n- The ghost dispatch you caught was the last gasp — nothing can trigger it now\n\n**Sub-agent timestamp discipline:** Updated HEARTBEAT.md with explicit instructions that every sub-agent must:\n1. Set `currentStep` to a specific action *before* starting work (not \"Agent starting…\")\n2. Update `lastActivity` with an ISO timestamp at every step\n3. Update `progress` to reflect actual completion\n4. Write a `summary` before marking done\n\nThe Move Incident ShortCut task's timestamps were actually fine (completedAt and lastActivity matched), but the sub-agent didn't update `currentStep` *during* work — it jumped from \"Agent starting…\" straight to \"Completed\". That gap is what stall detection would miss. The new instructions close that gap.\n\nSystem is clean. 🐒"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":191,"output":223,"cacheRead":77824,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":78238,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780509440221,"responseId":"gen-1780509440-EIbh3gdm8flxkf75d4F0"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b2f18760","parentId":"1c03bc87","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The task system is now clean — work-dispatcher dead, heartbeat is the \nonly dispatcher, end-to-end test passed. Now I want the system to work \nautonomously while I sleep instead of sitting idle.\n\nDesign a \"Night Shift\" mode. Do NOT build it yet — design only.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nTHE NIGHT SHIFT CONCEPT\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nWhen I'm asleep (01:00-07:00) and there are dispatchable backlog tasks, \nthe system should work through them autonomously rather than doing nothing.\n\nTRIGGER: At 01:00, the heartbeat checks if Night Shift should activate.\n- Are there dispatchable backlog tasks?\n- Are rate limits healthy (no recent 429s)?\n- Is Andre marked as \"away\" (no recent chat activity)?\n- If all three are true → enter Night Shift mode\n\nBEHAVIOUR:\n- Pick ONE task at a time (P1 first, then P2, then P3)\n- Spawn a sub-agent to work on it\n- Complete it → move to Done → pick the next\n- Continue until: no more dispatchable tasks, OR rate limits spike, \n  OR 07:00 arrives\n\nCONSTRAINTS:\n- Maximum 5 tasks per night (don't burn through the entire backlog)\n- Stop immediately if rate limit warnings appear (429 errors)\n- Only work on tasks that don't need my input — skip tasks tagged \n  \"needs-human-input\" or marked as planning/design\n- Don't start a new task after 06:30 (time to wrap up and report)\n- Each completed task must have: completion summary, currentStep \n  history, progress tracking\n\nMORNING REPORT (07:00):\nSend a Telegram sitrep:\n\"🌙 Night shift complete. X tasks done. Y remaining in backlog. \n ~Z tokens used.\n Completed: [task titles with one-line summaries]\"\n\nSAFETY RULES:\n- Never auto-dispatch tasks that have stalledAt set\n- Never re-dispatch a task attempted 3+ times (dispatchCount ≥ 3)\n- If a task fails, move it back to backlog with failure note\n- Never modify openclaw.json, LaunchAgents, or system config\n- Never touch the gateway or cron jobs\n- Shell-only infrastructure checks only — no model calls for monitoring\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nDESIGN QUESTIONS TO ANSWER\n═══════════════════════════════\n\n1. How would Night Shift integrate with the existing heartbeat?\n   - Should it be a separate cron job, or part of the heartbeat cycle?\n   - How does it coexist with Dreaming (3am) and Daily Station Check (23:00)?\n\n2. What changes to HEARTBEAT.md are needed?\n   - New section for Night Shift rules?\n   - Modified dispatch logic during 01:00-07:00 window?\n\n3. What changes to tasks.json schema are needed?\n   - New field like `nightShiftEligible: true/false`?\n   - Or use existing tags/priority to determine eligibility?\n\n4. What are the risks?\n   - Token exhaustion before morning?\n   - Sub-agent runaway (tool-call loops)?\n   - Corrupted tasks.json from rapid-fire saves?\n   - How do we mitigate each one?\n\n5. How do we test this safely?\n   - Manual trigger for a single task first?\n   - Dry-run mode that logs what it WOULD do?\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nDELIVERABLE\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nA design document (add to MEMORY.md or a new NIGHT_SHIFT.md) covering:\n- Architecture: how it integrates with heartbeat/cron\n- Eligibility rules: which tasks qualify for night work\n- Safety constraints: what it must never do\n- Morning report format\n- Test plan\n\nNo code. No implementation. Design only.","timestamp":1780509713882,"idempotencyKey":"f11a625e-b49e-4ba2-8d23-11b3e8b10bda:user"}}
