{"type":"message","id":"234c685b","parentId":"8417cb31","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"5c926354-be38-4615-998d-864baf3806c3","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 85 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if needed"}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n 54 \n 55 - **2026-06-02:** OPS-002 — Incident→Task Linking: `Task.linkedIncidentId` is source of truth (not `Incident.linkedTaskIds`). Auto-detect creates linked triage tasks. Task status changes auto-append to incident timeline via `/api/incidents/timeline`. Added `triage` to Task status union, new Triage Kanban column, Linked Incident section in task detail, derived linked tasks in IncidentDetailsDrawer.\n 56 - **2026-06-03:** Task system overhaul — removed work-dispatcher.sh (was flipping JSON without spawning agents). Heartbeat is now the only dispatcher. 28 stale/protected tasks cleaned up (6 incident artifacts → obsolete, 22 strategic → deferred). End-to-end test passed: sub-agent dispatched, completed, moved to Done with summary. 16 planning tasks remain in backlog for human triage.\n 57 \n+58 ## Night Shift\n+59 \n+60 Autonomous task processing during 01:00-07:00 when Andre is asleep. Design doc at `NIGHT_SHIFT.md`. Not yet implemented — pending Andre's review.\n+61 \n 58 ---\n 59 _Last updated: 2026-06-03 by Space Monkey_","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n@@ -54,6 +54,10 @@\n \n - **2026-06-02:** OPS-002 — Incident→Task Linking: `Task.linkedIncidentId` is source of truth (not `Incident.linkedTaskIds`). Auto-detect creates linked triage tasks. Task status changes auto-append to incident timeline via `/api/incidents/timeline`. Added `triage` to Task status union, new Triage Kanban column, Linked Incident section in task detail, derived linked tasks in IncidentDetailsDrawer.\n - **2026-06-03:** Task system overhaul — removed work-dispatcher.sh (was flipping JSON without spawning agents). Heartbeat is now the only dispatcher. 28 stale/protected tasks cleaned up (6 incident artifacts → obsolete, 22 strategic → deferred). End-to-end test passed: sub-agent dispatched, completed, moved to Done with summary. 16 planning tasks remain in backlog for human triage.\n \n+## Night Shift\n+\n+Autonomous task processing during 01:00-07:00 when Andre is asleep. Design doc at `NIGHT_SHIFT.md`. Not yet implemented — pending Andre's review.\n+\n ---\n _Last updated: 2026-06-03 by Space Monkey_\n","firstChangedLine":58},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780509908031}}
{"type":"message","id":"68ac76a8","parentId":"234c685b","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"e2ba84b8-a668-49aa-9b1e-73f2497d2223","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && git add NIGHT_SHIFT.md MEMORY.md && git commit -m \"Add Night Shift design doc — autonomous task processing 01:00-07:00\"","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && git add NIGHT_SHIFT.md MEMORY.md && git commit -m \\\"Add Night Shift design doc — autonomous task processing 01:00-07:00\\\"\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":244,"output":68,"cacheRead":85504,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":85816,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780509908037,"responseId":"gen-1780509908-7sxSGpcChioAYWqbaab8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2979abee","parentId":"68ac76a8","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"e2ba84b8-a668-49aa-9b1e-73f2497d2223","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 169 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if neede"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":44,"aggregated":"[main 1a13ccb] Add Night Shift design doc — autonomous task processing 01:00-07:00\n 2 files changed, 264 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 NIGHT_SHIFT.md","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780509933573}}
{"type":"message","id":"773a119c","parentId":"2979abee","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Design doc written. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Night Shift Design — Summary\n\n**What:** Autonomous task processing during 01:00-07:00 BST when you're asleep.\n\n**How it integrates:** Not a separate cron — it's a mode within the existing heartbeat. A single 01:00 cron fires a systemEvent to activate it. The heartbeat handles all the dispatch logic.\n\n**Task eligibility:** P2/P3 tasks only, tagged as `nightShiftEligible: true`, no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`. P1 tasks, planning/design tasks, and anything tagged `needs-human-input` are excluded.\n\n**Safety rails:**\n- Max 5 tasks per night, max 50K tokens\n- No new tasks after 06:30, hard stop at 07:00\n- Stops immediately on 429 rate limits or if you send a message\n- Never touches system config, gateway, cron jobs, or LaunchAgents\n- Sub-agents must verify app loads before marking done\n\n**Morning report:** Telegram sitrep at 07:00 with completed/failed/skipped counts, task summaries, and token usage.\n\n**State persistence:** `data/night-shift-state.json` tracks progress across heartbeat cycles, archived after each night.\n\n**Testing plan:** 4 phases — dry run → single task → full night → edge cases.\n\n**Coexistence with existing jobs:** No conflict. Sessions Cleanup (03:00 BST) and Session Auto-Expiry (05:00 BST) are lightweight infrastructure tasks. FreeRide update (06:00 BST) is isolated. Night Shift is the only one that dispatches work.\n\nFull design in `NIGHT_SHIFT.md`. Ready for your review — no code until you give the green light."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":260,"output":398,"cacheRead":85632,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":86290,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780509933577,"responseId":"gen-1780509933-3H9syPcr1bnx7NUyB9yV"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4502009c","parentId":"773a119c","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Night Shift design looks solid. A few questions before approval:\n\n1. How do tasks get tagged as nightShiftEligible? Is it manual (I set \n   the tag) or automatic (system determines eligibility)?\n\n2. The 50K token limit — is that per task or total per night? If total, \n   that's quite low (5 tasks × 10K tokens each). Bump to 100K total.\n\n3. Morning report: add disk usage and any incidents created overnight, \n   not just task summaries. I want to know the station status at a glance.\n\n4. Dry run test: when can we run the first dry run? I want to see it \n   log what it WOULD do before it actually does anything.\n\nAfter these clarifications, we can implement Phase 1 (dry run).","timestamp":1780510102718,"idempotencyKey":"d2b3b5e1-cf80-444c-aa39-314e56e38b93:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"620b4c2c","parentId":"4502009c","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good questions. Let me address each one and update the design.\n\n**1. `nightShiftEligible` — automatic, not manual.**\n\nThe system determines eligibility at dispatch time using existing fields. No manual tagging needed. The rules are:\n\n- **Eligible by default** — any task with `status: \"backlog\"`, no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`\n- **Auto-excluded** if: P1 priority, or has tags `needs-human-input`/`planning`/`design`/`roadmap`, or `wasStalled`\n- **Andre can opt out** a specific task by adding `\"nightShiftEligible\": false` — but this is the exception, not the rule\n\nSo the field exists as an override, not a requirement. 95% of tasks will never need it set.\n\n**2. Token limit — bumping to 100K total per night.**\n\nAgreed, 50K was too conservative. Updated to 100K total across all tasks. That's ~20K per task average, which is generous for small-to-medium tasks.\n\n**3. Morning report — adding station status.**\n\nGood call. The report should include:\n- Disk usage (workspace + MC repo size)\n- Any incidents created overnight (from auto-detect)\n- Gateway uptime\n- Token usage breakdown\n\n**4. Dry run — we can do it right now.**\n\nNo code changes needed. I can simulate the full Night Shift logic in this session: read tasks.json, evaluate eligibility, log what it WOULD dispatch, and produce a mock morning report. Want me to run it now?\n\nLet me update the design doc with the clarifications first:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"17122f84-f09b-4644-a2b8-bb0125fb480b","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### Task Eligibility\n\nNot all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\n\n**Must have:**\n- `status: \"backlog\"`\n- `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\n- `stalledAt` not set\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\n- `wasStalled: false`\n\n**Must NOT have:**\n- `priority: \"P1\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\n- Tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n- `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\n\n**Sort order for pickup:**\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)","newText":"### Task Eligibility\n\nNot all backlog tasks qualify. Eligibility is determined **automatically** by the system at dispatch time — no manual tagging required.\n\n**Automatically eligible:**\n- `status: \"backlog\"`\n- `stalledAt` not set\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\n- `wasStalled: false`\n- Priority is P2 or P3 (P1 excluded)\n- No exclusion tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n\n**Manual override:**\n- `nightShiftEligible: false` — Andre can opt out a specific task\n- This is the exception, not the rule. Most tasks never need this field.\n\n**Sort order for pickup:**\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)"},{"oldText":"- **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded","newText":"- **Max 100K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit)"},{"oldText":"```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\n✅ Completed: X tasks\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n\nFailed:\n• [Task title] — [reason]\n\nBacklog remaining: N tasks\n```\n\nIf zero tasks were completed, the report is still sent (so Andre knows the system is working):\n\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\nNo tasks completed.\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\nBacklog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n```","newText":"```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\n✅ Completed: X tasks\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n\nFailed:\n• [Task title] — [reason]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n```\n\nIf zero tasks were completed:\n\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\nNo tasks completed.\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n```"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"### Task Eligibility\\n\\nNot all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\\n\\n**Must have:**\\n- `status: \\\"backlog\\\"`\\n- `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\\n- `stalledAt` not set\\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\\n- `wasStalled: false`\\n\\n**Must NOT have:**\\n- `priority: \\\"P1\\\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\\n- Tags: `\\\"needs-human-input\\\"`, `\\\"planning\\\"`, `\\\"design\\\"`, `\\\"roadmap\\\"`\\n- `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\\n\\n**Sort order for pickup:**\\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\", \"newText\": \"### Task Eligibility\\n\\nNot all backlog tasks qualify. Eligibility is determined **automatically** by the system at dispatch time — no manual tagging required.\\n\\n**Automatically eligible:**\\n- `status: \\\"backlog\\\"`\\n- `stalledAt` not set\\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\\n- `wasStalled: false`\\n- Priority is P2 or P3 (P1 excluded)\\n- No exclusion tags: `\\\"needs-human-input\\\"`, `\\\"planning\\\"`, `\\\"design\\\"`, `\\\"roadmap\\\"`\\n\\n**Manual override:**\\n- `nightShiftEligible: false` — Andre can opt out a specific task\\n- This is the exception, not the rule. Most tasks never need this field.\\n\\n**Sort order for pickup:**\\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\"}, {\"oldText\": \"- **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded\", \"newText\": \"- **Max 100K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit)\"}, {\"oldText\": \"```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\n✅ Completed: X tasks\\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n\\nFailed:\\n• [Task title] — [reason]\\n\\nBacklog remaining: N tasks\\n```\\n\\nIf zero tasks were completed, the report is still sent (so Andre knows the system is working):\\n\\n```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\nNo tasks completed.\\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\\nBacklog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\\n```\", \"newText\": \"```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\n✅ Completed: X tasks\\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n\\nFailed:\\n• [Task title] — [reason]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\\n```\\n\\nIf zero tasks were completed:\\n\\n```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\nNo tasks completed.\\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\\n```\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":77060,"output":1348,"cacheRead":9472,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":87880,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780510102817,"responseId":"gen-1780510103-FgSForhRtDCsPkPYuq2N"}}
