{"type":"message","id":"89c06cc2","parentId":"d17a16e3","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"5c672f5e-99a2-400a-9944-7daf8f302888","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"Not all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\n\n**Must have:**\n- `status: \"backlog\"`\n- `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\n- `stalledAt` not set\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\n- `wasStalled: false`\n\n**Must NOT have:**\n- `priority: \"P1\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\n- Tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n- `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\n\n**Sort order for pickup:**\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)","newText":"Not all backlog tasks qualify. Eligibility is determined **automatically** by the system at dispatch time — no manual tagging required.\n\n**Automatically eligible:**\n- `status: \"backlog\"`\n- `stalledAt` not set\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\n- `wasStalled: false`\n- Priority is P2 or P3 (P1 excluded)\n- No exclusion tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n\n**Manual override:**\n- `nightShiftEligible: false` — Andre can opt out a specific task\n- This is the exception, not the rule. Most tasks never need this field.\n\n**Sort order for pickup:**\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)"},{"oldText":"- **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded","newText":"- **Max 100K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit)"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"Not all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\\n\\n**Must have:**\\n- `status: \\\"backlog\\\"`\\n- `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\\n- `stalledAt` not set\\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\\n- `wasStalled: false`\\n\\n**Must NOT have:**\\n- `priority: \\\"P1\\\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\\n- Tags: `\\\"needs-human-input\\\"`, `\\\"planning\\\"`, `\\\"design\\\"`, `\\\"roadmap\\\"`\\n- `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\\n\\n**Sort order for pickup:**\\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\", \"newText\": \"Not all backlog tasks qualify. Eligibility is determined **automatically** by the system at dispatch time — no manual tagging required.\\n\\n**Automatically eligible:**\\n- `status: \\\"backlog\\\"`\\n- `stalledAt` not set\\n- `dispatchCount < 3`\\n- `wasStalled: false`\\n- Priority is P2 or P3 (P1 excluded)\\n- No exclusion tags: `\\\"needs-human-input\\\"`, `\\\"planning\\\"`, `\\\"design\\\"`, `\\\"roadmap\\\"`\\n\\n**Manual override:**\\n- `nightShiftEligible: false` — Andre can opt out a specific task\\n- This is the exception, not the rule. Most tasks never need this field.\\n\\n**Sort order for pickup:**\\n1. Priority: P2 before P3\\n2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\"}, {\"oldText\": \"- **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded\", \"newText\": \"- **Max 100K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit)\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":359,"output":508,"cacheRead":87936,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":88803,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780510184603,"responseId":"gen-1780510184-23axRgKcytN5rFbtJanb"}}
{"type":"message","id":"45fc18ce","parentId":"89c06cc2","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"5c672f5e-99a2-400a-9944-7daf8f302888","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 90 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if needed"}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  60 ---\n  61 \n  62 ## 3. Task Eligibility\n  63 \n- 64 Not all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\n+ 64 Not all backlog tasks qualify. Eligibility is determined **automatically** by the system at dispatch time — no manual tagging required.\n  65 \n- 66 **Must have:**\n+ 66 **Automatically eligible:**\n  67 - `status: \"backlog\"`\n- 68 - `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\n  69 - `stalledAt` not set\n  70 - `dispatchCount < 3`\n  71 - `wasStalled: false`\n+ 71 - Priority is P2 or P3 (P1 excluded)\n+ 72 - No exclusion tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n  72 \n- 73 **Must NOT have:**\n- 74 - `priority: \"P1\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\n- 75 - Tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n- 76 - `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\n+ 74 **Manual override:**\n+ 75 - `nightShiftEligible: false` — Andre can opt out a specific task\n+ 76 - This is the exception, not the rule. Most tasks never need this field.\n  77 \n  78 **Sort order for pickup:**\n  79 1. Priority: P2 before P3\n  80 2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\n     ...\n  86 ### Hard Limits\n  87 - **Max 5 tasks per night** — prevents burning through backlog\n  88 - **No new tasks after 06:30** — wrap-up window\n  89 - **Stop at 07:00 sharp** — even if a task is mid-work (move back to backlog)\n- 90 - **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded\n+ 90 - **Max 100K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit)\n  91 \n  92 ### Rate Limit Protection\n  93 - Before each task dispatch, check for recent 429 errors\n  94 - If 429s detected → pause Night Shift, log reason, send alert\n     ...","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\n@@ -60,21 +60,21 @@\n ---\n \n ## 3. Task Eligibility\n \n-Not all backlog tasks qualify. A task is Night Shift eligible only if:\n+Not all backlog tasks qualify. Eligibility is determined **automatically** by the system at dispatch time — no manual tagging required.\n \n-**Must have:**\n+**Automatically eligible:**\n - `status: \"backlog\"`\n-- `nightShiftEligible: true` (new field, defaults to `true` on task creation)\n - `stalledAt` not set\n - `dispatchCount < 3`\n - `wasStalled: false`\n+- Priority is P2 or P3 (P1 excluded)\n+- No exclusion tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n \n-**Must NOT have:**\n-- `priority: \"P1\"` — P1 tasks need Andre's awareness, even at night\n-- Tags: `\"needs-human-input\"`, `\"planning\"`, `\"design\"`, `\"roadmap\"`\n-- `assignee` set to a specific crew member (Night Shift uses generic sub-agents)\n+**Manual override:**\n+- `nightShiftEligible: false` — Andre can opt out a specific task\n+- This is the exception, not the rule. Most tasks never need this field.\n \n **Sort order for pickup:**\n 1. Priority: P2 before P3\n 2. Age: oldest first (by `ts` or earliest `history[].ts`)\n@@ -86,9 +86,9 @@\n ### Hard Limits\n - **Max 5 tasks per night** — prevents burning through backlog\n - **No new tasks after 06:30** — wrap-up window\n - **Stop at 07:00 sharp** — even if a task is mid-work (move back to backlog)\n-- **Max 50K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded\n+- **Max 100K tokens per night** — hard stop if exceeded (~20K avg per task at 5-task limit)\n \n ### Rate Limit Protection\n - Before each task dispatch, check for recent 429 errors\n - If 429s detected → pause Night Shift, log reason, send alert\n","firstChangedLine":64},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780510214947}}
