{"type":"message","id":"9534cf05","parentId":"a11e0d08","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me run through the heartbeat checks. First, I'll do the dry run test Andre asked for — simulating Night Shift logic against the current backlog."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"4210e027-0e69-49da-bcb7-7113dbb17097","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\ntasks_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n\n# ── Simulate Night Shift eligibility ──\nEXCLUDED_TAGS = {\"needs-human-input\", \"planning\", \"design\", \"roadmap\"}\n\ndef is_night_shift_eligible(t):\n    if t.get('status') != 'backlog': return False, \"not backlog\"\n    if t.get('stalledAt'): return False, f\"stalled at {t['stalledAt'][:19]}\"\n    if t.get('dispatchCount', 0) >= 3: return False, f\"dispatchCount={t.get('dispatchCount',0)}\"\n    if t.get('wasStalled'): return False, \"wasStalled\"\n    if t.get('priority') == 'P1': return False, \"P1 excluded\"\n    tags = set(t.get('tags', []))\n    excluded = tags & EXCLUDED_TAGS\n    if excluded: return False, f\"excluded tags: {excluded}\"\n    if t.get('nightShiftEligible') == False: return False, \"nightShiftEligible=false\"\n    return True, \"eligible\"\n\n# Categorize all tasks\neligible = []\nineligible = []\nfor t in tasks:\n    ok, reason = is_night_shift_eligible(t)\n    if ok:\n        eligible.append(t)\n    elif t.get('status') == 'backlog':\n        ineligible.append((t, reason))\n\n# Sort eligible: P2 first, then P3, then oldest\neligible.sort(key=lambda t: ({'P2':0,'P3':1}.get(t.get('priority','P3'),1), t.get('ts','')))\n\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\nprint(\"NIGHT SHIFT DRY RUN — \" + now.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M UTC'))\nprint(\"=\" * 60)\n\nprint(f\"\\n📊 Total tasks: {len(tasks)}\")\nprint(f\"   Backlog: {len([t for t in tasks if t['status']=='backlog'])}\")\nprint(f\"   Night Shift eligible: {len(eligible)}\")\nprint(f\"   Ineligible (backlog): {len(ineligible)}\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n✅ ELIGIBLE TASKS (would dispatch up to 5):\")\nfor i, t in enumerate(eligible[:5], 1):\n    notes_preview = (t.get('note','') or '')[:80].replace('\\n', ' ')\n    print(f\"  {i}. [{t.get('priority','?')}] {t['id']}\")\n    print(f\"     {t['title'][:65]}\")\n    print(f\"     Note: {notes_preview}\")\n    print()\nif len(eligible) > 5:\n    print(f\"  ... {len(eligible)-5} more eligible (would not dispatch tonight)\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n⛔ INELIGIBLE BACKLOG TASKS:\")\nfor t, reason in ineligible:\n    print(f\"  [{t.get('priority','?')}] {t['id']}: {t['title'][:50]} — {reason}\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n── Simulation ──\")\nprint(f\"If Night Shift activated now:\")\nprint(f\"  → Would pick: {eligible[0]['title'][:50] if eligible else 'None (no eligible tasks)'}\")\nprint(f\"  → Would complete up to: {min(5, len(eligible))} tasks\")\nprint(f\"  → Would stop at 06:30 or after 5 tasks\")\nprint(f\"  → Morning report at 07:00\")\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\\ntasks_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\\\"\\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\\n\\n# ── Simulate Night Shift eligibility ──\\nEXCLUDED_TAGS = {\\\"needs-human-input\\\", \\\"planning\\\", \\\"design\\\", \\\"roadmap\\\"}\\n\\ndef is_night_shift_eligible(t):\\n    if t.get('status') != 'backlog': return False, \\\"not backlog\\\"\\n    if t.get('stalledAt'): return False, f\\\"stalled at {t['stalledAt'][:19]}\\\"\\n    if t.get('dispatchCount', 0) >= 3: return False, f\\\"dispatchCount={t.get('dispatchCount',0)}\\\"\\n    if t.get('wasStalled'): return False, \\\"wasStalled\\\"\\n    if t.get('priority') == 'P1': return False, \\\"P1 excluded\\\"\\n    tags = set(t.get('tags', []))\\n    excluded = tags & EXCLUDED_TAGS\\n    if excluded: return False, f\\\"excluded tags: {excluded}\\\"\\n    if t.get('nightShiftEligible') == False: return False, \\\"nightShiftEligible=false\\\"\\n    return True, \\\"eligible\\\"\\n\\n# Categorize all tasks\\neligible = []\\nineligible = []\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    ok, reason = is_night_shift_eligible(t)\\n    if ok:\\n        eligible.append(t)\\n    elif t.get('status') == 'backlog':\\n        ineligible.append((t, reason))\\n\\n# Sort eligible: P2 first, then P3, then oldest\\neligible.sort(key=lambda t: ({'P2':0,'P3':1}.get(t.get('priority','P3'),1), t.get('ts','')))\\n\\nprint(\\\"=\\\" * 60)\\nprint(\\\"NIGHT SHIFT DRY RUN — \\\" + now.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M UTC'))\\nprint(\\\"=\\\" * 60)\\n\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n📊 Total tasks: {len(tasks)}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"   Backlog: {len([t for t in tasks if t['status']=='backlog'])}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"   Night Shift eligible: {len(eligible)}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"   Ineligible (backlog): {len(ineligible)}\\\")\\n\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n✅ ELIGIBLE TASKS (would dispatch up to 5):\\\")\\nfor i, t in enumerate(eligible[:5], 1):\\n    notes_preview = (t.get('note','') or '')[:80].replace('\\\\n', ' ')\\n    print(f\\\"  {i}. [{t.get('priority','?')}] {t['id']}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"     {t['title'][:65]}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"     Note: {notes_preview}\\\")\\n    print()\\nif len(eligible) > 5:\\n    print(f\\\"  ... {len(eligible)-5} more eligible (would not dispatch tonight)\\\")\\n\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n⛔ INELIGIBLE BACKLOG TASKS:\\\")\\nfor t, reason in ineligible:\\n    print(f\\\"  [{t.get('priority','?')}] {t['id']}: {t['title'][:50]} — {reason}\\\")\\n\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n── Simulation ──\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"If Night Shift activated now:\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"  → Would pick: {eligible[0]['title'][:50] if eligible else 'None (no eligible tasks)'}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"  → Would complete up to: {min(5, len(eligible))} tasks\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"  → Would stop at 06:30 or after 5 tasks\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"  → Morning report at 07:00\\\")\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"d0d2e49d-9cda-4106-b947-333d024298f1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \"%{http_code}\" http://localhost:3000/","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"curl -s -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" http://localhost:3000/\", \"timeout\": 5}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"acd3e3c0-75c1-4984-9f6d-63e31d50f575","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check for any in_progress tasks\npython3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\nip = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'in_progress']\nprint(f'in_progress: {len(ip)}')\nfor t in ip:\n    print(f'  {t[\\\"id\\\"]}: {t[\\\"title\\\"][:50]} (step={t.get(\\\"currentStep\\\",\\\"?\\\")}, progress={t.get(\\\"progress\\\",0)}%)')\n\"","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"# Check for any in_progress tasks\\npython3 -c \\\"\\nimport json\\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\nip = [t for t in tasks if t.get('status') == 'in_progress']\\nprint(f'in_progress: {len(ip)}')\\nfor t in ip:\\n    print(f'  {t[\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\"]}: {t[\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\"][:50]} (step={t.get(\\\\\\\"currentStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"?\\\\\\\")}, progress={t.get(\\\\\\\"progress\\\\\\\",0)}%)')\\n\\\"\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":80746,"output":1061,"cacheRead":9600,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":91407,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780510362330,"responseId":"gen-1780510362-kytqttZKXr6bosoiuoyu"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b7def3ef","parentId":"9534cf05","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"4210e027-0e69-49da-bcb7-7113dbb17097","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 1368 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if need"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":65,"aggregated":"============================================================\nNIGHT SHIFT DRY RUN — 2026-06-03 18:13 UTC\n============================================================\n\n📊 Total tasks: 81\n   Backlog: 14\n   Night Shift eligible: 13\n   Ineligible (backlog): 1\n\n✅ ELIGIBLE TASKS (would dispatch up to 5):\n  1. [P2] task-ac75ac7b\n     Operational Work Panel\n     Note: Add a filtered view that shows only incident and operational tasks, visually dis\n\n  2. [P2] task-efcd3558\n     Runbook Data Model\n     Note: Design and implement a structured data model for runbooks: incident type, severi\n\n  3. [P2] task-d7b9c364\n     Runbook UI\n     Note: Display runbook steps when viewing an incident. Show the relevant runbook based \n\n  4. [P2] task-f9f8c7ce\n     Incident Type Mapping\n     Note: Classify incidents into types (e.g., cron failure, rate limit, service down, dep\n\n  5. [P2] task-f2727327\n     Task Creation From Runbooks\n     Note: Convert runbook steps into actionable tasks on the Kanban board. Each step becom\n\n  ... 8 more eligible (would not dispatch tonight)\n\n⛔ INELIGIBLE BACKLOG TASKS:\n  [P2] task-9f6de5b0: Operational Readiness Dashboard — stalled at 2026-06-03T17:43:52\n\n── Simulation ──\nIf Night Shift activated now:\n  → Would pick: Operational Work Panel\n  → Would complete up to: 5 tasks\n  → Would stop at 06:30 or after 5 tasks\n  → Morning report at 07:00","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780510412906}}
