{"type":"message","id":"25a2e755","parentId":"48e0e900","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now spawn the sub-agent with explicit timestamp update instructions:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"4de5cf47-8ad7-4cd2-a357-a2a604b6cec8","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"label":"operational-work-panel","mode":"run","task":"## Task: Operational Work Panel\n\n**Task ID:** task-ac75ac7b\n**Priority:** P2\n**Phase:** 2 Night Shift test — single task validation\n\n### What to do\nAdd a filtered view to the Mission Control Dashboard that shows only incident and operational tasks, visually distinct from feature work. Different color coding, separate section in the Kanban, and a toggle to show/hide operational vs. feature work.\n\n### Context\n- Mission Control is a TanStack Start app at `~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/`\n- Dev server running on port 3000 (Vite) — don't restart it\n- Tasks are in `data/tasks.json` — the Kanban board reads from here\n- The task type is defined in the route components (likely `src/routes/tasks.tsx`)\n- Look for existing task filtering/color coding patterns\n\n### Steps\n1. Read the tasks route component and understand the current Kanban structure\n2. Add a toggle/filter mechanism for operational vs feature tasks\n3. Add color coding or visual distinction for operational tasks\n4. Test that the app still loads (port 3000 returns 200)\n5. Commit with message: \"Add operational work panel filter to Kanban\"\n\n### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Task Progress Updates\nYou MUST update `data/tasks.json` at each step:\n\n```python\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\n# Read current state\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\n# Find your task and update it\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-ac75ac7b':\n        t['currentStep'] = 'Your specific action here'  # e.g. \"Reading tasks.tsx\"\n        t['progress'] = 25  # 10% start, 25% early, 50% midway, 75% late, 100% done\n        t['lastActivity'] = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n        break\n\n# Write back\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\n```\n\nUpdate at LEAST at these milestones:\n- 10%: \"Reading tasks route component\"\n- 25%: \"Adding operational filter UI\"\n- 50%: \"Implementing color coding\"\n- 75%: \"Testing and fixing\"\n- 100%: completion (see below)\n\n### Completion\nBefore finishing, update the task to done:\n- status: \"done\"\n- progress: 100\n- currentStep: \"Completed\"\n- completedAt: current ISO timestamp\n- summary: \"One-line description of what was implemented\"\n- Add history entry with action \"completed\"\n\nThen commit and push code changes.\n\n### Safety\n- Do NOT modify openclaw.json, cron jobs, LaunchAgents, or gateway config\n- Do NOT restart the dev server\n- Do NOT touch work-dispatcher.sh.disabled\n- Verify app loads after changes (curl localhost:3000)\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"label\": \"operational-work-panel\", \"mode\": \"run\", \"task\": \"## Task: Operational Work Panel\\n\\n**Task ID:** task-ac75ac7b\\n**Priority:** P2\\n**Phase:** 2 Night Shift test — single task validation\\n\\n### What to do\\nAdd a filtered view to the Mission Control Dashboard that shows only incident and operational tasks, visually distinct from feature work. Different color coding, separate section in the Kanban, and a toggle to show/hide operational vs. feature work.\\n\\n### Context\\n- Mission Control is a TanStack Start app at `~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/`\\n- Dev server running on port 3000 (Vite) — don't restart it\\n- Tasks are in `data/tasks.json` — the Kanban board reads from here\\n- The task type is defined in the route components (likely `src/routes/tasks.tsx`)\\n- Look for existing task filtering/color coding patterns\\n\\n### Steps\\n1. Read the tasks route component and understand the current Kanban structure\\n2. Add a toggle/filter mechanism for operational vs feature tasks\\n3. Add color coding or visual distinction for operational tasks\\n4. Test that the app still loads (port 3000 returns 200)\\n5. Commit with message: \\\"Add operational work panel filter to Kanban\\\"\\n\\n### ⚠️ CRITICAL: Task Progress Updates\\nYou MUST update `data/tasks.json` at each step:\\n\\n```python\\nimport json\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\\n# Read current state\\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\n# Find your task and update it\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] == 'task-ac75ac7b':\\n        t['currentStep'] = 'Your specific action here'  # e.g. \\\"Reading tasks.tsx\\\"\\n        t['progress'] = 25  # 10% start, 25% early, 50% midway, 75% late, 100% done\\n        t['lastActivity'] = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\\n        break\\n\\n# Write back\\nwith open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json', 'w') as f:\\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\\n```\\n\\nUpdate at LEAST at these milestones:\\n- 10%: \\\"Reading tasks route component\\\"\\n- 25%: \\\"Adding operational filter UI\\\"\\n- 50%: \\\"Implementing color coding\\\"\\n- 75%: \\\"Testing and fixing\\\"\\n- 100%: completion (see below)\\n\\n### Completion\\nBefore finishing, update the task to done:\\n- status: \\\"done\\\"\\n- progress: 100\\n- currentStep: \\\"Completed\\\"\\n- completedAt: current ISO timestamp\\n- summary: \\\"One-line description of what was implemented\\\"\\n- Add history entry with action \\\"completed\\\"\\n\\nThen commit and push code changes.\\n\\n### Safety\\n- Do NOT modify openclaw.json, cron jobs, LaunchAgents, or gateway config\\n- Do NOT restart the dev server\\n- Do NOT touch work-dispatcher.sh.disabled\\n- Verify app loads after changes (curl localhost:3000)\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha",