{"type":"message","id":"9657335f","parentId":"d22f136b","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me update the Night Shift section with the two fixes:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"1c297f58-90a2-474b-90bc-17301b0645a8","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### Dispatch\n- Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\n- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min\n- On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\n- On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\n- Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message","newText":"### Dispatch\n- Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\n- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min — this is CRITICAL. Without intermediate updates, stall detection cannot function and the morning report cannot assess agent behavior.\n- **Night Shift stall rule:** If a task has been in_progress for >30 min with no `lastActivity` update (or currentStep still shows \"Agent starting…\"), reset it to backlog immediately. Do NOT let Night Shift tasks sit frozen. The 07:00 morning report should never show a task that's been stuck for hours.\n- On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\n- On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\n- Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message"},{"oldText":"### Morning Report (07:00)\nSend Telegram sitrep:\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task] — [one-line summary]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n```","newText":"### Morning Report (07:00)\nSend Telegram sitrep:\n```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task] — [one-line summary]\n  ↳ Progress updates: [N] intermediate steps logged — [good/needs improvement]\n\n── Agent Behavior ──\n📈 Tasks with intermediate progress updates: X/Y\n⚠️ Tasks that went straight start→complete with no steps: [list or \"None\"]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n```\n\n**Progress update assessment:** For each completed task, check its history. If there are no `progress` or `step_update` entries between `started` and `completed`, flag it. The goal is at least 2-3 intermediate updates per task."}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"### Dispatch\\n- Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\\n- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min\\n- On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\\n- On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\\n- Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message\", \"newText\": \"### Dispatch\\n- Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\\n- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min — this is CRITICAL. Without intermediate updates, stall detection cannot function and the morning report cannot assess agent behavior.\\n- **Night Shift stall rule:** If a task has been in_progress for >30 min with no `lastActivity` update (or currentStep still shows \\\"Agent starting…\\\"), reset it to backlog immediately. Do NOT let Night Shift tasks sit frozen. The 07:00 morning report should never show a task that's been stuck for hours.\\n- On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\\n- On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\\n- Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message\"}, {\"oldText\": \"### Morning Report (07:00)\\nSend Telegram sitrep:\\n```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task] — [one-line summary]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\\n```\", \"newText\": \"### Morning Report (07:00)\\nSend Telegram sitrep:\\n```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task] — [one-line summary]\\n  ↳ Progress updates: [N] intermediate steps logged — [good/needs improvement]\\n\\n── Agent Behavior ──\\n📈 Tasks with intermediate progress updates: X/Y\\n⚠️ Tasks that went straight start→complete with no steps: [list or \\\"None\\\"]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\\n```\\n\\n**Progress update assessment:** For each completed task, check its history. If there are no `progress` or `step_update` entries between `started` and `completed`, flag it. The goal is at least 2-3 intermediate updates per task.\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1804,"output":731,"cacheRead":103296,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":105831,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780513334950,"responseId":"gen-1780513335-h5GhM9MxtjNvFGIeZtii"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee2e8ed2","parentId":"9657335f","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"1c297f58-90a2-474b-90bc-17301b0645a8","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 88 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if needed"}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  78 - Token limit: 100K total per night\n  79 \n  80 ### Dispatch\n  81 - Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\n- 82 - Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min\n+ 82 - Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min — this is CRITICAL. Without intermediate updates, stall detection cannot function and the morning report cannot assess agent behavior.\n+ 83 - **Night Shift stall rule:** If a task has been in_progress for >30 min with no `lastActivity` update (or currentStep still shows \"Agent starting…\"), reset it to backlog immediately. Do NOT let Night Shift tasks sit frozen. The 07:00 morning report should never show a task that's been stuck for hours.\n  83 - On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\n  84 - On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\n  85 - Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message\n  86 \n     ...\n 101 ✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\n 102 \n 103 Completed:\n 104 • [Task] — [one-line summary]\n+106   ↳ Progress updates: [N] intermediate steps logged — [good/needs improvement]\n 105 \n+108 ── Agent Behavior ──\n+109 📈 Tasks with intermediate progress updates: X/Y\n+110 ⚠️ Tasks that went straight start→complete with no steps: [list or \"None\"]\n+111 \n 106 ── Station Status ──\n 107 💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n 108 🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \"None\"]\n 109 ⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n 110 📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n 111 ```\n 112 \n+119 **Progress update assessment:** For each completed task, check its history. If there are no `progress` or `step_update` entries between `started` and `completed`, flag it. The goal is at least 2-3 intermediate updates per task.\n+120 \n 113 ## Rule: Sub-agent Timeout\n 114 - If a sub-agent runs for >5 minutes with no resolution, kill it and add the task to backlog\n 115 - If the main agent spends >10 minutes debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n 116 - Always report what was tried and what the blocker is when adding to backlog","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\n@@ -78,9 +78,10 @@\n - Token limit: 100K total per night\n \n ### Dispatch\n - Pick ONE eligible task, spawn sub-agent with full task brief\n-- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min\n+- Sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5-10 min — this is CRITICAL. Without intermediate updates, stall detection cannot function and the morning report cannot assess agent behavior.\n+- **Night Shift stall rule:** If a task has been in_progress for >30 min with no `lastActivity` update (or currentStep still shows \"Agent starting…\"), reset it to backlog immediately. Do NOT let Night Shift tasks sit frozen. The 07:00 morning report should never show a task that's been stuck for hours.\n - On completion: mark done with summary, pick next eligible task\n - On failure: move back to backlog with failure note, no retry\n - Stop immediately if 429s detected or Andre sends a message\n \n@@ -101,16 +102,23 @@\n ✅ Completed: X tasks | ⏭️ Skipped: Y | ❌ Failed: Z | 🪙 Tokens: ~N\n \n Completed:\n • [Task] — [one-line summary]\n+  ↳ Progress updates: [N] intermediate steps logged — [good/needs improvement]\n \n+── Agent Behavior ──\n+📈 Tasks with intermediate progress updates: X/Y\n+⚠️ Tasks that went straight start→complete with no steps: [list or \"None\"]\n+\n ── Station Status ──\n 💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n 🚨 Incidents overnight: [count or \"None\"]\n ⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n 📊 Backlog: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n ```\n \n+**Progress update assessment:** For each completed task, check its history. If there are no `progress` or `step_update` entries between `started` and `completed`, flag it. The goal is at least 2-3 intermediate updates per task.\n+\n ## Rule: Sub-agent Timeout\n - If a sub-agent runs for >5 minutes with no resolution, kill it and add the task to backlog\n - If the main agent spends >10 minutes debugging the same issue, stop and add to backlog\n - Always report what was tried and what the blocker is when adding to backlog\n","firstChangedLine":82},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780513366094}}
{"type":"message","id":"02ba44af","parentId":"ee2e8ed2","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update the NIGHT_SHIFT.md design doc to match:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"38f027d5-2291-4cb4-89ff-4bcfef4c0f23","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md","edits":[{"oldText":"### Sub-agent Constraints\n- Each sub-agent gets a 15-minute timeout\n- Sub-agent must update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5 min\n- Sub-agent must write a completion summary before marking done\n- If a sub-agent fails, the task goes back to backlog with failure note — no retry","newText":"### Sub-agent Constraints\n- Each sub-agent gets a 15-minute timeout\n- Sub-agent must update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5 min — **this is non-negotiable for Night Shift**. The morning report will flag tasks that went straight from start→completion with no intermediate steps.\n- Sub-agent must write a completion summary before marking done\n- If a sub-agent fails, the task goes back to backlog with failure note — no retry\n- **Night Shift stall rule:** If a task has been in_progress for >30 min with no `lastActivity` update (or currentStep still \"Agent starting…\"), reset to backlog immediately. Never let a frozen task sit until morning."},{"oldText":"```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\n✅ Completed: X tasks\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n\nFailed:\n• [Task title] — [reason]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n```\n\nIf zero tasks were completed:\n\n```\n🟥 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\nNo tasks completed.\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n```","newText":"```\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\n✅ Completed: X tasks\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\n\nCompleted:\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\n  ↳ Progress updates: [N] intermediate steps logged — [good/needs improvement]\n\n── Agent Behavior ──\n📈 Tasks with intermediate progress updates: X/Y\n⚠️ Tasks that went straight start→complete with no steps: [list or \"None\"]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\n```\n\nIf zero tasks were completed:\n\n```\n🟥 Night Shift Report — [date]\n\nNo tasks completed.\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\n\n── Station Status ──\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \"None\"]\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\n```\n\n**Progress update assessment:** For each completed task, check its history. If there are no `progress` or `step_update` entries between `started` and `completed`, flag it. The goal is at least 2-3 intermediate updates per task."}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/NIGHT_SHIFT.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"### Sub-agent Constraints\\n- Each sub-agent gets a 15-minute timeout\\n- Sub-agent must update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5 min\\n- Sub-agent must write a completion summary before marking done\\n- If a sub-agent fails, the task goes back to backlog with failure note — no retry\", \"newText\": \"### Sub-agent Constraints\\n- Each sub-agent gets a 15-minute timeout\\n- Sub-agent must update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` every 5 min — **this is non-negotiable for Night Shift**. The morning report will flag tasks that went straight from start→completion with no intermediate steps.\\n- Sub-agent must write a completion summary before marking done\\n- If a sub-agent fails, the task goes back to backlog with failure note — no retry\\n- **Night Shift stall rule:** If a task has been in_progress for >30 min with no `lastActivity` update (or currentStep still \\\"Agent starting…\\\"), reset to backlog immediately. Never let a frozen task sit until morning.\"}, {\"oldText\": \"```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\n✅ Completed: X tasks\\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n\\nFailed:\\n• [Task title] — [reason]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\\n```\\n\\nIf zero tasks were completed:\\n\\n```\\n🟥 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\nNo tasks completed.\\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\\n```\", \"newText\": \"```\\n🌙 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\n✅ Completed: X tasks\\n⏭️ Skipped: Y tasks (rate limit / time / eligibility)\\n❌ Failed: Z tasks\\n🪙 Tokens used: ~N\\n\\nCompleted:\\n• [Task title] — [one-line summary]\\n  ↳ Progress updates: [N] intermediate steps logged — [good/needs improvement]\\n\\n── Agent Behavior ──\\n📈 Tasks with intermediate progress updates: X/Y\\n⚠️ Tasks that went straight start→complete with no steps: [list or \\\"None\\\"]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog remaining: N tasks (M night-shift eligible)\\n```\\n\\nIf zero tasks were completed:\\n\\n```\\n🟥 Night Shift Report — [date]\\n\\nNo tasks completed.\\nReason: [no eligible tasks / rate limits hit / etc.]\\n\\n── Station Status ──\\n💾 Disk: workspace X GB / MC repo Y GB\\n🚨 Incidents overnight: [count + brief description, or \\\"None\\\"]\\n⏱️ Gateway uptime: Xh Ym\\n📊 Backlog: N tasks (0 night-shift eligible)\\n```\\n\\n**Progress update assessment:** For each completed task, check its history. If there are no `progress` or `step_update` entries between `started` and `completed`, flag it. The goal is at least 2-3 intermediate updates per task.\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":784,"output":942,"cacheRead":105088,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":106814,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780513366105,"responseId":"gen-1780513366-9MHmON2NDMlJKD99WImI"}}
