{"type":"message","id":"06d71d58","parentId":"ea320634","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me quickly assess the remaining tasks and batch-decide:\n\n- **task-f9f8c7ce \"Incident Type Mapping\" (P2):** Auto-suggest incident type based on error patterns. Can implement — add a mapping function and integrate with incident creation.\n- **task-f2727327 \"Task Creation From Runbooks\" (P2):** Convert runbook steps into Kanban tasks. Can implement — extend the incidents-create handler.\n- **task-e8a74157 \"Asset View\" (P2):** Dedicated assets page. Can implement — new route page.\n- **task-bcd36145 \"Unified Event Model\" (P2):** All events feed into a single model. This is a significant data model change — probably needs design discussion. Move to Triage.\n- **task-f9e3796c \"Incident Events in Timeline\" (P2):** — partially done (timeline exists in incidents). Clarify scope.\n- **task-fde53af6 \"Automation Health States\" (P2):** — partially exists (cron status in scheduler). Clarify scope.\n- **task-9f6de5b0 \"Operational Readiness Dashboard\" (P2):** — design-heavy. Triage.\n- **task-de47f5f5 \"Auto Remediation\" (P3):** — clear scope, can implement.\n- **task-be03dff8 \"Runbook Evolution\" (P3):** — needs runbook resolution history. Design-heavy. Triage.\n- **task-fce301b7 \"Incident Response Atmosphere\" (P3):** — agent office animation events. Fun but design-heavy. Triage.\n\nLet me implement the straightforward ones and triage the rest. I'll do Incident Type Mapping first:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ac9112e1-2b42-48e6-b260-59fd5b1df029","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\ntasks_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-f9f8c7ce':\n        t['status'] = 'in_progress'\n        t['currentStep'] = 'Implementing incident type auto-detection'\n        t['progress'] = 10\n        t['lastActivity'] = now.isoformat()\n        t['startedAt'] = now.isoformat()\n        if 'history' not in t:\n            t['history'] = []\n        t['history'].append({\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\n            'action': 'started',\n            'actor': 'monkey',\n            'details': 'Picked up for backlog processing — implementing incident type auto-detection'\n        })\n        print(f\"Picked up: {t['title']}\")\n        break\n\nwith open(tasks_file, 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\\ntasks_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\\\"\\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\\n\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] == 'task-f9f8c7ce':\\n        t['status'] = 'in_progress'\\n        t['currentStep'] = 'Implementing incident type auto-detection'\\n        t['progress'] = 10\\n        t['lastActivity'] = now.isoformat()\\n        t['startedAt'] = now.isoformat()\\n        if 'history' not in t:\\n            t['history'] = []\\n        t['history'].append({\\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\\n            'action': 'started',\\n            'actor': 'monkey',\\n            'details': 'Picked up for backlog processing — implementing incident type auto-detection'\\n        })\\n        print(f\\\"Picked up: {t['title']}\\\")\\n        break\\n\\nwith open(tasks_file, 'w') as f:\\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":412,"output":671,"cacheRead":123776,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":124859,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse