{"type":"message","id":"b508a83c","parentId":"80d9c034","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. I'll add the Operations Engine section after the Anti-Patterns section:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"e710f2fa-d0a5-404f-b6c9-e2f6c54639d4","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md","edits":[{"oldText":"## Agent Communication Rules","newText":"## Operations Engine\n\n**Definition:** Task Dispatcher + Agent Execution + Stall Detection + Triage Flow.\n\nThe Operations Engine is the system that works through the task backlog autonomously during awake hours. It is NOT the same as Dreaming (which is memory consolidation at 3am).\n\n**How it works:**\n1. **Task Dispatcher** (heartbeat) picks the highest-priority dispatchable task from Backlog\n2. **Agent Execution** — spawns a sub-agent that works the task, updating `currentStep` and `lastActivity` at every step\n3. **Stall Detection** — if a task sits In Progress with no activity for >30 min, it's reset to Backlog\n4. **Triage Flow** — if an agent hits a wall (blocked, unclear, needs human input), the task moves to Triage with clear notes explaining what's needed. Tasks never sit frozen in In Progress.\n\n**Key rules:**\n- ONE task In Progress at a time per agent\n- Blocked/unclear tasks → Triage (not frozen In Progress)\n- Triage tasks include: what was attempted, what's blocking, what specific action Andre needs to take\n- Completed tasks auto-move to Done with summaries\n- P1 tasks stay in Backlog for Andre's awareness (not auto-dispatched)\n- Night Shift (01:00-07:00) is the Operations Engine running autonomously while Andre sleeps, with stricter limits (max 2-5 tasks, no P1, stops on rate limits)\n\n**Triage is NOT a graveyard.** It's where tasks go when they need human input. Andre reviews Triage regularly and moves approved tasks back to Backlog.\n\n## Agent Communication Rules"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"## Agent Communication Rules\", \"newText\": \"## Operations Engine\\n\\n**Definition:** Task Dispatcher + Agent Execution + Stall Detection + Triage Flow.\\n\\nThe Operations Engine is the system that works through the task backlog autonomously during awake hours. It is NOT the same as Dreaming (which is memory consolidation at 3am).\\n\\n**How it works:**\\n1. **Task Dispatcher** (heartbeat) picks the highest-priority dispatchable task from Backlog\\n2. **Agent Execution** — spawns a sub-agent that works the task, updating `currentStep` and `lastActivity` at every step\\n3. **Stall Detection** — if a task sits In Progress with no activity for >30 min, it's reset to Backlog\\n4. **Triage Flow** — if an agent hits a wall (blocked, unclear, needs human input), the task moves to Triage with clear notes explaining what's needed. Tasks never sit frozen in In Progress.\\n\\n**Key rules:**\\n- ONE task In Progress at a time per agent\\n- Blocked/unclear tasks → Triage (not frozen In Progress)\\n- Triage tasks include: what was attempted, what's blocking, what specific action Andre needs to take\\n- Completed tasks auto-move to Done with summaries\\n- P1 tasks stay in Backlog for Andre's awareness (not auto-dispatched)\\n- Night Shift (01:00-07:00) is the Operations Engine running autonomously while Andre sleeps, with stricter limits (max 2-5 tasks, no P1, stops on rate limits)\\n\\n**Triage is NOT a graveyard.** It's where tasks go when they need human input. Andre reviews Triage regularly and moves approved tasks back to Backlog.\\n\\n## Agent Communication Rules\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1979,"output":446,"cacheRead":145792,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":148217,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780515184639,"responseId":"gen-1780515184-t77omGsTloEEwsPnwn2W"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a6947a2b","parentId":"b508a83c","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"e710f2fa-d0a5-404f-b6c9-e2f6c54639d4","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 88 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if needed"}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n 102 - **Status:** Watcher unloaded on 2026-05-22 due to persistent pool exhaustion. Re-enable manually when pool recovers.\n 103 \n 104 \n 105 \n+106 ## Operations Engine\n+107 \n+108 **Definition:** Task Dispatcher + Agent Execution + Stall Detection + Triage Flow.\n+109 \n+110 The Operations Engine is the system that works through the task backlog autonomously during awake hours. It is NOT the same as Dreaming (which is memory consolidation at 3am).\n+111 \n+112 **How it works:**\n+113 1. **Task Dispatcher** (heartbeat) picks the highest-priority dispatchable task from Backlog\n+114 2. **Agent Execution** — spawns a sub-agent that works the task, updating `currentStep` and `lastActivity` at every step\n+115 3. **Stall Detection** — if a task sits In Progress with no activity for >30 min, it's reset to Backlog\n+116 4. **Triage Flow** — if an agent hits a wall (blocked, unclear, needs human input), the task moves to Triage with clear notes explaining what's needed. Tasks never sit frozen in In Progress.\n+117 \n+118 **Key rules:**\n+119 - ONE task In Progress at a time per agent\n+120 - Blocked/unclear tasks → Triage (not frozen In Progress)\n+121 - Triage tasks include: what was attempted, what's blocking, what specific action Andre needs to take\n+122 - Completed tasks auto-move to Done with summaries\n+123 - P1 tasks stay in Backlog for Andre's awareness (not auto-dispatched)\n+124 - Night Shift (01:00-07:00) is the Operations Engine running autonomously while Andre sleeps, with stricter limits (max 2-5 tasks, no P1, stops on rate limits)\n+125 \n+126 **Triage is NOT a graveyard.** It's where tasks go when they need human input. Andre reviews Triage regularly and moves approved tasks back to Backlog.\n+127 \n 106 ## Agent Communication Rules\n 107 \n 108 ### Status Reports Only\n 109 When the user asks \"anything else?\" or \"more recommendations?\", respond with a **status report only**:\n     ...","patch":"--- /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md\n+++ /Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/FRAMEWORK.md\n@@ -102,8 +102,30 @@\n - **Status:** Watcher unloaded on 2026-05-22 due to persistent pool exhaustion. Re-enable manually when pool recovers.\n \n \n \n+## Operations Engine\n+\n+**Definition:** Task Dispatcher + Agent Execution + Stall Detection + Triage Flow.\n+\n+The Operations Engine is the system that works through the task backlog autonomously during awake hours. It is NOT the same as Dreaming (which is memory consolidation at 3am).\n+\n+**How it works:**\n+1. **Task Dispatcher** (heartbeat) picks the highest-priority dispatchable task from Backlog\n+2. **Agent Execution** — spawns a sub-agent that works the task, updating `currentStep` and `lastActivity` at every step\n+3. **Stall Detection** — if a task sits In Progress with no activity for >30 min, it's reset to Backlog\n+4. **Triage Flow** — if an agent hits a wall (blocked, unclear, needs human input), the task moves to Triage with clear notes explaining what's needed. Tasks never sit frozen in In Progress.\n+\n+**Key rules:**\n+- ONE task In Progress at a time per agent\n+- Blocked/unclear tasks → Triage (not frozen In Progress)\n+- Triage tasks include: what was attempted, what's blocking, what specific action Andre needs to take\n+- Completed tasks auto-move to Done with summaries\n+- P1 tasks stay in Backlog for Andre's awareness (not auto-dispatched)\n+- Night Shift (01:00-07:00) is the Operations Engine running autonomously while Andre sleeps, with stricter limits (max 2-5 tasks, no P1, stops on rate limits)\n+\n+**Triage is NOT a graveyard.** It's where tasks go when they need human input. Andre reviews Triage re