{"type":"message","id":"3f4cbdb4","parentId":"8449c9f5","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.224Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All clear. MC 200, 0 in_progress, 0 backlog, 74 done, 7 triaged. Night Shift inactive (22:00 BST). Nothing needs attention.\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":794,"output":50,"cacheRead":149120,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":149964,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780521189063,"responseId":"gen-1780521189-NZYTVjl1XwziUQoS0n6O"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ab3a1def","parentId":"3f4cbdb4","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.224Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"I've reviewed all 7 Triage tasks. Update each task card with these \ndecisions, then move them back to Backlog with the clarified scope.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n1. UNIFIED EVENT MODEL (task-bcd36145) + INCIDENT EVENTS (task-f9e3796c)\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nMERGE these two into one task: \"Timeline — Unified Event Model\"\n\nBuild a \"Timeline\" tab on the Dashboard showing:\n- Task state changes (created → in_progress → done → stalled)\n- Incident state changes (created → investigating → resolved)\n- Cron job runs (success/failure/timeout)\n- Agent actions (task assigned, task completed)\n- System health events (gateway status, disk warnings)\n\nAlso add a Timeline section inside the Incident detail drawer showing \nthat incident's full chronological history.\n\nFilterable by event type. Each event has: timestamp, type, source, \nseverity, description, links to related entities.\n\nMove BOTH cards to Done (merged) and create ONE new Backlog task \nwith this combined scope. Priority: P2.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n2. AUTOMATION HEALTH STATES (task-fde53af6)\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nIntegrate into the EXISTING Scheduler page. Do not build a new page.\n\nEach cron job row gets:\n- Colored status dot: green (healthy), amber (1-2 consecutive failures), \n  red (3+ failures)\n- Consecutive failure count\n- Average duration\n\nTop of Scheduler page: overall health summary bar — \"3 healthy, \n1 degraded, 0 failing\"\n\nStates: healthy, degraded, failing, unknown.\n\nMove back to Backlog. Priority: P2.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n3. RETRY POLICIES (task-a6f37a6f)\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nKeep it simple. One global policy:\n- 3 retries with 5-minute gaps between attempts\n- After 3 failures, auto-create a P2 incident\n- No exponential backoff (that's Phase 5)\n- No per-job customization (not needed for a single-user system)\n\nMove back to Backlog. Priority: P2.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n4. RUNBOOK EVOLUTION (task-be03dff8)\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nPark this. It depends on Runbooks (Phase 2) which hasn't been built yet.\nThere are no runbooks to evolve.\n\nMove to Backlog with a dependency note: \"Depends on Phase 2 Runbooks \ncompletion.\" Priority stays P3.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n5. INCIDENT RESPONSE ATMOSPHERE (task-fce301b7)\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nThree effects only. Calm operational awareness, not arcade chaos:\n\na) AMBIENTSTATION TINT SHIFT — Already built (AmbientStation has \n   calm/busy/alert/critical states). Wire it to incident severity:\n   - P1 critical → shift to critical (red tint)\n   - P2 high → shift to alert (amber tint)\n   - P3/P4 → shift to busy (subtle warm tint)\n   - No open incidents → calm (default)\n\nb) ALERT BANNER ON DASHBOARD — A slim banner at the top of the \n   Dashboard when incidents are open:\n   - \"⚠️ 2 open incidents — 1 P1, 1 P2\" — clickable to Incidents page\n   - Disappears when all incidents are resolved\n\nc) ROOM PULSE FOR ASSIGNED AGENT — When an incident has an assigned \n   agent, that agent's room pulses subtly:\n   - Incident assigned to Life Support → Security Bay pulses amber\n   - Incident assigned to Systems Engineer → Engineering pulses amber\n   - Incident assigned to Space Monkey → Command HQ pulses amber\n   - Incident assigned to Archivist → Archive pulses amber\n   - Pulse stops when incident is resolved\n   - The pulse is SUBTLE — a gentle glow, not a flashing alarm\n\nMove back to Backlog. Priority: P3.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\n6. OPERATIONAL READINESS DASHBOARD (task-9f6de5b0)\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nThis is NOT a new page. Enhance the EXISTING Dashboard with:\n\na) STATION STATUS BAR — At the top of the Dashboard:\n   - 🟢 \"All systems nominal\" (no incidents, no stalled tasks)\n   - 🟡 \"2 incidents, 1 stalled task\" (warnings present)\n   - 🔴 \"1 P1 incident requires attention\" (critical)\n\nb) AGENT LOAD INDICATORS — On the Spacestation or Team page, show \n   how many tasks each agent has:\n   - Space Monkey: 3 tasks (1 in_progress, 2 assigned)\n   - Life Support: 0 tasks (standby)\n   - etc.\n\nc) BACKLOG COUNT BADGE — Already partially built on the sidebar \n   Tasks icon. Verify it's working and visible.\n\nMove back to Backlog. Priority: P2.\n\n═══════════════════════════════\nAFTER UPDATING THE CARDS\n═══════════════════════════════\n\nPick up the highest priority task that's ready to execute. Skip \nanything with unmet dependencies (Runbook Evolution depends on \nPhase 2 Runbooks, which isn't built yet).\n\nReport: how many tasks moved back to Backlog with clarified scope, \nand which task you're picking up first.","timestamp":1780521901272,"idempotencyKey":"d6418576-f29c-4d0c-af2a-413bd86d99a7:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0135d499","parentId":"ab3a1def","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.224Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me execute all of this. First, update the triage tasks and create the merged one:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"99e9d81f-b767-49d5-a187-99a0a69a7fe8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\ntasks_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n\n# 1. Merge Unified Event Model + Incident Events into one new task\n# Mark both originals as done (merged)\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] in ('task-bcd36145', 'task-f9e3796c'):\n        t['status'] = 'done'\n        t['completedAt'] = now.isoformat()\n        t['lastActivity'] = now.isoformat()\n        t['progress'] = 100\n        t['currentStep'] = 'Merged into new Timeline task'\n        t['summary'] = 'Merged into new combined task: Timeline — Unified Event Model (task-timeline-unified)'\n        if 'history' not in t:\n            t['history'] = []\n        t['history'].append({\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\n            'action': 'completed',\n            'actor': 'monkey',\n            'details': 'Merged with task-f9e3796c into new combined Timeline task per Andre review'\n        })\n        print(f\"✅ Merged: {t['title'][:50]}\")\n\n# Create the merged task\nnew_timeline_task = {\n    \"id\": \"task-timeline-unified\",\n    \"title\": \"Timeline — Unified Event Model\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": now.isoformat(),\n    \"note\": \"Build a Timeline tab on the Dashboard showing all station events: task state changes, incident state changes, cron job runs, agent actions, system health events. Also add a Timeline section inside the Incident detail drawer showing that incident's full chronological history. Filterable by event type. Each event has: timestamp, type, source, severity, description, links to related entities.\",\n    \"tags\": [\"timeline\", \"events\", \"dashboard\", \"incidents\"],\n    \"history\": [{\"ts\": now.isoformat(), \"action\": \"created\", \"actor\": \"monkey\", \"details\": \"Created by merging Unified Event Model (task-bcd36145) + Incident Events in Timeline (task-f9e3796c) per Andre review\"}],\n    \"lastActivity\": now.isoformat(),\n    \"currentStep\": None,\n    \"progress\": 0,\n    \"dispatchCount\": 0\n}\ntasks.append(new_timeline_task)\nprint(f\"✅ Created: {new_timeline_task['title']}\")\n\n# 2. Automation Health States — move back to Backlog with clarified scope\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-fde53af6':\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\n        t['currentStep'] = None\n        t['progress'] = 0\n        t['note'] = \"Integrate into the EXISTING Scheduler page. Each cron job row gets: colored status dot (green=healthy, amber=1-2 failures, red=3+ failures), consecutive failure count, average duration. Top of Scheduler: overall health summary bar — '3 healthy, 1 degraded, 0 failing'. States: healthy, degraded, failing, unknown. Do NOT build a new page.\"\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\n        if 'history' not in t:\n            t['history'] = []\n        t['history'].append({\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\n            'action': 'reassigned',\n            'actor': 'monkey',\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: integrate into existing Scheduler page, not a new page'\n        })\n        print(f\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']}\")\n        break\n\n# 3. Retry Policies — move back to Backlog with clarified scope\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-a6f37a6f':\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\n        t['currentStep'] = None\n        t['progress'] = 0\n        t['note'] = \"Keep it simple. One global policy: 3 retries with 5-minute gaps between attempts. After 3 failures, auto-create a P2 incident. No exponential backoff (Phase 5). No per-job customization (single-user system).\"\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\n        if 'history' not in t:\n            t['history'] = []\n        t['history'].append({\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\n            'action': 'reassigned',\n            'actor': 'monkey',\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: simple global policy, 3 retries + 5min gap, auto-P2 incident after 3 failures'\n        })\n        print(f\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']}\")\n        break\n\n# 4. Runbook Evolution — move back to Backlog with dependency note\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-be03dff8':\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\n        t['currentStep'] = None\n        t['progress'] = 0\n        t['note'] = \"Park this. Depends on Phase 2 Runbooks completion — there are no runbooks to evolve yet. When runbooks exist: update runbooks based on resolution history. When an incident is resolved differently than the runbook suggests, flag the runbook for review. Track runbook effectiveness over time.\"\n        t['tags'] = [\"runbook-evolution\", \"phase-2-dependent\"]\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\n        if 'history' not in t:\n            t['history'] = []\n        t['history'].append({\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\n            'action': 'reassigned',\n            'actor': 'monkey',\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with dependency: depends on Phase 2 Runbooks completion'\n        })\n        print(f\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']} (dependency: Phase 2 Runbooks)\")\n        break\n\n# 5. Incident Response Atmosphere — move back to Backlog with clarified scope\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-fce301b7':\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\n        t['currentStep'] = None\n        t['progress'] = 0\n        t['note'] = \"Three effects only — calm operational awareness, not arcade chaos:\\n\\na) AMBIENT STATION TINT SHIFT — Wire existing AmbientStation states to incident severity: P1→critical (red), P2→alert (amber), P3/P4→busy (warm), none→calm.\\n\\nb) ALERT BANNER ON DASHBOARD — Slim banner at top of Dashboard when incidents open: '⚠️ 2 open incidents — 1 P1, 1 P2' — clickable to Incidents page. Disappears when all resolved.\\n\\nc) ROOM PULSE FOR ASSIGNED AGENT — When an incident has an assigned agent, that agent's room pulses subtly (gentle glow, not flashing). Pulse stops when incident resolved.\"\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\n        if 'history' not in t:\n            t['history'] = []\n        t['history'].append({\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\n            'action': 'reassigned',\n            'actor': 'monkey',\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: 3 subtle effects (tint shift, alert banner, room pulse)'\n        })\n        print(f\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']}\")\n        break\n\n# 6. Operational Readiness Dashboard — move back to Backlog with clarified scope\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-9f6de5b0':\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\n        t['currentStep'] = None\n        t['progress'] = 0\n        t['note'] = \"Enhance the EXISTING Dashboard — NOT a new page.\\n\\na) STATION STATUS BAR — At top of Dashboard: 🟢 'All systems nominal' / 🟡 '2 incidents, 1 stalled task' / 🔴 '1 P1 incident requires attention'\\n\\nb) AGENT LOAD INDICATORS — On Spacestation or Team page, show task count per agent (e.g., Space Monkey: 3 tasks (1 in_progress, 2 assigned))\\n\\nc) BACKLOG COUNT BADGE — Verify existing sidebar Tasks badge is working and visible.\"\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\n        if 'history' not in t:\n            t['history'] = []\n        t['history'].append({\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\n            'action': 'reassigned',\n            'actor': 'monkey',\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: enhance existing Dashboard, not a new page'\n        })\n        print(f\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']}\")\n        break\n\nwith open(tasks_file, 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\n\n# Summary\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'backlog']\ndone = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'done']\ntriage = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'triage']\nprint(f\"\\n=== Summary ===\")\nprint(f\"Backlog: {len(backlog)}\")\nprint(f\"Done: {len(done)}\")\nprint(f\"Triage: {len(triage)}\")\nprint(f\"\\n=== Backlog tasks ===\")\nbacklog.sort(key=lambda t: ({'P1':0,'P2':1,'P3':2}.get(t.get('priority','P3'),3), t.get('ts','')))\nfor t in backlog:\n    dep = \" [DEPENDS ON Phase 2]\" if \"phase-2-dependent\" in t.get('tags',[]) else \"\"\n    print(f\"  [{t.get('priority','?')}] {t['id']}: {t['title'][:60]}{dep}\")\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\\ntasks_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\\\"\\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\\n\\n# 1. Merge Unified Event Model + Incident Events into one new task\\n# Mark both originals as done (merged)\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] in ('task-bcd36145', 'task-f9e3796c'):\\n        t['status'] = 'done'\\n        t['completedAt'] = now.isoformat()\\n        t['lastActivity'] = now.isoformat()\\n        t['progress'] = 100\\n        t['currentStep'] = 'Merged into new Timeline task'\\n        t['summary'] = 'Merged into new combined task: Timeline — Unified Event Model (task-timeline-unified)'\\n        if 'history' not in t:\\n            t['history'] = []\\n        t['history'].append({\\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\\n            'action': 'completed',\\n            'actor': 'monkey',\\n            'details': 'Merged with task-f9e3796c into new combined Timeline task per Andre review'\\n        })\\n        print(f\\\"✅ Merged: {t['title'][:50]}\\\")\\n\\n# Create the merged task\\nnew_timeline_task = {\\n    \\\"id\\\": \\\"task-timeline-unified\\\",\\n    \\\"title\\\": \\\"Timeline — Unified Event Model\\\",\\n    \\\"assignee\\\": \\\"monkey\\\",\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"backlog\\\",\\n    \\\"priority\\\": \\\"P2\\\",\\n    \\\"ts\\\": now.isoformat(),\\n    \\\"note\\\": \\\"Build a Timeline tab on the Dashboard showing all station events: task state changes, incident state changes, cron job runs, agent actions, system health events. Also add a Timeline section inside the Incident detail drawer showing that incident's full chronological history. Filterable by event type. Each event has: timestamp, type, source, severity, description, links to related entities.\\\",\\n    \\\"tags\\\": [\\\"timeline\\\", \\\"events\\\", \\\"dashboard\\\", \\\"incidents\\\"],\\n    \\\"history\\\": [{\\\"ts\\\": now.isoformat(), \\\"action\\\": \\\"created\\\", \\\"actor\\\": \\\"monkey\\\", \\\"details\\\": \\\"Created by merging Unified Event Model (task-bcd36145) + Incident Events in Timeline (task-f9e3796c) per Andre review\\\"}],\\n    \\\"lastActivity\\\": now.isoformat(),\\n    \\\"currentStep\\\": None,\\n    \\\"progress\\\": 0,\\n    \\\"dispatchCount\\\": 0\\n}\\ntasks.append(new_timeline_task)\\nprint(f\\\"✅ Created: {new_timeline_task['title']}\\\")\\n\\n# 2. Automation Health States — move back to Backlog with clarified scope\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] == 'task-fde53af6':\\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\\n        t['currentStep'] = None\\n        t['progress'] = 0\\n        t['note'] = \\\"Integrate into the EXISTING Scheduler page. Each cron job row gets: colored status dot (green=healthy, amber=1-2 failures, red=3+ failures), consecutive failure count, average duration. Top of Scheduler: overall health summary bar — '3 healthy, 1 degraded, 0 failing'. States: healthy, degraded, failing, unknown. Do NOT build a new page.\\\"\\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\\n        if 'history' not in t:\\n            t['history'] = []\\n        t['history'].append({\\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\\n            'action': 'reassigned',\\n            'actor': 'monkey',\\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: integrate into existing Scheduler page, not a new page'\\n        })\\n        print(f\\\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']}\\\")\\n        break\\n\\n# 3. Retry Policies — move back to Backlog with clarified scope\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] == 'task-a6f37a6f':\\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\\n        t['currentStep'] = None\\n        t['progress'] = 0\\n        t['note'] = \\\"Keep it simple. One global policy: 3 retries with 5-minute gaps between attempts. After 3 failures, auto-create a P2 incident. No exponential backoff (Phase 5). No per-job customization (single-user system).\\\"\\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\\n        if 'history' not in t:\\n            t['history'] = []\\n        t['history'].append({\\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\\n            'action': 'reassigned',\\n            'actor': 'monkey',\\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: simple global policy, 3 retries + 5min gap, auto-P2 incident after 3 failures'\\n        })\\n        print(f\\\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']}\\\")\\n        break\\n\\n# 4. Runbook Evolution — move back to Backlog with dependency note\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] == 'task-be03dff8':\\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\\n        t['currentStep'] = None\\n        t['progress'] = 0\\n        t['note'] = \\\"Park this. Depends on Phase 2 Runbooks completion — there are no runbooks to evolve yet. When runbooks exist: update runbooks based on resolution history. When an incident is resolved differently than the runbook suggests, flag the runbook for review. Track runbook effectiveness over time.\\\"\\n        t['tags'] = [\\\"runbook-evolution\\\", \\\"phase-2-dependent\\\"]\\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\\n        if 'history' not in t:\\n            t['history'] = []\\n        t['history'].append({\\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\\n            'action': 'reassigned',\\n            'actor': 'monkey',\\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with dependency: depends on Phase 2 Runbooks completion'\\n        })\\n        print(f\\\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']} (dependency: Phase 2 Runbooks)\\\")\\n        break\\n\\n# 5. Incident Response Atmosphere — move back to Backlog with clarified scope\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] == 'task-fce301b7':\\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\\n        t['currentStep'] = None\\n        t['progress'] = 0\\n        t['note'] = \\\"Three effects only — calm operational awareness, not arcade chaos:\\\\n\\\\na) AMBIENT STATION TINT SHIFT — Wire existing AmbientStation states to incident severity: P1→critical (red), P2→alert (amber), P3/P4→busy (warm), none→calm.\\\\n\\\\nb) ALERT BANNER ON DASHBOARD — Slim banner at top of Dashboard when incidents open: '⚠️ 2 open incidents — 1 P1, 1 P2' — clickable to Incidents page. Disappears when all resolved.\\\\n\\\\nc) ROOM PULSE FOR ASSIGNED AGENT — When an incident has an assigned agent, that agent's room pulses subtly (gentle glow, not flashing). Pulse stops when incident resolved.\\\"\\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\\n        if 'history' not in t:\\n            t['history'] = []\\n        t['history'].append({\\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\\n            'action': 'reassigned',\\n            'actor': 'monkey',\\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: 3 subtle effects (tint shift, alert banner, room pulse)'\\n        })\\n        print(f\\\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']}\\\")\\n        break\\n\\n# 6. Operational Readiness Dashboard — move back to Backlog with clarified scope\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] == 'task-9f6de5b0':\\n        t['status'] = 'backlog'\\n        t['currentStep'] = None\\n        t['progress'] = 0\\n        t['note'] = \\\"Enhance the EXISTING Dashboard — NOT a new page.\\\\n\\\\na) STATION STATUS BAR — At top of Dashboard: 🟢 'All systems nominal' / 🟡 '2 incidents, 1 stalled task' / 🔴 '1 P1 incident requires attention'\\\\n\\\\nb) AGENT LOAD INDICATORS — On Spacestation or Team page, show task count per agent (e.g., Space Monkey: 3 tasks (1 in_progress, 2 assigned))\\\\n\\\\nc) BACKLOG COUNT BADGE — Verify existing sidebar Tasks badge is working and visible.\\\"\\n        t.pop('stalledAt', None)\\n        t['dispatchCount'] = 0\\n        if 'history' not in t:\\n            t['history'] = []\\n        t['history'].append({\\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\\n            'action': 'reassigned',\\n            'actor': 'monkey',\\n            'details': 'Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: enhance existing Dashboard, not a new page'\\n        })\\n        print(f\\\"✅ Backlog: {t['title']}\\\")\\n        break\\n\\nwith open(tasks_file, 'w') as f:\\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\\n\\n# Summary\\nbacklog = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'backlog']\\ndone = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'done']\\ntriage = [t for t in tasks if t['status'] == 'triage']\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n=== Summary ===\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Backlog: {len(backlog)}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Done: {len(done)}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Triage: {len(triage)}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n=== Backlog tasks ===\\\")\\nbacklog.sort(key=lambda t: ({'P1':0,'P2':1,'P3':2}.get(t.get('priority','P3'),3), t.get('ts','')))\\nfor t in backlog:\\n    dep = \\\" [DEPENDS ON Phase 2]\\\" if \\\"phase-2-dependent\\\" in t.get('tags',[]) else \\\"\\\"\\n    print(f\\\"  [{t.get('priority','?')}] {t['id']}: {t['title'][:60]}{dep}\\\")\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":141005,"output":2313,"cacheRead":9600,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":152918,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780521901448,"responseId":"gen-1780521901-V4Z8F7Qu4fHMnGVtUs6I"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d28eb8c4","parentId":"0135d499","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.224Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"99e9d81f-b767-49d5-a187-99a0a69a7fe8","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[... 721 more characters truncated; rerun with narrower args if neede"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":75,"aggregated":"✅ Merged: Unified Event Model\n✅ Merged: Incident Events in Timeline\n✅ Created: Timeline — Unified Event Model\n✅ Backlog: Automation Health States\n✅ Backlog: Retry Policies with Backoff\n✅ Backlog: Runbook Evolution (dependency: Phase 2 Runbooks)\n✅ Backlog: Incident Response Atmosphere\n✅ Backlog: Operational Readiness Dashboard\n\n=== Summary ===\nBacklog: 6\nDone: 76\nTriage: 0\n\n=== Backlog tasks ===\n  [P2] task-timeline-unified: Timeline — Unified Event Model\n  [P2] task-fde53af6: Automation Health States\n  [P2] task-a6f37a6f: Retry Policies with Backoff\n  [P2] task-9f6de5b0: Operational Readiness Dashboard\n  [P3] task-be03dff8: Runbook Evolution [DEPENDS ON Phase 2]\n  [P3] task-fce301b7: Incident Response Atmosphere","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780521972382}}
{"type":"message","id":"e01e388a","parentId":"d28eb8c4","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:23:08.224Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Triage is clear. 6 tasks back in Backlog with clarified scope. Now pick up the highest priority ready task. The P2 tasks are all ready — I'll start with \"Timeline — Unified Event Model\" since it's the most complex:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"10ca37c8-d84a-4e2d-a45e-a6826694b5c2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\ntasks_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-timeline-unified':\n        t['status'] = 'in_progress'\n        t['currentStep'] = 'Reading existing task/incident data models and route structure'\n        t['progress'] = 5\n        t['lastActivity'] = now.isoformat()\n        t['startedAt'] = now.isoformat()\n        if 'history' not in t:\n            t['history'] = []\n        t['history'].append({\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\n            'action': 'started',\n            'actor': 'monkey',\n            'details': 'Picked up for Operations Engine — building Timeline tab'\n        })\n        print(f\"Picked up: {t['title']}\")\n        break\n\nwith open(tasks_file, 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\\ntasks_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\\\"\\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\\n\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] == 'task-timeline-unified':\\n        t['status'] = 'in_progress'\\n        t['currentStep'] = 'Reading existing task/incident data models and route structure'\\n        t['progress'] = 5\\n        t['lastActivity'] = now.isoformat()\\n        t['startedAt'] = now.isoformat()\\n        if 'history' not in t:\\n            t['history'] = []\\n        t['history'].append({\\n            'ts': now.isoformat(),\\n            'action': 'started',\\n            'actor': 'monkey',\\n            'details': 'Picked up for Operations Engine — building Timeline tab'\\n        })\\n        print(f\\\"Picked up: {t['title']}\\\")\\n        break\\n\\nwith open(tasks_file, 'w') as f:\\n    json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":2627,"output":321,"cacheRead":150528,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":153476,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780521972390,"responseId":"gen-1780521972-JM3TyYZ0xr6dTrjH31wt"}}
