{"type":"message","id":"8153f8ce","parentId":"dc89ffec","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:29:17.557Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Room rendering is SVG-based. Rather than modifying the SVG floorplan (which would be complex and fragile), I'll add the room pulse effect at the Dashboard level by absolutely positioning pulsing overlays. But actually, the simpler approach is to just modify the StationFloorplan to accept an `activeRooms` prop and add a subtle glow filter to those rooms.\n\nGiven the complexity, let me just commit what we have (mood tint + alert banner working) and log the room pulse as a follow-up. The mood tint and alert banner are the impactful parts. The room pulse is polish."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"0f2e929e-de54-420a-8d1f-0491f22b391d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":8,"output":148,"cacheRead":20864,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":21020,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780525750204,"responseId":"gen-1780525750-uBERL0M9d44k79SyTQwg"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5c48e338","parentId":"8153f8ce","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:29:17.607Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"0f2e929e-de54-420a-8d1f-0491f22b391d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-be03dff8\",\n    \"title\": \"Runbook Evolution\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Park this. Depends on Phase 2 Runbooks completion \\u2014 there are no runbooks to evolve yet. When runbooks exist: update runbooks based on resolution history. When an incident is resolved differently than the runbook suggests, flag the runbook for review. Track runbook effectiveness over time.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning \\u2014 created from strategic roadmap\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T19:23:12.737604+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Moved to Triage \\u2014 needs human input: Runbook Evolution \\u2014 need resolution history tracking on runbooks. Design input needed on what to track and how to flag outdated steps\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T21:26:12.356009+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Moved back to Backlog with dependency: depends on Phase 2 Runbooks completion\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"currentStep\": null,\n    \"lastActivity\": \"2026-06-03T19:23:12.737604+00:00\",\n    \"progress\": 0,\n    \"tags\": [\n      \"runbook-evolution\",\n      \"phase-2-dependent\"\n    ],\n    \"dispatchCount\": 0\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-fce301b7\",\n    \"title\": \"Incident Response Atmosphere\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"done\",\n    \"priority\": \"P3\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Three effects only \\u2014 calm operational awareness, not arcade chaos:\\n\\na) AMBIENT STATION TINT SHIFT \\u2014 Wire existing AmbientStation states to incident severity: P1\\u2192critical (red), P2\\u2192alert (amber), P3/P4\\u2192busy (warm), none\\u2192calm.\\n\\nb) ALERT BANNER ON DASHBOARD \\u2014 Slim banner at top of Dashboard when incidents open: '\\u26a0\\ufe0f 2 open incidents \\u2014 1 P1, 1 P2' \\u2014 clickable to Incidents page. Disappears when all resolved.\\n\\nc) ROOM PULSE FOR ASSIGNED AGENT \\u2014 When an incident has an assigned agent, that agent's room pulses subtly (gentle glow, not flashing). Pulse stops when incident resolved.\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning \\u2014 created from strategic roadmap\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T19:23:12.737604+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Moved to Triage \\u2014 needs human input: Incident Response Atmosphere \\u2014 ambient agent office effects. Need Andre to define which visual effects, how they map to incident severity, scope of change\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T21:26:12.356009+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: 3 subtle effects (tint shift, alert banner, room pulse)\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T22:13:12.903727+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"started\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Picked up by Operations Engine \\u2014 implementing 3 subtle atmosphere effects\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T22:21:20.133871+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"completed\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Incident Response Atmosphere: tint shift, alert banner, room pulse implemented\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"currentStep\": \"Completed\",\n    \"lastActivity\": \"2026-06-03T22:21:20.133871+00:00\",\n    \"progress\": 100,\n    \"dispatchCount\": 0,\n    \"startedAt\": \"2026-06-03T22:13:12.903727+00:00\",\n    \"completedAt\": \"2026-06-03T22:21:20.133871+00:00\",\n    \"summary\": \"Implemented 2 of 3 atmosphere effects: (a) AmbientStation tint shift wired to incident severity (P1\\u2192critical/red, P2\\u2192alert/amber, P3/P4\\u2192busy/warm, none\\u2192calm), (b) Alert banner on Dashboard when incidents open (\\u26a0\\ufe0f 2 open incidents \\u2014 clickable to Incidents page). Room pulse (c) deferred \\u2014 needs StationFloorplan changes for activeIncidentRooms prop.\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"id\": \"task-9f6de5b0\",\n    \"title\": \"Operational Readiness Dashboard\",\n    \"assignee\": \"monkey\",\n    \"status\": \"backlog\",\n    \"priority\": \"P2\",\n    \"ts\": \"just now\",\n    \"note\": \"Enhance the EXISTING Dashboard \\u2014 NOT a new page.\\n\\na) STATION STATUS BAR \\u2014 At top of Dashboard: \\ud83d\\udfe2 'All systems nominal' / \\ud83d\\udfe1 '2 incidents, 1 stalled task' / \\ud83d\\udd34 '1 P1 incident requires attention'\\n\\nb) AGENT LOAD INDICATORS \\u2014 On Spacestation or Team page, show task count per agent (e.g., Space Monkey: 3 tasks (1 in_progress, 2 assigned))\\n\\nc) BACKLOG COUNT BADGE \\u2014 Verify existing sidebar Tasks badge is working and visible. [auto-dispatched 2026-06-03 22:34] [auto-dispatched 2026-06-03 23:05]\",\n    \"history\": [\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-02T14:43:59.301126+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"created\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Backlog planning \\u2014 created from strategic roadmap\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T17:43:52.178676+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"stalled\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog \\u2014 ghost dispatch, no agent spawned, no activity timestamp\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T19:23:12.737604+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Moved to Triage \\u2014 needs human input: Operational Readiness Dashboard \\u2014 need Andre to define specific metrics, layout, and what \\\"at a glance\\\" means for the station\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T21:26:12.356009+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"monkey\",\n        \"details\": \"Moved back to Backlog with clarified scope: enhance existing Dashboard, not a new page\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T21:43:06.854914+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog \\u2014 140min stale with no progress. Picked up in previous session but not completed.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"ts\": \"2026-06-03T22:13:12.903727+00:00\",\n        \"action\": \"reassigned\",\n        \"actor\": \"heartbeat\",\n        \"details\": \"Reset from in_progress to backlog \\u2014 30min stale with no progress. Sub-agent never started.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"dispatchCount\": 0,\n    \"lastActivity\": \"2026-06-03T22:13:12.903727+00:00\",\n    \"currentStep\": null,\n    \"progress\": 0\n  }\n]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780525757606}}
{"type":"message","id":"94ed4624","parentId":"5c48e338","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:29:24.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Current state: **2 backlog** (Incident Response Atmosphere is now done), 0 in_progress, 0 triage. The stale task from before has been cleaned up. Let me update the task and do the room pulse effect to finish Incident Response Atmosphere properly, then update the summary.\n\nLet me read the StationFloorplan to find the exact room rendering section:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"6def0c51-a774-4f40-86e9-f2177ab9b698","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":50,"offset":100,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationFloorplan.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 50, \"offset\": 100, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationFloorplan.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":2518,"output":130,"cacheRead":20864,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":23512,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780525757616,"responseId":"gen-1780525757-3dix9DIIMaYhZg0ymorC"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb50de40","parentId":"94ed4624","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:29:24.933Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"6def0c51-a774-4f40-86e9-f2177ab9b698","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    \"oklch(0.78 0.14 200 / 0.9)\",\n    \"oklch(0.62 0.22 295 / 0.9)\",\n    \"oklch(0.85 0.18 90 / 0.8)\",\n    \"oklch(0.78 0.18 350 / 0.85)\",\n  ];\n  const drones: Drone[] = [];\n  let id = 0;\n  for (let i = 0; i < 6; i++) {\n    drones.push({\n      id: id++, axis: i % 2 === 0 ? \"h\" : \"v\",\n      offset: (Math.random() - 0.5) * 1.6,\n      duration: 7 + Math.random() * 6, delay: Math.random() * 8,\n      reverse: Math.random() > 0.5, color: colors[id % colors.length],\n      size: 3 + Math.floor(Math.random() * 2),\n    });\n  }\n  return drones;\n}\n\nfunction DroneLayer() {\n  const [drones, setDrones] = useState<Drone[]>([]);\n  const gen = useRef(false);\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (gen.current) return;\n    gen.current = true;\n    setDrones(generateDrones());\n  }, []);\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 z-[16] overflow-hidden\">\n      {drones.map(d => {\n        const isH = d.axis === \"h\";\n        const start = d.reverse ? \"110%\" : \"-10%\";\n        const end   = d.reverse ? \"-10%\" : \"110%\";\n        return (\n          <motion.div key={d.id} className=\"absolute rounded-full\"\n            style={{\n              width: d.size, height: d.size,\n              backgroundColor: d.color, boxShadow: `0 0 6px ${d.color}`,\n              [isH ? \"top\" : \"left\"]: `calc(50% + ${d.offset}px)`,\n              [isH ? \"left\" : \"top\"]: start,\n            }}\n            animate={{ [isH ? \"left\" : \"top\"]: [start, end] }}\n            transition={{ duration: d.duration, delay: d.delay, repeat: Infinity, repeatDelay: 2 + Math.random() * 4, ease: \"linear\" }}\n          />\n        );\n      })}\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n\n[143 more lines in file. Use offset=150 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780525764932}}
{"type":"message","id":"837ec864","parentId":"fb50de40","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:29:29.008Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"a753fee1-1515-42a1-9dba-880c723aee0b","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":80,"offset":150,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationFloorplan.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 80, \"offset\": 150, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationFloorplan.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":795,"output":55,"cacheRead":23296,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":24146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780525764944,"responseId":"gen-1780525765-weg4squdVs3f3n9bFSIM"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d41a6515","parentId":"837ec864","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:29:29.057Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"a753fee1-1515-42a1-9dba-880c723aee0b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n// ── L-shaped path ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfunction pathPoints(from: RoomId, to: RoomId): Array<{ x: number; y: number }> {\n  const a = ROOM_CENTERS[from];\n  const b = ROOM_CENTERS[to];\n  return [a, { x: a.x, y: 50 }, HUB, { x: b.x, y: 50 }, b];\n}\n\n// ── Crew visit orchestrator ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// Bug 1 fix: reports visiting agentId up via onVisitorChange so the home room\n// can suppress its static in-room sprite while the agent is shown walking/staying here.\ninterface CrewVisitsProps {\n  active: boolean;\n  onVisitorChange: (agentId: string | null) => void;\n}\n\nfunction CrewVisits({ active, onVisitorChange }: CrewVisitsProps) {\n  const [visitor, setVisitor] = useState<VisitorState | null>(null);\n\n  // Stable ref so the effect never re-runs just because the callback identity changed.\n  // Re-running the effect would trigger the cleanup which calls onVisitorChange(null),\n  // immediately resetting isAway=false and creating a duplicate sprite.\n  const cbRef = useRef(onVisitorChange);\n  useEffect(() => { cbRef.current = onVisitorChange; });\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!active) return;\n    let cancelled = false;\n\n    const scheduleNext = (delay: number) => {\n      const t = setTimeout(() => {\n        if (cancelled) return;\n        const ids = Object.keys(AGENT_HOME);\n        const agentId = ids[Math.floor(Math.random() * ids.length)];\n        const from = AGENT_HOME[agentId];\n        const others = ROOM_KEYS.filter(r => r !== from);\n        const to = others[Math.floor(Math.random() * others.length)];\n        const id = `${agentId}-${Date.now()}`;\n\n        setVisitor({ id, agentId, from, to, phase: \"outbound\" });\n        cbRef.current(agentId); // hide home-room sprite for entire visit duration\n\n        // outbound (2.4s walk) → stay (3.5s) → return (2.4s walk) → cleanup\n        setTimeout(() => {\n          if (!cancelled) setVisitor(v => v?.id === id ? { ...v, phase: \"stay\" } : v);\n        }, 2400);\n        setTimeout(() => {\n          if (!cancelled) setVisitor(v => v?.id === id ? { ...v, phase: \"return\" } : v);\n        }, 2400 + 3500);\n        setTimeout(() => {\n          if (cancelled) return;\n          setVisitor(v => v?.id === id ? null : v);\n          cbRef.current(null); // restore home-room sprite only after walk-back completes\n          scheduleNext(12000 + Math.random() * 12000);\n        }, 2400 + 3500 + 2400 + 200);\n      }, delay);\n      return t;\n    };\n\n    const initial = scheduleNext(4000 + Math.random() * 4000);\n    const onVis = () => {\n      if (document.hidden) {\n        cancelled = true;\n        setVisitor(null);\n        cbRef.current(null);\n      }\n    };\n    document.addEventListener(\"visibilitychange\", onVis);\n\n    return () => {\n      cancelled = true;\n      clearTimeout(initial);\n      // Note: do NOT call cbRef.current(null) here — cleanup fires whenever\n      // the parent re-renders (changing callback identity), which would reset\n      // isAway prematurely. Instead, the visit completion timeout is the sole\n      // owner of the isAway=false transition.\n      document.removeEventListener(\"visibilitychange\", onVis);\n    };\n  }, [active]); // ← only re-run when visits are toggled on/off, never on callback change\n\n\n[63 more lines in file. Use offset=230 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780525769057}}
{"type":"message","id":"a7f9d17e","parentId":"d41a6515","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:29:33.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"ea3629c7-595d-4567-9cd6-33c4da8f0fe2","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":65,"offset":230,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationFloorplan.tsx"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 65, \"offset\": 230, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/StationFloorplan.tsx\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":961,"output":55,"cacheRead":24064,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":25080,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780525769069,"responseId":"gen-1780525769-jpwDM1O5Kqv1gxVF0WHZ"}}
{"type":"message","id":"89ea60e9","parentId":"a7f9d17e","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:29:33.223Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ea3629c7-595d-4567-9cd6-33c4da8f0fe2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"  if (!visitor) return null;\n\n  const outboundPath = pathPoints(visitor.from, visitor.to);\n  const returnPath   = [...outboundPath].reverse();\n  const path = visitor.phase === \"return\" ? returnPath : outboundPath;\n  const dest = visitor.phase === \"stay\" ? ROOM_CENTERS[visitor.to] : null;\n\n  if (dest) {\n    return (\n      <motion.div key={`${visitor.id}-stay`}\n        className=\"pointer-events-none absolute z-[18]\"\n        initial={false}\n        style={{ left: `${dest.x}%`, top: `${dest.y}%`, x: \"-50%\", y: \"-50%\" }}>\n        <div className=\"agent-idle\">\n          <CrewSprite agentId={visitor.agentId} pose=\"idle\" displayWidth={96} displayHeight={72} />\n        </div>\n        <div className=\"absolute left-1/2 top-full -translate-x-1/2 mt-0.5 whitespace-nowrap rounded bg-background/70 px-1 py-[1px] font-mono text-[7px] tracking-wider text-cyan-accent\">VISITING</div>\n      </motion.div>\n    );\n  }\n\n  return (\n    <motion.div key={`${visitor.id}-${visitor.phase}`}\n      className=\"pointer-events-none absolute z-[18]\"\n      style={{ left: `${path[0].x}%`, top: `${path[0].y}%`, x: \"-50%\", y: \"-50%\" }}\n      animate={{ left: path.map(p => `${p.x}%`), top: path.map(p => `${p.y}%`) }}\n      transition={{ duration: 2.4, ease: \"easeInOut\", times: [0, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 1] }}>\n      <div className=\"agent-walking\">\n        <CrewSprite agentId={visitor.agentId} pose=\"walk\" displayWidth={96} displayHeight={72} />\n      </div>\n      <div className=\"absolute left-1/2 -top-3 -translate-x-1/2 whitespace-nowrap rounded bg-background/70 px-1 py-[1px] font-mono text-[7px] tracking-wider text-cyan-accent\">EN ROUTE</div>\n    </motion.div>\n  );\n}\n\n// ── StationFloorplan wrapper ────────────────────────────────────────────────\nexport function StationFloorplan({\n  children,\n  enableVisits = true,\n  onVisitingAgentChange,\n}: {\n  children: ReactNode;\n  enableVisits?: boolean;\n  onVisitingAgentChange?: (agentId: string | null) => void;\n}) {\n  // useCallback keeps identity stable so CrewVisits' cbRef sync is a no-op re-render,\n  // and never accidentally re-triggers the visits effect.\n  const handleVisitorChange = useCallback((agentId: string | null) => {\n    onVisitingAgentChange?.(agentId);\n  }, [onVisitingAgentChange]);\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"relative\">\n      <div className=\"relative grid grid-cols-2 gap-[2px] rounded-lg overflow-hidden bg-[oklch(0.10_0.03_265)]\">\n        {children}\n      </div>\n      <HallwayOverlay />\n      <DroneLayer />\n      <CrewVisits active={enableVisits} onVisitorChange={handleVisitorChange} />\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780525773223}}
{"type":"message","id":"2183cda0","parentId":"89ea60e9","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:30:02.223Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I see the full picture. The StationFloorplan renders children in a 2x2 grid, then overlays HallwayOverlay, DroneLayer, and CrewVisits. I need to add an `activeIncidentRooms` prop and render a pulsing glow overlay on those rooms.\n\nThe rooms are rendered as `children` in a CSS grid. I can add an overlay div that positions absolutely over the grid cells. Let me implement this:"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":877,"output":1066,"cacheRead":24960,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":26903,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780525773233,"responseId":"gen-1780525773-81dDlkQYilUcZi9v8x8a"}}
