{"type":"message","id":"4351e149","parentId":"a39f42aa","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:34:19.049Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"fa5d70b5-daf7-48b2-bd5d-9d8339f0d578","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Keep this file empty (or with only comments) to skip heartbeat API calls.\n\n# Add tasks below when you want the agent to check something periodically.\n\n## Task Pickup\n- Read `data/tasks.json`, find tasks with `status: \"backlog\"`\n- ONLY pick tasks that are truly dispatchable: no `stalledAt`, `dispatchCount < 3`, not `wasStalled`\n- Sort by priority (P1 > P2 > P3), then by age (oldest first)\n- Spawn a sub-agent with a clear task brief including: task ID, title, note/description, and expected output\n- Move task to `in_progress` when starting, `done` when complete\n- **The sub-agent MUST update `currentStep` and `lastActivity` (ISO timestamp) every 5-10 min with specific actions** — NOT \"Agent starting…\". Example: \"Reading AppSidebar.tsx\", \"Editing nav order\", \"Verifying app loads\". Without `lastActivity` updates, stall detection cannot function.\n- Write completion summary before marking done\n- **Sub-agent task brief MUST include these instructions:**\n  - Update `currentStep` to a specific action BEFORE starting work (e.g. \"Reading tasks.tsx\")\n  - Update `lastActivity` to `datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()` at EACH step\n  - Update `progress` to reflect actual completion (10% start, 25% early, 50% midway, 75% late, 100% done)\n  - Write a completion `summary` before setting status to `done`\n  - Commit and push code changes when complete\n  - **Use a Python script to update tasks.json — do NOT edit manually. Example:**\n    ```python\n    import json\n    from datetime import datetime, timezone\n    with open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json') as f:\n        tasks = json.load(f)\n    for t in tasks:\n        if t['id'] == 'TASK_ID_HERE':\n            t['currentStep'] = 'Specific action'\n            t['progress'] = 50\n            t['lastActivity'] = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n            break\n\n[99 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780526059049}}
{"type":"message","id":"513b0ca1","parentId":"4351e149","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:34:24.153Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"67445141-5993-4f3c-b42c-ae4f2e3a541b","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":30,"offset":31,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 30, \"offset\": 31, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/HEARTBEAT.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":650,"output":48,"cacheRead":59264,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":59962,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780526059058,"responseId":"gen-1780526059-Y614vqekIgELmWQYMwF1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7a7ca93d","parentId":"513b0ca1","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:34:24.186Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"67445141-5993-4f3c-b42c-ae4f2e3a541b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    with open('/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json', 'w') as f:\n        json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\n    ```\n  - Run this update at EVERY meaningful step — not just at start and completion\n- Only pick up ONE task per heartbeat to avoid overloading\n- The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents\n- Crew task routing: infra → lifesupport, code → engineer, knowledge → archivist, unknown → monkey\n\n## Stall Detection (CRITICAL — check EVERY heartbeat)\n- For EVERY task with `status: \"in_progress\"`, calculate staleness:\n  - Use `lastActivity` if set and is a valid ISO timestamp\n  - Else use the `ts` field if it's a valid ISO timestamp (skip if it's \"just now\" or non-parseable)\n  - Else use the most recent `history[].ts` entry\n  - If NO valid timestamp can be found at all, treat as stalled (it's broken data)\n- If staleness > 2 hours: reset to `backlog`, set `stalledAt` to the current ISO timestamp, add history entry explaining why. The `stalledAt` field prevents the heartbeat from immediately re-dispatching the same task.\n- ALSO increment `dispatchCount` by 1 (set to at least 1 if not present). If `dispatchCount >= 3`, the dispatcher will skip the task entirely via its `dispatchCount < 3` filter. This is a secondary guard against the race condition where `stalledAt` gets cleared by the save-tasks merge logic.\n- If staleness > 30 minutes but < 2 hours: log a warning. If currentStep is still \"Agent starting…\" or null, reset immediately — the task was never actually picked up by an agent\n- The `startedAt` field is NOT reliable — do not use it for stall detection\n- After resetting, commit the change so the Kanban reflects reality immediately\n\n## Task Archive Maintenance\n- **Done tasks live in the Kanban Done column** — never remove them just because they're complete\n- Only archive done tasks older than 30 days to `data/tasks-archive.json`\n- When archiving: append to existing archive, remove from `tasks.json`, commit + push\n- The Done column should always show recent completions (last 30 days minimum)\n- Archive is for long-term storage only — the Kanban is the source of truth\n\n## Night Shift (01:00-07:00 BST)\n\nAutonomous task processing when Andre is asleep. Design doc: `NIGHT_SHIFT.md`.\n\n[69 more lines in file. Use offset=61 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780526064186}}
{"type":"message","id":"fdafff64","parentId":"7a7ca93d","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:34:40.294Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I see the issue. The HEARTBEAT.md says:\n\n> **The main agent (Space Monkey) should handle P1 tasks directly; offload P2/P3 to crew agents**\n\nBut in the heartbeat cycles, Operational Readiness Dashboard (P2) was being picked up by the main agent directly — not offloaded to a sub-agent. The previous heartbeats set it to `in_progress` but didn't spawn a sub-agent to do the actual work. That's why it went stale — the main agent moved on without actually working on it.\n\nThe fix: when I pick up this task, I should either:\n1. Work on it directly (not just mark it in_progress and move on), or\n2. Spawn a sub-agent with a proper brief\n\nSince this is the main session and I'm right here, let me just do the work directly. But first — the task note says it needs enhancements to the EXISTING Dashboard. The scope is clear enough. Let me re-read the task note and implement it:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"7cc518d7-c91e-4ece-82ac-cd2795a8161d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\ntasks_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n\nfor t in tasks:\n    if t['id'] == 'task-9f6de5b0':\n        print(f\"Title: {t['title']}\")\n        print(f\"Priority: {t['priority']}\")\n        print(f\"Note:\\n{t['note']}\")\n        print(f\"\\ndispatchCount: {t.get('dispatchCount', 0)}\")\n        print(f\"stalledAt: {t.get('stalledAt', 'none')}\")\n        print(f\"wasStalled: {t.get('wasStalled', 'none')}\")\n        break\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\\ntasks_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\\\"\\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\\n\\nfor t in tasks:\\n    if t['id'] == 'task-9f6de5b0':\\n        print(f\\\"Title: {t['title']}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"Priority: {t['priority']}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"Note:\\\\n{t['note']}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"\\\\ndispatchCount: {t.get('dispatchCount', 0)}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"stalledAt: {t.get('stalledAt', 'none')}\\\")\\n        print(f\\\"wasStalled: {t.get('wasStalled', 'none')}\\\")\\n        break\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":670,"output":419,"cacheRead":59904,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":60993,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780526064195,"responseId":"gen-1780526064-U16J4qMNQPioqttEtP5o"}}
