{"type":"message","id":"bb36cd87","parentId":"b65f3cbd","timestamp":"2026-06-03T22:42:52.445Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Backlog is clear. Good work on the Operations Engine.\n\nOne thing: the Unified Event Model + Incident Events task — was this \nmerged and moved back to Backlog as instructed? I don't see it in the \ncompleted or backlog lists. Check if it's still in Triage or if it \nwas accidentally skipped.\n\nAlso: the \"stale task\" bug where the main agent marks tasks in_progress \nbut doesn't spawn a sub-agent or do the work — this happened multiple \ntimes. Add a rule to HEARTBEAT.md: \"If you pick up a task, you MUST \neither work on it directly in this session or spawn a sub-agent. Never \nmark a task in_progress and then walk away.\"\n\nFor now: the board is clear. Station is stable. Good session.","timestamp":1780526555013,"idempotencyKey":"ac002a7c-9268-4e56-98eb-f05e49b8e0b8:user"}}
