{"type":"message","id":"7d2e54d1","parentId":"733cf713","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:13:37.749Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"The Incidents page shows 37 incidents in TRIAGE, 2 in MITIGATING, \nand only 3 RESOLVED. Most of these are likely old incidents from \ndays or weeks ago that should have been resolved by now.\n\nThis is the sync problem OPS-002 (Incident → Task Linking) was \nsupposed to fix. When a linked task moves to Done, the incident \nshould auto-resolve. Clearly this isn't happening.\n\nInvestigate:\n1. Do the 37 TRIAGE incidents have linked tasks? Check a few.\n2. If the linked tasks are already Done, why didn't the incident \n   auto-resolve?\n3. Is the auto-resolution logic actually running? Check the code \n   path: task status change → check linkedIncidentId → update \n   incident status\n4. For the 2 MITIGATING incidents — are they actively being worked \n   on, or are they abandoned like the TRIAGE ones?\n\nFix:\n1. If linked tasks are Done, bulk-resolve those incidents\n2. If incidents have no linked tasks and are old (5+ days), bulk-close them\n3. Verify auto-resolution works for future incidents\n4. The Incidents page should reflect reality — not a graveyard of \n   forgotten TRIAGE items","timestamp":1780528400347,"idempotencyKey":"526cf179-e391-4d17-a6a6-d367a43d160c:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"94b34081","parentId":"7d2e54d1","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:14:02.966Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me investigate this systematically. First, check the incidents data and their linked tasks:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"57667ba8-1fd1-4fd2-ac35-08c57d1ea33b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\n\nincidents_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/incidents.json\"\nwith open(incidents_file) as f:\n    incidents = json.load(f)\n\ntasks_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\n\n# Count by status\nfrom collections import Counter\nstatus_counts = Counter(i['status'] for i in incidents)\nprint(\"=== Incident Status Counts ===\")\nfor s, c in sorted(status_counts.items()):\n    print(f\"  {s}: {c}\")\n\n# Check TRIAGE incidents\ntriage = [i for i in incidents if i['status'] == 'TRIAGE']\nprint(f\"\\n=== TRIAGE Incidents ({len(triage)}) ===\")\nfor i in triage[:10]:\n    age_days = 0\n    try:\n        ts = datetime.fromisoformat(i['opened'].replace('Z', '+00:00'))\n        age_days = (now - ts).days\n    except:\n        pass\n    linked_task_id = i.get('linkedTaskId') or i.get('linkedTaskIds', [])\n    print(f\"  {i['id']}: {i['title'][:50]} | age: {age_days}d | linked: {linked_task_id} | severity: {i.get('severity','?')}\")\n\n# Check MITIGATING incidents\nmitigating = [i for i in incidents if i['status'] == 'MITIGATING']\nprint(f\"\\n=== MITIGATING Incidents ({len(mitigating)}) ===\")\nfor i in mitigating:\n    age_days = 0\n    try:\n        ts = datetime.fromisoformat(i['opened'].replace('Z', '+00:00'))\n        age_days = (now - ts).days\n    except:\n        pass\n    linked_task_id = i.get('linkedTaskId') or i.get('linkedTaskIds', [])\n    print(f\"  {i['id']}: {i['title'][:50]} | age: {age_days}d | linked: {linked_task_id}\")\n\n# Check if any tasks reference these incidents\nprint(f\"\\n=== Tasks with linkedIncidentId ===\")\nlinked_tasks = [t for t in tasks if t.get('linkedIncidentId')]\nprint(f\"  {len(linked_tasks)} tasks have linkedIncidentId\")\nfor t in linked_tasks:\n    print(f\"  {t['id']}: {t['title'][:50]} → {t['linkedIncidentId']} (status: {t['status']})\")\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\\n\\nincidents_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/incidents.json\\\"\\nwith open(incidents_file) as f:\\n    incidents = json.load(f)\\n\\ntasks_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\\\"\\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\nnow = datetime.now(timezone.utc)\\n\\n# Count by status\\nfrom collections import Counter\\nstatus_counts = Counter(i['status'] for i in incidents)\\nprint(\\\"=== Incident Status Counts ===\\\")\\nfor s, c in sorted(status_counts.items()):\\n    print(f\\\"  {s}: {c}\\\")\\n\\n# Check TRIAGE incidents\\ntriage = [i for i in incidents if i['status'] == 'TRIAGE']\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n=== TRIAGE Incidents ({len(triage)}) ===\\\")\\nfor i in triage[:10]:\\n    age_days = 0\\n    try:\\n        ts = datetime.fromisoformat(i['opened'].replace('Z', '+00:00'))\\n        age_days = (now - ts).days\\n    except:\\n        pass\\n    linked_task_id = i.get('linkedTaskId') or i.get('linkedTaskIds', [])\\n    print(f\\\"  {i['id']}: {i['title'][:50]} | age: {age_days}d | linked: {linked_task_id} | severity: {i.get('severity','?')}\\\")\\n\\n# Check MITIGATING incidents\\nmitigating = [i for i in incidents if i['status'] == 'MITIGATING']\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n=== MITIGATING Incidents ({len(mitigating)}) ===\\\")\\nfor i in mitigating:\\n    age_days = 0\\n    try:\\n        ts = datetime.fromisoformat(i['opened'].replace('Z', '+00:00'))\\n        age_days = (now - ts).days\\n    except:\\n        pass\\n    linked_task_id = i.get('linkedTaskId') or i.get('linkedTaskIds', [])\\n    print(f\\\"  {i['id']}: {i['title'][:50]} | age: {age_days}d | linked: {linked_task_id}\\\")\\n\\n# Check if any tasks reference these incidents\\nprint(f\\\"\\\\n=== Tasks with linkedIncidentId ===\\\")\\nlinked_tasks = [t for t in tasks if t.get('linkedIncidentId')]\\nprint(f\\\"  {len(linked_tasks)} tasks have linkedIncidentId\\\")\\nfor t in linked_tasks:\\n    print(f\\\"  {t['id']}: {t['title'][:50]} → {t['linkedIncidentId']} (status: {t['status']})\\\")\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":66181,"output":613,"cacheRead":10240,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":77034,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780528417760,"responseId":"gen-1780528417-cf2akO3mdujTIKH2TH0e"}}
