{"type":"message","id":"78aed1e6","parentId":"e9aba53b","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:19:21.621Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** OPS-002 auto-resolution was never implemented. The auto-detect script creates incidents with linked tasks, but when those tasks move to `done`, nothing told the incident to resolve. The `incidents-timeline` endpoint only appended timeline entries — it never checked task status.\n\n**What was fixed:**\n1. **`incidents-timeline.tsx`** — added auto-resolution: when `taskStatus === \"done\"` is sent alongside a timeline entry, the incident is automatically resolved\n2. **New `/api/incidents/auto-resolve` endpoint** — bulk resolve/close stale incidents: scans all open incidents, resolves those with done linked tasks, closes those with no linked tasks and age ≥ 5 days\n\n**Cleanup results:**\n- **39 RESOLVED** (was 3 → +36)\n- **3 TRIAGE remaining** — all genuinely new (< 5 days), no linked tasks yet:\n  - INC-039: P1 gateway crash-loop (2d old)\n  - INC-038: P3 stale tasks (2d old)\n  - INC-036: P2 rate limit exhaustion (3d old)\n- **2 abandoned MITIGATING** (INC-001, INC-004) — closed, were 999-day-old stale items\n\nThe 3 remaining TRIAGE incidents are current issues that the auto-detect script will continue monitoring. When their linked tasks (once created) are resolved, the incidents will auto-resolve via the new logic."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":242,"output":333,"cacheRead":93952,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":94527,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780528746057,"responseId":"gen-1780528746-LKa8rCfHPgjELbSxlTZT"}}
{"type":"message","id":"faa06799","parentId":"78aed1e6","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:20:20.986Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Good work on the incident cleanup. The Incidents page now reflects \nreality — 3 current issues, not 39 ghosts.\n\nOne thing to verify: the 3 remaining TRIAGE incidents (INC-036, \nINC-038, INC-039) — the auto-detect script should create linked \ntasks for them. Check if those tasks exist. If not, the script that \ncreates incidents isn't creating tasks, which means the auto-resolution \nwon't work for future incidents either.\n\nAlso: add a cron or heartbeat check that runs the auto-resolve endpoint \ndaily so we never accumulate 37 stale incidents again.\n\nThen the board is clean and we can move forward.","timestamp":1780528820839,"idempotencyKey":"c6a7a8ec-e1e9-4b01-8805-e87878c9f355:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5682a205","parentId":"faa06799","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:20:37.495Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me verify the linked tasks and set up the auto-resolve cron."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"efe90f23-519b-420e-93fe-3df7a5fb5a3d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\n\ntasks_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\"\narchive_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks-archive.json\"\n\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\n    tasks = json.load(f)\n\nimport os\narchive = []\nif os.path.exists(archive_file):\n    with open(archive_file) as f:\n        archive = json.load(f)\n\nall_tasks = tasks + archive\n\n# Check for linked tasks for the 3 remaining incidents\nfor inc_id in ['INC-039', 'INC-038', 'INC-036']:\n    linked = [t for t in all_tasks if t.get('linkedIncidentId') == inc_id]\n    if linked:\n        for t in linked:\n            print(f\"{inc_id} → {t['id']}: \\\"{t['title'][:50]}\\\" (status: {t['status']})\")\n    else:\n        print(f\"{inc_id} → NO LINKED TASK FOUND\")\n\n# Also check: do ALL open incidents have linked tasks?\nprint(\"\\n=== All tasks with linkedIncidentId ===\")\nlinked_tasks = [t for t in all_tasks if t.get('linkedIncidentId')]\nprint(f\"Total: {len(linked_tasks)}\")\nfor t in linked_tasks:\n    print(f\"  {t['linkedIncidentId']} ← {t['id']}: \\\"{t['title'][:45]}\\\" ({t['status']})\")\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\n\\ntasks_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks.json\\\"\\narchive_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks-archive.json\\\"\\n\\nwith open(tasks_file) as f:\\n    tasks = json.load(f)\\n\\nimport os\\narchive = []\\nif os.path.exists(archive_file):\\n    with open(archive_file) as f:\\n        archive = json.load(f)\\n\\nall_tasks = tasks + archive\\n\\n# Check for linked tasks for the 3 remaining incidents\\nfor inc_id in ['INC-039', 'INC-038', 'INC-036']:\\n    linked = [t for t in all_tasks if t.get('linkedIncidentId') == inc_id]\\n    if linked:\\n        for t in linked:\\n            print(f\\\"{inc_id} → {t['id']}: \\\\\\\"{t['title'][:50]}\\\\\\\" (status: {t['status']})\\\")\\n    else:\\n        print(f\\\"{inc_id} → NO LINKED TASK FOUND\\\")\\n\\n# Also check: do ALL open incidents have linked tasks?\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n=== All tasks with linkedIncidentId ===\\\")\\nlinked_tasks = [t for t in all_tasks if t.get('linkedIncidentId')]\\nprint(f\\\"Total: {len(linked_tasks)}\\\")\\nfor t in linked_tasks:\\n    print(f\\\"  {t['linkedIncidentId']} ← {t['id']}: \\\\\\\"{t['title'][:45]}\\\\\\\" ({t['status']})\\\")\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":18654,"output":363,"cacheRead":76032,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":95049,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780528820994,"responseId":"gen-1780528821-pVf7vNgf5pBaEqB8hqr3"}}
