{"type":"message","id":"e5cc8712","parentId":"5ef970db","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:20:47.553Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"As suspected — the 3 remaining TRIAGE incidents have **no linked tasks**. The auto-detect script's deduplication logic is preventing task creation because these incidents already exist (same title + source tag match). Let me check:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"098fd4ca-e6be-46b2-a7b7-35b49d38bc93","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\n\nincidents_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/incidents.json\"\nwith open(incidents_file) as f:\n    incidents = json.load(f)\n\nfor inc_id in ['INC-039', 'INC-038', 'INC-036']:\n    inc = next(i for i in incidents if i['id'] == inc_id)\n    print(f\"{inc_id}:\")\n    print(f\"  title: {inc['title']}\")\n    print(f\"  tags: {inc.get('tags', [])}\")\n    print(f\"  status: {inc['status']}\")\n    print()\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json\\n\\nincidents_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/incidents.json\\\"\\nwith open(incidents_file) as f:\\n    incidents = json.load(f)\\n\\nfor inc_id in ['INC-039', 'INC-038', 'INC-036']:\\n    inc = next(i for i in incidents if i['id'] == inc_id)\\n    print(f\\\"{inc_id}:\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"  title: {inc['title']}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"  tags: {inc.get('tags', [])}\\\")\\n    print(f\\\"  status: {inc['status']}\\\")\\n    print()\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":619,"output":216,"cacheRead":94592,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":95427,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780528837597,"responseId":"gen-1780528837-6VMMrJhZqcPBp6pT9UdG"}}
{"type":"message","id":"103cb820","parentId":"e5cc8712","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:20:47.626Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"098fd4ca-e6be-46b2-a7b7-35b49d38bc93","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"INC-039:\n  title: Gateway session errors — 3 session(s) with EmbeddedAttemptSessionTakeoverError\n  tags: ['gateway', 'crash-loop', 'session-takeover', 'gateway-monitor']\n  status: TRIAGE\n\nINC-038:\n  title: Tasks stuck In Progress — 3 tasks with no recent activity\n  tags: ['tasks', 'stale', 'in-progress', 'task-monitor']\n  status: TRIAGE\n\nINC-036:\n  title: Rate limit exhaustion — 11 429 errors in gateway log\n  tags: ['rate-limit', '429', 'models', 'rate-monitor']\n  status: TRIAGE"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":40,"aggregated":"INC-039:\n  title: Gateway session errors — 3 session(s) with EmbeddedAttemptSessionTakeoverError\n  tags: ['gateway', 'crash-loop', 'session-takeover', 'gateway-monitor']\n  status: TRIAGE\n\nINC-038:\n  title: Tasks stuck In Progress — 3 tasks with no recent activity\n  tags: ['tasks', 'stale', 'in-progress', 'task-monitor']\n  status: TRIAGE\n\nINC-036:\n  title: Rate limit exhaustion — 11 429 errors in gateway log\n  tags: ['rate-limit', '429', 'models', 'rate-monitor']\n  status: TRIAGE","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780528847626}}
{"type":"message","id":"226609ba","parentId":"103cb820","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:20:59.401Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The auto-detect script deduplicates by checking if an active (non-RESOLVED) incident with the same title + source tag already exists. Since these 3 are still TRIAGE, the script sees them as duplicates and skips task creation. This is actually correct behavior — it means the conditions that triggered them are still present, and the incidents are legitimately open.\n\nThe problem is that these incidents were **created without linked tasks in the first place**. Let me check the auto-detect script's `create_incident` function more carefully:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"96f47126-71e8-4069-8b94-fd980696ede0","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":30,"offset":80,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/auto-detect-incidents.sh"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 30, \"offset\": 80, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/auto-detect-incidents.sh\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":489,"output":161,"cacheRead":95104,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":95754,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780528847635,"responseId":"gen-1780528847-8TTgxCJEm0HURaish1mZ"}}
{"type":"message","id":"32a0ff49","parentId":"226609ba","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:20:59.436Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"96f47126-71e8-4069-8b94-fd980696ede0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"incidents.insert(0, inc)\nwith open(incidents_path, \"w\") as f:\n    json.dump(incidents, f, indent=2)\n\n# Create linked task in tasks.json\ntry:\n    tasks = json.load(open(tasks_path)) if os.path.exists(tasks_path) else []\n    task_id = f\"task-{next_id.lower()}-{os.urandom(2).hex()}\"\n    task = {\n        \"id\": task_id,\n        \"title\": f\"Investigate: {next_id}\",\n        \"assignee\": \"$owner\",\n        \"status\": \"triage\",\n        \"priority\": \"$severity\",\n        \"ts\": \"just now\",\n        \"note\": f\"Auto-created from incident {next_id}: $summary\",\n        \"linkedIncidentId\": next_id,\n        \"tags\": [\"incident-response\"] + ${tags},\n        \"history\": [{\"ts\": now, \"action\": \"created\", \"actor\": \"system\", \"details\": f\"Auto-created from incident {next_id}\"}],\n        \"lastActivity\": now\n    }\n    tasks.insert(0, task)\n    with open(tasks_path, \"w\") as f:\n        json.dump(tasks, f, indent=2)\n    print(f\"{next_id}|{task_id}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(next_id)\n    print(f\"task_create_error: {e}\", file=__import__(\"sys\").stderr)\nPYEOF\n}\n\n[174 more lines in file. Use offset=110 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780528859436}}
{"type":"message","id":"829bacc2","parentId":"32a0ff49","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:21:13.112Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The script does create tasks. But the deduplication check at the top of `create_incident` exits early if an active incident with the same title + source exists:\n\n```python\nfor i in incidents:\n    if i[\"status\"] != \"RESOLVED\" and i[\"title\"] == \"$title\" and \"$source\" in i.get(\"tags\", []):\n        print(\"duplicate\")\n        exit(0)\n```\n\nSo the 3 remaining incidents were created with tasks initially, but those tasks got cleaned up when we bulk-resolved the old incidents. Wait — no. These 3 incidents are NEW (2-3 days old) and were never resolved. Let me check if their tasks exist in the archive:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"b33eb4c3-b8b9-43ca-ae13-ae8e32199cb9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json, os\n\narchive_file = \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks-archive.json\"\nif os.path.exists(archive_file):\n    with open(archive_file) as f:\n        archive = json.load(f)\n    for inc_id in ['INC-039', 'INC-038', 'INC-036']:\n        linked = [t for t in archive if t.get('linkedIncidentId') == inc_id]\n        if linked:\n            for t in linked:\n                print(f\"{inc_id} → ARCHIVED: {t['id']}: \\\"{t['title'][:50]}\\\" (status: {t['status']})\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"{inc_id} → NOT in archive either\")\nelse:\n    print(\"No archive file\")\nPYEOF","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 << 'PYEOF'\\nimport json, os\\n\\narchive_file = \\\"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/data/tasks-archive.json\\\"\\nif os.path.exists(archive_file):\\n    with open(archive_file) as f:\\n        archive = json.load(f)\\n    for inc_id in ['INC-039', 'INC-038', 'INC-036']:\\n        linked = [t for t in archive if t.get('linkedIncidentId') == inc_id]\\n        if linked:\\n            for t in linked:\\n                print(f\\\"{inc_id} → ARCHIVED: {t['id']}: \\\\\\\"{t['title'][:50]}\\\\\\\" (status: {t['status']})\\\")\\n        else:\\n            print(f\\\"{inc_id} → NOT in archive either\\\")\\nelse:\\n    print(\\\"No archive file\\\")\\nPYEOF\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":603,"output":350,"cacheRead":95488,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":96441,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780528859448,"responseId":"gen-1780528859-Sw9lOYpMrINPiD2S9wAQ"}}
