{"type":"message","id":"2d98f579","parentId":"3689e386","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:50:05.102Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"That's a draft. Let me populate it properly as the first review package:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"b7cd65f3-5b6d-4df3-b2d9-7b2ad1a10daa","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/review-system/pending/REV-2026-06-04-001.md","content":"---\nreview_id: REV-2026-06-04-001\nproject: Mission Control Dashboard\ncreated: 2026-06-04T00:48:00+01:00\npriority: P2\nstatus: pending\n---\n\n# Summary\n\nThis review covers the first major operational work session for the Mission Control\nDashboard, completed between 2026-06-02 and 2026-06-04. The work transformed the\nproject from a prototype with a bloated backlog into a clean, operational system with\nautomated incident management.\n\nSix feature areas were delivered, 42 incidents were cleaned up, and multiple systemic\nbugs in the task dispatch and incident lifecycle were fixed.\n\n# Files Changed\n\n### Scheduler Page\n- `src/routes/scheduler.tsx` — Added health summary bar, status dots, degraded/failing filters\n- `src/components/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx` — Added health status dot, retry counter display\n- `src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts` — Existing fields leveraged for health states\n\n### Retry Policy\n- `src/routes/api/retry-policy.tsx` — New endpoint, tracks retry state, auto-creates P2 incident at limit\n\n### Incident Management\n- `src/routes/api/incidents-timeline.tsx` — Added auto-resolution when linked task completes\n- `src/routes/api/incidents-auto-resolve.tsx` — New bulk resolve/close endpoint\n- `src/lib/server-data/tasks.ts` — Added `getBacklogCount` endpoint\n- `scripts/auto-detect-incidents.sh` — Fixed dedup logic to create linked tasks for existing TRIAGE incidents\n\n### Dashboard\n- `src/routes/index.tsx` — Added incidents + tasks data to loader\n- `src/components/Dashboard.tsx` — Station Status Bar, Agent Load Indicators, alert banner\n- `src/components/AppSidebar.tsx` — Backlog count badge with polling\n- `src/components/StationFloorplan.tsx` — Room pulse overlay for active incidents\n\n### Agent Office\n- Existing components: AmbientStation mood tints wired to incident severity\n\n### Task System\n- `HEARTBEAT.md` — Multiple rule fixes (NO GHOST DISPATCHES, exclusion tags, auto-resolve check)\n- `data/tasks.json` — 28+ stale tasks cleaned up, backlog cleared\n- `data/incidents.json` — 39 ghosts resolved, auto-resolution linked\n\n# Decisions Made\n\n### Decision: Health states integrated into existing Scheduler page (not a new page)\nReason: Avoid page bloat. The Scheduler already shows all cron jobs. Adding health\nsummary bar and status dots was zero-cost visually and reused existing data\n(`consecutiveErrors`, `enabled`).\n\n### Decision: Simple retry policy (3 retries + 5min gap, no exponential backoff)\nReason: Phase 1 — get the basics working. Per-job customization and exponential\nbackoff deferred to Phase 5. Global policy is sufficient for now.\n\n### Decision: Incident auto-resolve via `taskStatus` field on timeline endpoint\nReason: The timeline endpoint is already the hook point for task→incident sync.\nAdding `taskStatus` as an optional field means auto-resolution happens naturally\nwithout a separate call. Falls back gracefully if `taskStatus` is not sent.\n\n### Decision: Bulk auto-resolve endpoint separate from real-time resolve\nReason: Two different use cases. Real-time (timeline endpoint) for when tasks complete.\nBulk (auto-resolve endpoint) for cleanup of stale incidents and cron runs. Keeping\nthem apart avoids side effects.\n\n### Decision: Linked tasks created even when TRIAGE incident already exists\nReason: Previous dedup logic skipped everything — including task creation — when it\nfound an existing active incident. This meant repeat detections never got linked tasks,\nbreaking the entire auto-resolution chain.\n\n### Decision: Backlog count badge uses separate polling endpoint\nReason: `getBacklogCount` is lighter than `getTasks`. The sidebar polls every 30s —\nno need to serialize the full task list just for a count.\n\n# Risks Identified\n\n### Risk: `tasks.json` data loss during concurrent writes\nBoth the auto-detect shell script and the MC API write to `tasks.json`. The shell\nscript has no atomic write (no `rename` guard). The API (`saveTasks`) does use\n`tmpPath + rename`. If both write simultaneously, data loss is possible.\nLikelihood: low (30-min cron vs interactive API calls). Impact: medium.\n\n### Risk: Deduplication by title match may merge distinct incidents\nThe auto-detect script deduplicates by exact title + source tag match. If the same\nunderlying issue triggers with different counts (e.g., \"11 429 errors\" vs\n\"26 429 errors\"), they get different titles and are NOT deduplicated. This creates\nmultiple incidents for the same root cause. The 12+ historical rate-limit incidents\nare evidence of this.\n\n### Risk: Client-side task data staleness\nThe Dashboard fetches tasks at page load via the loader. If a task status changes\nvia the heartbeat or API, the Dashboard won't reflect it until next navigation.\nThe sidebar badge polls every 30s but the main page doesn't.\n\n### Risk: `ts` field inconsistency across tasks\nMost tasks use `ts: \"just now\"` (non-parseable), some use ISO timestamps. The\nstallend detection logic has to handle both. This is fragile — a future refactor\nshould enforce ISO timestamps everywhere.\n\n# Known Limitation\n\n- No real-time updates on the Dashboard (requires navigation to refresh task/incident data)\n- No per-job retry configuration (global 3-retry policy only)\n- No exponential backoff on retries\n- Incident dedup is title-exact-match only (no fuzzy grouping)\n- Browser automation for external review not implemented (Phase 1 is framework only)\n- The `/api/incidents/auto-resolve` endpoint exists but is triggered only by\n  cron/heartbeat — no UI button to run it manually\n\n# Proposed Next Steps\n\n1. Validate this review framework with manual review cycle\n2. If review value confirmed: implement Phase 2 (automated external AI review loop)\n3. Fix `tasks.json` atomic write in auto-detect script\n4. Add fuzzy incident grouping (same root cause → single incident)\n5. Add real-time refresh to Dashboard (polling or SSE)\n\n# Questions For Reviewer\n\n1. **Architecture:** Is the two-layer auto-resolution (real-time timeline + bulk cron)\n   the right pattern, or should this be a single mechanism?\n\n2. **Incident lifecycle:** Should rate-limit incidents (all \"429 errors in gateway log\")\n   be grouped into a single rolling incident instead of creating new ones each time?\n\n3. **Data integrity:** Is the `tasks.json` concurrent-write risk acceptable, or should\n   the auto-detect script be converted to use the API exclusively?\n\n4. **Review package quality:** Does this level of detail make for a useful review,\n   or is it too much/too little? What would you want to see in future packages?\n\n5. **Phase 2 approach:** Which integration method (browser / OpenRouter / dedicated API)\n   would you recommend based on the comparison matrix in the review-agent design?\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/review-system/pending/REV-2026-06-04-001.md\", \"content\": \"---\\nreview_id: REV-2026-06-04-001\\nproject: Mission Control Dashboard\\ncreated: 2026-06-04T00:48:00+01:00\\npriority: P2\\nstatus: pending\\n---\\n\\n# Summary\\n\\nThis review covers the first major operational work session for the Mission Control\\nDashboard, completed between 2026-06-02 and 2026-06-04. The work transformed the\\nproject from a prototype with a bloated backlog into a clean, operational system with\\nautomated incident management.\\n\\nSix feature areas were delivered, 42 incidents were cleaned up, and multiple systemic\\nbugs in the task dispatch and incident lifecycle were fixed.\\n\\n# Files Changed\\n\\n### Scheduler Page\\n- `src/routes/scheduler.tsx` — Added health summary bar, status dots, degraded/failing filters\\n- `src/components/scheduler/CronJobCard.tsx` — Added health status dot, retry counter display\\n- `src/components/scheduler/useCronData.ts` — Existing fields leveraged for health states\\n\\n### Retry Policy\\n- `src/routes/api/retry-policy.tsx` — New endpoint, tracks retry state, auto-creates P2 incident at limit\\n\\n### Incident Management\\n- `src/routes/api/incidents-timeline.tsx` — Added auto-resolution when linked task completes\\n- `src/routes/api/incidents-auto-resolve.tsx` — New bulk resolve/close endpoint\\n- `src/lib/server-data/tasks.ts` — Added `getBacklogCount` endpoint\\n- `scripts/auto-detect-incidents.sh` — Fixed dedup logic to create linked tasks for existing TRIAGE incidents\\n\\n### Dashboard\\n- `src/routes/index.tsx` — Added incidents + tasks data to loader\\n- `src/components/Dashboard.tsx` — Station Status Bar, Agent Load Indicators, alert banner\\n- `src/components/AppSidebar.tsx` — Backlog count badge with polling\\n- `src/components/StationFloorplan.tsx` — Room pulse overlay for active incidents\\n\\n### Agent Office\\n- Existing components: AmbientStation mood tints wired to incident severity\\n\\n### Task System\\n- `HEARTBEAT.md` — Multiple rule fixes (NO GHOST DISPATCHES, exclusion tags, auto-resolve check)\\n- `data/tasks.json` — 28+ stale tasks cleaned up, backlog cleared\\n- `data/incidents.json` — 39 ghosts resolved, auto-resolution linked\\n\\n# Decisions Made\\n\\n### Decision: Health states integrated into existing Scheduler page (not a new page)\\nReason: Avoid page bloat. The Scheduler already shows all cron jobs. Adding health\\nsummary bar and status dots was zero-cost visually and reused existing data\\n(`consecutiveErrors`, `enabled`).\\n\\n### Decision: Simple retry policy (3 retries + 5min gap, no exponential backoff)\\nReason: Phase 1 — get the basics working. Per-job customization and exponential\\nbackoff deferred to Phase 5. Global policy is sufficient for now.\\n\\n### Decision: Incident auto-resolve via `taskStatus` field on timeline endpoint\\nReason: The timeline endpoint is already the hook point for task→incident sync.\\nAdding `taskStatus` as an optional field means auto-resolution happens naturally\\nwithout a separate call. Falls back gracefully if `taskStatus` is not sent.\\n\\n### Decision: Bulk auto-resolve endpoint separate from real-time resolve\\nReason: Two different use cases. Real-time (timeline endpoint) for when tasks complete.\\nBulk (auto-resolve endpoint) for cleanup of stale incidents and cron runs. Keeping\\nthem apart avoids side effects.\\n\\n### Decision: Linked tasks created even when TRIAGE incident already exists\\nReason: Previous dedup logic skipped everything — including task creation — when it\\nfound an existing active incident. This meant repeat detections never got linked tasks,\\nbreaking the entire auto-resolution chain.\\n\\n### Decision: Backlog count badge uses separate polling endpoint\\nReason: `getBacklogCount` is lighter than `getTasks`. The sidebar polls every 30s —\\nno need to serialize the full task list just for a count.\\n\\n# Risks Identified\\n\\n### Risk: `tasks.json` data loss during concurrent writes\\nBoth the auto-detect shell script and the MC API write to `tasks.json`. The shell\\nscript has no atomic write (no `rename` guard). The API (`saveTasks`) does use\\n`tmpPath + rename`. If both write simultaneously, data loss is possible.\\nLikelihood: low (30-min cron vs interactive API calls). Impact: medium.\\n\\n### Risk: Deduplication by title match may merge distinct incidents\\nThe auto-detect script deduplicates by exact title + source tag match. If the same\\nunderlying issue triggers with different counts (e.g., \\\"11 429 errors\\\" vs\\n\\\"26 429 errors\\\"), they get different titles and are NOT deduplicated. This creates\\nmultiple incidents for the same root cause. The 12+ historical rate-limit incidents\\nare evidence of this.\\n\\n### Risk: Client-side task data staleness\\nThe Dashboard fetches tasks at page load via the loader. If a task status changes\\nvia the heartbeat or API, the Dashboard won't reflect it until next navigation.\\nThe sidebar badge polls every 30s but the main page doesn't.\\n\\n### Risk: `ts` field inconsistency across tasks\\nMost tasks use `ts: \\\"just now\\\"` (non-parseable), some use ISO timestamps. The\\nstallend detection logic has to handle both. This is fragile — a future refactor\\nshould enforce ISO timestamps everywhere.\\n\\n# Known Limitation\\n\\n- No real-time updates on the Dashboard (requires navigation to refresh task/incident data)\\n- No per-job retry configuration (global 3-retry policy only)\\n- No exponential backoff on retries\\n- Incident dedup is title-exact-match only (no fuzzy grouping)\\n- Browser automation for external review not implemented (Phase 1 is framework only)\\n- The `/api/incidents/auto-resolve` endpoint exists but is triggered only by\\n  cron/heartbeat — no UI button to run it manually\\n\\n# Proposed Next Steps\\n\\n1. Validate this review framework with manual review cycle\\n2. If review value confirmed: implement Phase 2 (automated external AI review loop)\\n3. Fix `tasks.json` atomic write in auto-detect script\\n4. Add fuzzy incident grouping (same root cause → single incident)\\n5. Add real-time refresh to Dashboard (polling or SSE)\\n\\n# Questions For Reviewer\\n\\n1. **Architecture:** Is the two-layer auto-resolution (real-time timeline + bulk cron)\\n   the right pattern, or should this be a single mechanism?\\n\\n2. **Incident lifecycle:** Should rate-limit incidents (all \\\"429 errors in gateway log\\\")\\n   be grouped into a single rolling incident instead of creating new ones each time?\\n\\n3. **Data integrity:** Is the `tasks.json` concurrent-write risk acceptable, or should\\n   the auto-detect script be converted to use the API exclusively?\\n\\n4. **Review package quality:** Does this level of detail make for a useful review,\\n   or is it too much/too little? What would you want to see in future packages?\\n\\n5. **Phase 2 approach:** Which integration method (browser / OpenRouter / dedicated API)\\n   would you recommend based on the comparison matrix in the review-agent design?\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":274,"output":1645,"cacheRead":108416,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":110335,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780530543136,"responseId":"gen-1780530543-g9kbvxJ4Fipr1b4hjvun"}}
