{"type":"message","id":"d5f332d5","parentId":"9663f8b2","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:50:35.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"d9c29182-a83b-4a23-b8bd-a43c65d9c587","name":"update_plan","arguments":{"plan":[{"step":"Create review-system directory structure","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create templates (review-package, recommendation, decision-log)","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create review-agent design document","status":"in_progress"},{"step":"Create Phase 2 comparison matrix","status":"pending"},{"step":"Create first review package REV-2026-06-04-001","status":"completed"},{"step":"Write README.md with success criteria and roadmap","status":"pending"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"plan\": [{\"step\": \"Create review-system directory structure\", \"status\": \"completed\"}, {\"step\": \"Create templates (review-package, recommendation, decision-log)\", \"status\": \"completed\"}, {\"step\": \"Create review-agent design document\", \"status\": \"in_progress\"}, {\"step\": \"Create Phase 2 comparison matrix\", \"status\": \"pending\"}, {\"step\": \"Create first review package REV-2026-06-04-001\", \"status\": \"completed\"}, {\"step\": \"Write README.md with success criteria and roadmap\", \"status\": \"pending\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":206,"output":137,"cacheRead":110464,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":110807,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780530627442,"responseId":"gen-1780530627-iI78ROP1zfbsu2jQdIX1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"31de75f5","parentId":"d5f332d5","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:50:35.925Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"d9c29182-a83b-4a23-b8bd-a43c65d9c587","toolName":"update_plan","content":[],"details":{"status":"updated","plan":[{"step":"Create review-system directory structure","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create templates (review-package, recommendation, decision-log)","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create review-agent design document","status":"in_progress"},{"step":"Create Phase 2 comparison matrix","status":"pending"},{"step":"Create first review package REV-2026-06-04-001","status":"completed"},{"step":"Write README.md with success criteria and roadmap","status":"pending"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780530635925}}
{"type":"message","id":"28828eb1","parentId":"31de75f5","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:51:11.244Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now the review-agent design document:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"4a4d3055-4fd3-41de-8e39-a2d6cf11f859","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/review-system/review-agent/DESIGN.md","content":"# Review Agent — Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Review Agent manages the lifecycle of external code/work review. It detects\ncompleted work, generates review packages, tracks review status, and records\ndecisions on recommendations.\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\n### 1. Detect Completed Work Requiring Review\n\nMonitor for completed features, significant refactors, architectural changes,\ninfrastructure changes, and security changes.\n\nDo NOT generate packages for small bug fixes, docs updates, minor UI changes,\nor routine maintenance.\n\n**Detection signals:**\n- Task status changes to `done` (from `tasks.json` or API)\n- Architectural decisions documented in `MEMORY.md` or `AGENTS.md`\n- New routes or API endpoints added to the MC dashboard\n- Changes to critical infrastructure (`scripts/`, `data/` schemas, cron jobs)\n\n### 2. Generate Review Packages\n\nWhen triggered, create a review package from the `review-package.md` template\nin `pending/`. Use the following ID format: `REV-YYYY-MM-DD-NNN`.\n\nPackage must include:\n- Summary of what was completed\n- All files changed (from git diff)\n- Decisions made and reasoning\n- Risks identified\n- Known limitations\n- Proposed next steps\n- Specific questions for the reviewer\n\n### 3. Track Review Status\n\nState machine for each review:\n\n```\npending → in-review → reviewed → actioned → archived\n```\n\n| State | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| `pending` | Package generated, not yet sent for review |\n| `in-review` | Package sent to reviewer, awaiting response |\n| `reviewed` | Recommendations received |\n| `actioned` | Decisions made on all recommendations |\n| `archived` | Complete, audit trail preserved |\n\n### 4. Accept Reviewer Recommendations\n\nWhen recommendations are received (from the reviewer), log them using the\n`recommendation.md` template in `recommendations/`.\n\nFile naming: `REV-YYYY-MM-DD-NNN-recommendations.md`\n\n### 5. Record Decisions\n\nFor every recommendation, record the decision using the `decision-log.md`\ntemplate. Outcomes:\n\n| Outcome | Meaning |\n|---------|---------|\n| `accepted` | Recommendation will be implemented |\n| `rejected` | Recommendation will not be implemented (reason required) |\n| `deferred` | Decision postponed (reason required) |\n\nEvery decision requires a reason. No recommendation should be silently ignored.\n\n### 6. Maintain Audit History\n\nAll review packages, recommendations, and decision logs are kept permanently.\nNothing is deleted — only archived. The `reviewed/` directory holds completed\nreview cycles.\n\n---\n\n## Workflow (Manual — Phase 1)\n\n```\n1. OpenClaw completes work\n       ↓\n2. Review Agent detects completion\n       ↓\n3. Generate review package → pending/\n       ↓\n4. Andre reviews work (manually)\n       ↓\n5. Write recommendations → recommendations/\n       ↓\n6. Review Agent records decisions → decision-log/\n       ↓\n7. Accepted items → implement\n       ↓\n8. Archive → reviewed/\n```\n\n## Workflow (Automated — Phase 2, Future)\n\n```\n1. OpenClaw completes work\n       ↓\n2. Review Agent detects completion\n       ↓\n3. Generate review package\n       ↓\n4. Submit to external AI reviewer (via chosen integration)\n       ↓\n5. Receive structured recommendations\n       ↓\n6. Review Agent logs decisions\n       ↓\n7. Accepted items → auto-dispatch implementation tasks\n       ↓\n8. Archive\n```\n\n---\n\n## Future Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1 (Current): Framework ✅\n- Directory structure created\n- Templates created\n- Workflow documented\n- First review package generated\n\n### Phase 2: Manual Testing\n- Use the process manually for 2-3 cycles\n- Andre pastes review packages into external AI\n- Recommendations returned to OpenClaw via `recommendations/` folder\n- Decisions recorded\n- Evaluate whether recommendations genuinely improve work quality\n\n### Phase 3: Automated Review Pipeline\n- Implement chosen integration method (see PHASE-2-ANALYSIS.md)\n- Automate package submission\n- Automate recommendation ingestion\n- Auto-dispatch accepted improvements as tasks\n\n---\n\n## File Layout\n\n```\nreview-system/\n├── pending/            # Packages awaiting review\n├── reviewed/           # Completed review cycles (audit trail)\n├── recommendations/   # Reviewer recommendations\n├── templates/          # review-package.md, recommendation.md, decision-log.md\n├── review-agent/       # This design document\n├── logs/               # Review agent activity log\n└── README.md           # System overview\n```\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/review-system/review-agent/DESIGN.md\", \"content\": \"# Review Agent — Design Document\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe Review Agent manages the lifecycle of external code/work review. It detects\\ncompleted work, generates review packages, tracks review status, and records\\ndecisions on recommendations.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\n### 1. Detect Completed Work Requiring Review\\n\\nMonitor for completed features, significant refactors, architectural changes,\\ninfrastructure changes, and security changes.\\n\\nDo NOT generate packages for small bug fixes, docs updates, minor UI changes,\\nor routine maintenance.\\n\\n**Detection signals:**\\n- Task status changes to `done` (from `tasks.json` or API)\\n- Architectural decisions documented in `MEMORY.md` or `AGENTS.md`\\n- New routes or API endpoints added to the MC dashboard\\n- Changes to critical infrastructure (`scripts/`, `data/` schemas, cron jobs)\\n\\n### 2. Generate Review Packages\\n\\nWhen triggered, create a review package from the `review-package.md` template\\nin `pending/`. Use the following ID format: `REV-YYYY-MM-DD-NNN`.\\n\\nPackage must include:\\n- Summary of what was completed\\n- All files changed (from git diff)\\n- Decisions made and reasoning\\n- Risks identified\\n- Known limitations\\n- Proposed next steps\\n- Specific questions for the reviewer\\n\\n### 3. Track Review Status\\n\\nState machine for each review:\\n\\n```\\npending → in-review → reviewed → actioned → archived\\n```\\n\\n| State | Meaning |\\n|-------|---------|\\n| `pending` | Package generated, not yet sent for review |\\n| `in-review` | Package sent to reviewer, awaiting response |\\n| `reviewed` | Recommendations received |\\n| `actioned` | Decisions made on all recommendations |\\n| `archived` | Complete, audit trail preserved |\\n\\n### 4. Accept Reviewer Recommendations\\n\\nWhen recommendations are received (from the reviewer), log them using the\\n`recommendation.md` template in `recommendations/`.\\n\\nFile naming: `REV-YYYY-MM-DD-NNN-recommendations.md`\\n\\n### 5. Record Decisions\\n\\nFor every recommendation, record the decision using the `decision-log.md`\\ntemplate. Outcomes:\\n\\n| Outcome | Meaning |\\n|---------|---------|\\n| `accepted` | Recommendation will be implemented |\\n| `rejected` | Recommendation will not be implemented (reason required) |\\n| `deferred` | Decision postponed (reason required) |\\n\\nEvery decision requires a reason. No recommendation should be silently ignored.\\n\\n### 6. Maintain Audit History\\n\\nAll review packages, recommendations, and decision logs are kept permanently.\\nNothing is deleted — only archived. The `reviewed/` directory holds completed\\nreview cycles.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Workflow (Manual — Phase 1)\\n\\n```\\n1. OpenClaw completes work\\n       ↓\\n2. Review Agent detects completion\\n       ↓\\n3. Generate review package → pending/\\n       ↓\\n4. Andre reviews work (manually)\\n       ↓\\n5. Write recommendations → recommendations/\\n       ↓\\n6. Review Agent records decisions → decision-log/\\n       ↓\\n7. Accepted items → implement\\n       ↓\\n8. Archive → reviewed/\\n```\\n\\n## Workflow (Automated — Phase 2, Future)\\n\\n```\\n1. OpenClaw completes work\\n       ↓\\n2. Review Agent detects completion\\n       ↓\\n3. Generate review package\\n       ↓\\n4. Submit to external AI reviewer (via chosen integration)\\n       ↓\\n5. Receive structured recommendations\\n       ↓\\n6. Review Agent logs decisions\\n       ↓\\n7. Accepted items → auto-dispatch implementation tasks\\n       ↓\\n8. Archive\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Future Implementation Plan\\n\\n### Phase 1 (Current): Framework ✅\\n- Directory structure created\\n- Templates created\\n- Workflow documented\\n- First review package generated\\n\\n### Phase 2: Manual Testing\\n- Use the process manually for 2-3 cycles\\n- Andre pastes review packages into external AI\\n- Recommendations returned to OpenClaw via `recommendations/` folder\\n- Decisions recorded\\n- Evaluate whether recommendations genuinely improve work quality\\n\\n### Phase 3: Automated Review Pipeline\\n- Implement chosen integration method (see PHASE-2-ANALYSIS.md)\\n- Automate package submission\\n- Automate recommendation ingestion\\n- Auto-dispatch accepted improvements as tasks\\n\\n---\\n\\n## File Layout\\n\\n```\\nreview-system/\\n├── pending/            # Packages awaiting review\\n├── reviewed/           # Completed review cycles (audit trail)\\n├── recommendations/   # Reviewer recommendations\\n├── templates/          # review-package.md, recommendation.md, decision-log.md\\n├── review-agent/       # This design document\\n├── logs/               # Review agent activity log\\n└── README.md           # System overview\\n```\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":233,"output":1034,"cacheRead":110592,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":111859,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780530635941,"responseId":"gen-1780530636-MpM2xMwkbbU1th1YftH6"}}
