{"type":"message","id":"1b96fd14","parentId":"3d6ef785","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:52:02.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"8890ca72-f268-4259-a137-b090a08cdbee","name":"update_plan","arguments":{"plan":[{"step":"Create review-system directory structure","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create templates (review-package, recommendation, decision-log)","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create review-agent design document","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create Phase 2 comparison matrix","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create first review package REV-2026-06-04-001","status":"completed"},{"step":"Write README.md with success criteria and roadmap","status":"in_progress"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"plan\": [{\"step\": \"Create review-system directory structure\", \"status\": \"completed\"}, {\"step\": \"Create templates (review-package, recommendation, decision-log)\", \"status\": \"completed\"}, {\"step\": \"Create review-agent design document\", \"status\": \"completed\"}, {\"step\": \"Create Phase 2 comparison matrix\", \"status\": \"completed\"}, {\"step\": \"Create first review package REV-2026-06-04-001\", \"status\": \"completed\"}, {\"step\": \"Write README.md with success criteria and roadmap\", \"status\": \"in_progress\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1355,"output":137,"cacheRead":111872,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":113364,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780530711325,"responseId":"gen-1780530711-LJMx8s2o9F6Sfa1YZsDl"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1325c747","parentId":"1b96fd14","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:52:02.504Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"8890ca72-f268-4259-a137-b090a08cdbee","toolName":"update_plan","content":[],"details":{"status":"updated","plan":[{"step":"Create review-system directory structure","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create templates (review-package, recommendation, decision-log)","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create review-agent design document","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create Phase 2 comparison matrix","status":"completed"},{"step":"Create first review package REV-2026-06-04-001","status":"completed"},{"step":"Write README.md with success criteria and roadmap","status":"in_progress"}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780530722503}}
{"type":"message","id":"b92689ec","parentId":"1325c747","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:52:34.376Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now the README:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"ee2678ee-61ef-4b7e-b4b3-8ec386993783","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/review-system/README.md","content":"# External AI Review System\n\n## Purpose\n\nValidate whether external AI review improves the quality of OpenClaw's work\nbefore investing in automation.\n\n**Phase 1 (current):** Framework only. Manual review process. No external API calls.\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\nreview-system/\n├── pending/            # Review packages awaiting review\n├── reviewed/           # Completed review cycles (audit trail)\n├── recommendations/   # Reviewer recommendations\n├── templates/          # Reusable templates\n│   ├── review-package.md\n│   ├── recommendation.md\n│   └── decision-log.md\n├── review-agent/       # Design docs and analysis\n│   ├── DESIGN.md\n│   └── PHASE-2-ANALYSIS.md\n├── logs/               # Review agent activity log\n└── README.md           # This file\n```\n\n## Review Triggers\n\nGenerate review packages when:\n- Feature completed\n- Significant refactor completed\n- Architectural change made\n- Infrastructure change made\n- Security change made\n\nDo NOT generate for:\n- Small bug fixes\n- Documentation updates\n- Minor UI changes\n- Routine maintenance\n\n## Review Workflow\n\n```\n1. OpenClaw completes work\n       ↓\n2. Review Agent detects completion\n       ↓\n3. Generate review package → pending/\n       ↓\n4. Andre reviews (manually in Phase 1)\n       ↓\n5. Write recommendations → recommendations/\n       ↓\n6. Review Agent records decisions → decision-log/\n       ↓\n7. Accepted items → implement\n       ↓\n8. Archive → reviewed/\n```\n\n## State Machine\n\n```\npending → in-review → reviewed → actioned → archived\n```\n\n## Success Criteria\n\nA successful Phase 1 implementation provides:\n- [x] Review system directory structure\n- [x] Working templates (review-package, recommendation, decision-log)\n- [x] Review workflow documented\n- [x] Review-agent design documented\n- [x] Phase 2 architecture comparison completed\n- [x] First review package generated (REV-2026-06-04-001)\n\n## Assessment\n\n### 1. Is the review process likely to improve outcomes?\n\n**Yes, with caveats.** External review adds value when:\n- The reviewer has different expertise or perspective\n- The work involves architectural decisions with long-term consequences\n- There are non-obvious risks or edge cases\n\nExternal review adds less value when:\n- The work is routine or well-understood\n- The reviewer has the same blind spots as the implementer\n- The overhead of generating packages exceeds the value of feedback\n\n**Recommendation:** Test with 3-5 review cycles. If at least 2 produce\nactionable recommendations that improve the work, proceed to Phase 2.\n\n### 2. Is Phase 2 automation justified?\n\n**Conditional yes.** Automation is justified if:\n- Manual review produces consistent value (see above)\n- The review cycle time is acceptable (target: <24h from completion to recommendations)\n- The cost of external API calls is reasonable (~$100/month for daily reviews)\n\nIf manual review doesn't produce value, automation won't help — it will just\nproduce expensive noise faster.\n\n### 3. Which integration option should be implemented first?\n\n**Option B: OpenRouter** (see `review-agent/PHASE-2-Analysis.md`)\n\n- Already integrated into OpenClaw\n- Provider-agnostic (swap models without code changes)\n- Lowest maintenance burden\n- ~$100/month at 1 review/day\n\nFallback: Option C with DeepSeek for cost reduction.\n\n### 4. Phased Roadmap\n\n| Phase | Goal | Status |\n|-------|------|--------|\n| **Phase 1** | Framework + manual testing | ✅ Complete |\n| **Phase 2** | Manual review cycles (3-5 tests) | 🔜 Next |\n| **Phase 3** | Automated pipeline (OpenRouter) | ⏳ Future |\n| **Phase 4** | Continuous review (every significant change) | ⏳ Future |\n\n**Phase 2 manual test process:**\n1. Andre takes `pending/REV-2026-06-04-001.md`\n2. Pastes into external AI (DeepSeek, Claude, etc.)\n3. Saves recommendations to `recommendations/REV-2026-06-04-001-recommendations.md`\n4. Space Monkey records decisions in `decision-log/`\n5. Accepted items become implementation tasks\n6. Archive to `reviewed/`\n\nAfter 3-5 cycles, evaluate: are recommendations genuinely improving work quality?\nIf yes → implement Phase 3 with OpenRouter.\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/review-system/README.md\", \"content\": \"# External AI Review System\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nValidate whether external AI review improves the quality of OpenClaw's work\\nbefore investing in automation.\\n\\n**Phase 1 (current):** Framework only. Manual review process. No external API calls.\\n\\n## Directory Structure\\n\\n```\\nreview-system/\\n├── pending/            # Review packages awaiting review\\n├── reviewed/           # Completed review cycles (audit trail)\\n├── recommendations/   # Reviewer recommendations\\n├── templates/          # Reusable templates\\n│   ├── review-package.md\\n│   ├── recommendation.md\\n│   └── decision-log.md\\n├── review-agent/       # Design docs and analysis\\n│   ├── DESIGN.md\\n│   └── PHASE-2-ANALYSIS.md\\n├── logs/               # Review agent activity log\\n└── README.md           # This file\\n```\\n\\n## Review Triggers\\n\\nGenerate review packages when:\\n- Feature completed\\n- Significant refactor completed\\n- Architectural change made\\n- Infrastructure change made\\n- Security change made\\n\\nDo NOT generate for:\\n- Small bug fixes\\n- Documentation updates\\n- Minor UI changes\\n- Routine maintenance\\n\\n## Review Workflow\\n\\n```\\n1. OpenClaw completes work\\n       ↓\\n2. Review Agent detects completion\\n       ↓\\n3. Generate review package → pending/\\n       ↓\\n4. Andre reviews (manually in Phase 1)\\n       ↓\\n5. Write recommendations → recommendations/\\n       ↓\\n6. Review Agent records decisions → decision-log/\\n       ↓\\n7. Accepted items → implement\\n       ↓\\n8. Archive → reviewed/\\n```\\n\\n## State Machine\\n\\n```\\npending → in-review → reviewed → actioned → archived\\n```\\n\\n## Success Criteria\\n\\nA successful Phase 1 implementation provides:\\n- [x] Review system directory structure\\n- [x] Working templates (review-package, recommendation, decision-log)\\n- [x] Review workflow documented\\n- [x] Review-agent design documented\\n- [x] Phase 2 architecture comparison completed\\n- [x] First review package generated (REV-2026-06-04-001)\\n\\n## Assessment\\n\\n### 1. Is the review process likely to improve outcomes?\\n\\n**Yes, with caveats.** External review adds value when:\\n- The reviewer has different expertise or perspective\\n- The work involves architectural decisions with long-term consequences\\n- There are non-obvious risks or edge cases\\n\\nExternal review adds less value when:\\n- The work is routine or well-understood\\n- The reviewer has the same blind spots as the implementer\\n- The overhead of generating packages exceeds the value of feedback\\n\\n**Recommendation:** Test with 3-5 review cycles. If at least 2 produce\\nactionable recommendations that improve the work, proceed to Phase 2.\\n\\n### 2. Is Phase 2 automation justified?\\n\\n**Conditional yes.** Automation is justified if:\\n- Manual review produces consistent value (see above)\\n- The review cycle time is acceptable (target: <24h from completion to recommendations)\\n- The cost of external API calls is reasonable (~$100/month for daily reviews)\\n\\nIf manual review doesn't produce value, automation won't help — it will just\\nproduce expensive noise faster.\\n\\n### 3. Which integration option should be implemented first?\\n\\n**Option B: OpenRouter** (see `review-agent/PHASE-2-Analysis.md`)\\n\\n- Already integrated into OpenClaw\\n- Provider-agnostic (swap models without code changes)\\n- Lowest maintenance burden\\n- ~$100/month at 1 review/day\\n\\nFallback: Option C with DeepSeek for cost reduction.\\n\\n### 4. Phased Roadmap\\n\\n| Phase | Goal | Status |\\n|-------|------|--------|\\n| **Phase 1** | Framework + manual testing | ✅ Complete |\\n| **Phase 2** | Manual review cycles (3-5 tests) | 🔜 Next |\\n| **Phase 3** | Automated pipeline (OpenRouter) | ⏳ Future |\\n| **Phase 4** | Continuous review (every significant change) | ⏳ Future |\\n\\n**Phase 2 manual test process:**\\n1. Andre takes `pending/REV-2026-06-04-001.md`\\n2. Pastes into external AI (DeepSeek, Claude, etc.)\\n3. Saves recommendations to `recommendations/REV-2026-06-04-001-recommendations.md`\\n4. Space Monkey records decisions in `decision-log/`\\n5. Accepted items become implementation tasks\\n6. Archive to `reviewed/`\\n\\nAfter 3-5 cycles, evaluate: are recommendations genuinely improving work quality?\\nIf yes → implement Phase 3 with OpenRouter.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":229,"output":1030,"cacheRead":113152,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":114411,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780530722519,"responseId":"gen-1780530722-WmAF6lMMwOBdUPcA3FZo"}}
