{"type":"message","id":"ec0fd89f","parentId":"314d0052","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:52:59.342Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"0e3ccc4a-d569-4a6d-a01c-12ff18b765e8","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[main a2ae420] External AI Review Loop — Phase 1 framework\n 8 files changed, 646 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)\n create mode 100644 review-system/README.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/pending/REV-2026-06-04-001.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/review-agent/DESIGN.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/review-agent/PHASE-2-ANALYSIS.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/templates/decision-log.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/templates/recommendation.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/templates/review-package.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":50,"aggregated":"[main a2ae420] External AI Review Loop — Phase 1 framework\n 8 files changed, 646 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)\n create mode 100644 review-system/README.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/pending/REV-2026-06-04-001.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/review-agent/DESIGN.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/review-agent/PHASE-2-ANALYSIS.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/templates/decision-log.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/templates/recommendation.md\n create mode 100644 review-system/templates/review-package.md","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780530779341}}
{"type":"message","id":"5fff1408","parentId":"ec0fd89f","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:53:17.657Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 Deliverables ✅\n\n**Directory structure** — `review-system/` with all 6 subdirectories.\n\n**Templates (3):**\n- `review-package.md` — Structured summary of completed work for external review\n- `recommendation.md` — Reviewer recommendations with priority/reasoning/benefit\n- `decision-log.md` — Decision tracking (accepted/rejected/deferred + reasoning)\n\n**Review Agent Design** (`review-agent/DESIGN.md`):\n- 6 responsibilities: detect, generate, track, accept, decide, audit\n- State machine: `pending → in-review → reviewed → actioned → archived`\n- Manual (Phase 1) and automated (Phase 3) workflows\n\n**Phase 2 Comparison** (`review-agent/PHASE-2-ANALYSIS.md`):\n- Option A (Browser): ❌ Not recommended — fragile, high maintenance, ToS risk\n- Option B (OpenRouter): ✅ **Recommended** — provider-agnostic, already integrated, ~$100/mo\n- Option C (Dedicated API): 🟡 Good fallback — cheaper with DeepSeek, less flexible\n\n**First Review Package** (`pending/REV-2026-06-04-001.md`):\n- Covers all 6 feature areas delivered in this session\n- Documents decisions, risks, limitations, and 5 specific reviewer questions\n\n---\n\n**Next step:** Take `REV-2026-06-04-001.md`, paste it into an external AI, and save the response to `recommendations/REV-2026-06-04-001-recommendations.md`. I'll record decisions from there."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":374,"output":382,"cacheRead":114816,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":115572,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780530779352,"responseId":"gen-1780530779-HNTkOa6L1inwD5U84hrx"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1a2f8593","parentId":"5fff1408","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:59:37.277Z","message":{"role":"user","content":"Good work on the Review System. Now fix the critical issue:\n\nThe Agent Office is broken on the Dashboard. The browser Console shows:\n\"Module node:fs has been externalized for browser compatibility. \nCannot access node:fs.readFileSync in client code.\"\n\nThis is the same node:fs leak we've fixed multiple times. The recent \nalert banner or incident atmosphere work likely added an import that \npulls server-side code into a client component.\n\nFix:\n1. Check the import chain in Dashboard.tsx — the alert banner or \n   incident mood changes probably imported something from server-data \n   or helpers that pulls in node:fs\n2. The pattern is always: component → server-data/index → helpers → \n   node:fs. Break that chain.\n3. Any fs-dependent code must stay in a server function or loader, \n   never imported directly into a component\n\nThe Assets tab removal and pagination can wait. This is the critical fix.","timestamp":1780531177102,"idempotencyKey":"d876554f-b2e9-4e6c-9c77-fd242f48ca26:user"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ffffeb28","parentId":"1a2f8593","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:59:46.537Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nLet me trace the import chain. The error says `node:fs` is leaking into client code — this happens when a server-only module gets imported into a client component."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"65d3f65b-14be-4caf-a20b-fbdfc60c5cde","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"head -20 ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/Dashboard.tsx","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"head -20 ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/Dashboard.tsx\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":9154,"output":78,"cacheRead":106624,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":115856,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780531177287,"responseId":"gen-1780531177-fImOoyhzAW1hrU5Z7tQ1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb57ba85","parentId":"ffffeb28","timestamp":"2026-06-03T23:59:46.609Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"65d3f65b-14be-4caf-a20b-fbdfc60c5cde","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { useEffect, useState } from \"react\";\nimport { getCrew, CREW } from \"@/lib/crew\";\nimport { getAwaitingReviewCount } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { AgentStatus, SystemStats, OpenClawStatus, ActivityEvent, Incident } from \"@/lib/server-data-types\";\nimport type { Task } from \"@/lib/server-data-types\";\nimport { getDreamingState, toggleDreaming } from \"@/lib/dreaming\";\nimport { Power, Moon, Activity, CheckCircle, AlertTriangle, Clock, Zap, HeartPulse } from \"lucide-react\";\nimport { Link } from \"@tanstack/react-router\";\nimport { AgentOffice } from \"./AgentOffice\";\nimport { AmbientStation } from \"./AmbientStation\";\nimport { StationFloorplan } from \"./StationFloorplan\";\nimport { CelebrationOverlay } from \"./CelebrationOverlay\";\n\n// ── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n// ── Live Activity Feed ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfunction LiveActivityFeed({ events, stats }: { events: ActivityEvent[]; stats: SystemStats }) {\n  const [currentTime, setCurrentTime] = useState<Date | null>(null);\n  useEffect(() => { setCurrentTime(new Date()); const t = setInterval(() => setCurrentTime(new Date()), 1000); return () => clearInterval(t); }, []);"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":11,"aggregated":"import { useEffect, useState } from \"react\";\nimport { getCrew, CREW } from \"@/lib/crew\";\nimport { getAwaitingReviewCount } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { AgentStatus, SystemStats, OpenClawStatus, ActivityEvent, Incident } from \"@/lib/server-data-types\";\nimport type { Task } from \"@/lib/server-data-types\";\nimport { getDreamingState, toggleDreaming } from \"@/lib/dreaming\";\nimport { Power, Moon, Activity, CheckCircle, AlertTriangle, Clock, Zap, HeartPulse } from \"lucide-react\";\nimport { Link } from \"@tanstack/react-router\";\nimport { AgentOffice } from \"./AgentOffice\";\nimport { AmbientStation } from \"./AmbientStation\";\nimport { StationFloorplan } from \"./StationFloorplan\";\nimport { CelebrationOverlay } from \"./CelebrationOverlay\";\n\n// ── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n// ── Live Activity Feed ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfunction LiveActivityFeed({ events, stats }: { events: ActivityEvent[]; stats: SystemStats }) {\n  const [currentTime, setCurrentTime] = useState<Date | null>(null);\n  useEffect(() => { setCurrentTime(new Date()); const t = setInterval(() => setCurrentTime(new Date()), 1000); return () => clearInterval(t); }, []);","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780531186608}}
