{"type":"message","id":"31ef05ba","parentId":"d590f87e","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:00:22.424Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There it is. `openclaw-status.ts` imports `readJsonOrNull` from `helpers.ts` which imports `node:fs`. Even though `getAwaitingReviewCount` is wrapped in `createServerFn` (which should be server-only), the **module-level import** of `readJsonOrNull` means `node:fs` gets pulled into the client bundle through the barrel export.\n\nThe fix: the Dashboard should NOT import `getAwaitingReviewCount` from the barrel. Instead, the data should come through the loader. Let me check how the Dashboard uses it:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"3627f144-69c1-424b-b027-fb3b229de92c","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"getAwaitingReviewCount\\|awaitingReviewCount\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/Dashboard.tsx","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"grep -n \\\"getAwaitingReviewCount\\\\|awaitingReviewCount\\\" ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/components/Dashboard.tsx\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":1434,"output":172,"cacheRead":117632,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":119238,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780531211295,"responseId":"gen-1780531211-abiASr6EmkjdYwoKrbU7"}}
