{"type":"message","id":"d0c2c467","parentId":"321fea57","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:01:45.738Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"e9d781fd-35b1-4159-83fa-e3aa3688574d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import { useState, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { CREW } from \"@/lib/crew\";\nimport { getTasks } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { Incident, IncidentAction, IncidentEvent, Task } from \"@/lib/server-data-types\";\nimport { getRunbookForIncident, type Runbook } from \"@/lib/server-data/runbooks\";\nimport { getIncidentTimeline } from \"@/lib/server-data/timeline-data\";\nimport { Sheet, SheetContent, SheetDescription, SheetHeader, SheetTitle } from \"@/components/ui/sheet\";\nimport { Pill } from \"@/components/PageHeader\";\nimport {\n  AlertTriangle,"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9,"aggregated":"import { useState, useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport { CREW } from \"@/lib/crew\";\nimport { getTasks } from \"@/lib/server-data\";\nimport type { Incident, IncidentAction, IncidentEvent, Task } from \"@/lib/server-data-types\";\nimport { getRunbookForIncident, type Runbook } from \"@/lib/server-data/runbooks\";\nimport { getIncidentTimeline } from \"@/lib/server-data/timeline-data\";\nimport { Sheet, SheetContent, SheetDescription, SheetHeader, SheetTitle } from \"@/components/ui/sheet\";\nimport { Pill } from \"@/components/PageHeader\";\nimport {\n  AlertTriangle,","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780531305737}}
{"type":"message","id":"db251462","parentId":"d0c2c467","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:01:56.794Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All four client components import from the barrel. The issue is that even though these are `createServerFn` functions (which should be tree-shaken from the client bundle), the **barrel file itself** re-exports from modules that have top-level `node:fs` imports. Vite can't tree-shake this because the barrel is a single module — if anything in it is imported, the whole thing gets evaluated.\n\nThe fix: these client components should import directly from the specific server module, not from the barrel. But actually, the better fix is to make the barrel not re-export the server-only modules that have `node:fs` imports. Let me check what the barrel exports and which ones are actually server-only:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"9ae90419-e9d2-490a-b4a5-61961aa03d58","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data.ts","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data.ts\", \"timeout\": 5}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":199,"output":187,"cacheRead":121344,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":121730,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780531305758,"responseId":"gen-1780531306-RpNt7ZMLNShDE2X228BR"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0149d46e","parentId":"db251462","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:01:56.839Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"9ae90419-e9d2-490a-b4a5-61961aa03d58","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// src/lib/server-data.ts — barrel export for all server data functions\n// Split into domain modules: server-data/{tasks,crons,memory,docs,projects,incidents,search,activity,system,agent-status,quick-actions,openclaw-status}.ts\n\nexport type {\n  // Types\n  Task, TaskHistoryEntry, QueueItem, CronJob, OpenClawCronJob,\n  SystemStats, AgentStatus, MemoryEntry, Doc, Project,\n  Incident, IncidentEvent, IncidentAction, CreateIncidentInput,\n  ActivityEvent, SearchResult, OpenClawStatus,\n  ActionResult, SystemHealth, AwaitingReviewResult, CronToggleResult,\n} from \"./server-data/types\";\nexport { WORKSPACE, OPENCLAW_DIR } from \"./server-data/types\";\n\nexport { getTasks, saveTasks, dispatchTask, getQueue, getBacklogCount } from \"./server-data/tasks\";\nexport { getCronJobs } from \"./server-data/crons\";\nexport { getDailyLogs, getLongTermMemory } from \"./server-data/memory\";\nexport { getDocs } from \"./server-data/docs\";\nexport { getProjects } from \"./server-data/projects\";\nexport { getIncidents, createIncident } from \"./server-data/incidents\";\nexport { search } from \"./server-data/search\";\nexport { getActivityFeed } from \"./server-data/activity\";\nexport { getSystemStats, getSystemHealth } from \"./server-data/system\";\nexport { getAgentStatus } from \"./server-data/agent-status\";\nexport {\n  restartGateway, clearCache, runFreerideRefresh, toggleDreaming,\n  pauseQueue, resumeQueue, restartMissionControl, runBackup,\n} from \"./server-data/quick-actions\";\nexport { getOpenClawStatus, getOpenClawCrons, getAwaitingReviewCount } from \"./server-data/openclaw-status\";"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":12,"aggregated":"// src/lib/server-data.ts — barrel export for all server data functions\n// Split into domain modules: server-data/{tasks,crons,memory,docs,projects,incidents,search,activity,system,agent-status,quick-actions,openclaw-status}.ts\n\nexport type {\n  // Types\n  Task, TaskHistoryEntry, QueueItem, CronJob, OpenClawCronJob,\n  SystemStats, AgentStatus, MemoryEntry, Doc, Project,\n  Incident, IncidentEvent, IncidentAction, CreateIncidentInput,\n  ActivityEvent, SearchResult, OpenClawStatus,\n  ActionResult, SystemHealth, AwaitingReviewResult, CronToggleResult,\n} from \"./server-data/types\";\nexport { WORKSPACE, OPENCLAW_DIR } from \"./server-data/types\";\n\nexport { getTasks, saveTasks, dispatchTask, getQueue, getBacklogCount } from \"./server-data/tasks\";\nexport { getCronJobs } from \"./server-data/crons\";\nexport { getDailyLogs, getLongTermMemory } from \"./server-data/memory\";\nexport { getDocs } from \"./server-data/docs\";\nexport { getProjects } from \"./server-data/projects\";\nexport { getIncidents, createIncident } from \"./server-data/incidents\";\nexport { search } from \"./server-data/search\";\nexport { getActivityFeed } from \"./server-data/activity\";\nexport { getSystemStats, getSystemHealth } from \"./server-data/system\";\nexport { getAgentStatus } from \"./server-data/agent-status\";\nexport {\n  restartGateway, clearCache, runFreerideRefresh, toggleDreaming,\n  pauseQueue, resumeQueue, restartMissionControl, runBackup,\n} from \"./server-data/quick-actions\";\nexport { getOpenClawStatus, getOpenClawCrons, getAwaitingReviewCount } from \"./server-data/openclaw-status\";","cwd":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780531316838}}
{"type":"message","id":"79b093a0","parentId":"0149d46e","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:02:07.656Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The problem is clear. Every single one of these modules imports from `helpers.ts` which has `node:fs` at the top level. The barrel re-exports all of them, so importing anything from the barrel pulls in everything.\n\nThe real fix: **stop using the barrel import in client components**. Each client component should import directly from the specific module, and only the functions that are safe for client-side use. But even better — the `createServerFn` functions should be safe because they're supposed to be tree-shaken. The issue is that Vite sees the static import of the barrel and includes the whole module graph.\n\nLet me verify my fix works by building:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"f9fb1ed7-6376-4067-9457-7ab30f490a07","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && bun run build 2>&1 | tail -10","timeout":30},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && bun run build 2>&1 | tail -10\", \"timeout\": 30}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":649,"output":185,"cacheRead":121472,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":122306,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780531316856,"responseId":"gen-1780531317-vFVOKCz4W1LpbYD8Gl4Y"}}
