{"type":"message","id":"96254eba","parentId":"5e570b4d","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:02:38.359Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait — `openclaw-status.ts` also imports from `helpers.ts` (which has `node:fs`). And `tasks.ts` also imports from `helpers.ts`. So importing directly from those modules won't help — they all have `node:fs` at the top level.\n\nThe real fix needs to be at the `helpers.ts` level. Let me check:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"f062a5df-63ac-483d-8bba-859b257a10d8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":311,"output":113,"cacheRead":122880,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":123304,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780531350146,"responseId":"gen-1780531350-2qyqOtcwDNXymECX0HpY"}}
{"type":"message","id":"60c8fc51","parentId":"96254eba","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:02:38.400Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"f062a5df-63ac-483d-8bba-859b257a10d8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts\n// Shared utility functions\n\nimport { readFileSync, existsSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { WORKSPACE } from \"./types\";\n\nexport function readFileOrNull(path: string): string | null {\n  try {\n    if (!existsSync(path)) return null;\n    return readFileSync(path, \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nexport function readJsonOrNull<T>(path: string): T | null {\n  const raw = readFileOrNull(path);\n  if (!raw) return null;\n  try {\n    return JSON.parse(raw) as T;\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nexport function formatBytes(bytes: number): string {\n  if (bytes === 0) return \"0 B\";\n  const k = 1024;\n  const sizes = [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\", \"TB\"];\n  const i = Math.floor(Math.log(bytes) / Math.log(k));\n  return parseFloat((bytes / Math.pow(k, i)).toFixed(1)) + \" \" + sizes[i];\n}\n\nexport function extractTitle(md: string): string {\n  const h1 = md.match(/^#\\s+(.+)/m);\n  if (h1) return h1[1].replace(/<!--.*?>/g, \"\").trim();\n  const h2 = md.match(/^##\\s+(.+)/m);\n  if (h2) return h2[1].replace(/<!--.*?>/g, \"\").trim();\n  return \"Untitled\";\n}\n\nexport function parseSize(s: string): number {\n  const match = s.match(/^([\\d.]+)\\s*([KMGT]?B?)$/i);\n  if (!match) return 0;\n  const num = parseFloat(match[1]);\n  const unit = (match[2] || \"B\").toUpperCase();\n  const mult = unit.startsWith(\"K\") ? 1024 : unit.startsWith(\"M\") ? 1024 ** 2 : unit.startsWith(\"G\") ? 1024 ** 3 : unit.startsWith(\"T\") ? 1024 ** 4 : 1;\n  return num * mult;\n}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780531358399}}
{"type":"message","id":"7695d250","parentId":"60c8fc51","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:02:57.923Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `node:fs` imports are at the top of `helpers.ts`. Every module that imports from `helpers.ts` pulls in `node:fs`. The `createServerFn` wrapper is supposed to prevent this from reaching the client, but Vite's tree-shaking isn't catching it because the imports are static.\n\nThe proper fix: make `helpers.ts` lazy-import `node:fs` so it's not a top-level import. This way, the module can be imported on the client without pulling in `node:fs` — the `fs` code only runs when the function is actually called (which only happens on the server)."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"cafcd38a-14fa-4c05-9397-dcb8d7945d86","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts","edits":[{"oldText":"// src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts\n// Shared utility functions\n\nimport { readFileSync, existsSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport { WORKSPACE } from \"./types\";\n\nexport function readFileOrNull(path: string): string | null {\n  try {\n    if (!existsSync(path)) return null;\n    return readFileSync(path, \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nexport function readJsonOrNull<T>(path: string): T | null {\n  const raw = readFileOrNull(path);\n  if (!raw) return null;\n  try {\n    return JSON.parse(raw) as T;\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}","newText":"// src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts\n// Shared utility functions\n// NOTE: node:fs is lazy-imported to avoid pulling it into client bundles.\n// These functions are only called from server-side code (createServerFn handlers),\n// but the module itself may be imported by client components through barrel exports.\nimport { WORKSPACE } from \"./types\";\n\nexport async function readFileOrNull(path: string): Promise<string | null> {\n  try {\n    const { existsSync, readFileSync } = await import(\"node:fs\");\n    if (!existsSync(path)) return null;\n    return readFileSync(path, \"utf-8\");\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function readJsonOrNull<T>(path: string): Promise<T | null> {\n  const raw = await readFileOrNull(path);\n  if (!raw) return null;\n  try {\n    return JSON.parse(raw) as T;\n  } catch {\n    return null;\n  }\n}"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"// src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts\\n// Shared utility functions\\n\\nimport { readFileSync, existsSync } from \\\"node:fs\\\";\\nimport { WORKSPACE } from \\\"./types\\\";\\n\\nexport function readFileOrNull(path: string): string | null {\\n  try {\\n    if (!existsSync(path)) return null;\\n    return readFileSync(path, \\\"utf-8\\\");\\n  } catch {\\n    return null;\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nexport function readJsonOrNull<T>(path: string): T | null {\\n  const raw = readFileOrNull(path);\\n  if (!raw) return null;\\n  try {\\n    return JSON.parse(raw) as T;\\n  } catch {\\n    return null;\\n  }\\n}\", \"newText\": \"// src/lib/server-data/helpers.ts\\n// Shared utility functions\\n// NOTE: node:fs is lazy-imported to avoid pulling it into client bundles.\\n// These functions are only called from server-side code (createServerFn handlers),\\n// but the module itself may be imported by client components through barrel exports.\\nimport { WORKSPACE } from \\\"./types\\\";\\n\\nexport async function readFileOrNull(path: string): Promise<string | null> {\\n  try {\\n    const { existsSync, readFileSync } = await import(\\\"node:fs\\\");\\n    if (!existsSync(path)) return null;\\n    return readFileSync(path, \\\"utf-8\\\");\\n  } catch {\\n    return null;\\n  }\\n}\\n\\nexport async function readJsonOrNull<T>(path: string): Promise<T | null> {\\n  const raw = await readFileOrNull(path);\\n  if (!raw) return null;\\n  try {\\n    return JSON.parse(raw) as T;\\n  } catch {\\n    return null;\\n  }\\n}\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":640,"output":572,"cacheRead":123136,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":124348,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780531358416,"responseId":"gen-1780531358-AfckjVMY0YSKlDFQbNuG"}}
