{"type":"message","id":"354d9765","parentId":"eb4680a1","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:04:06.457Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a significant refactor — 10 files with ~25 call sites. All the `createServerFn` handlers are already `async`, so adding `await` is straightforward. Let me update them systematically. The key insight: these are ALL inside `createServerFn` handlers which are already async, so I just need to add `await` to every call."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"976f0be5-69ea-4d42-9c18-cc9249b6c860","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data && for f in activity.ts agent-status.ts crons.ts incidents.ts memory.ts openclaw-status.ts projects.ts quick-actions.ts search.ts system.ts tasks.ts; do\n  # Add await before readJsonOrNull and readFileOrNull calls (but not in import lines or the helpers.ts file itself)\n  sed -i '' 's/= readJsonOrNull/= await readJsonOrNull/g' \"$f\"\n  sed -i '' 's/= readFileOrNull/= await readFileOrNull/g'  \"$f\"\n  # Also handle lines that don't start with = (e.g., const x = readJsonOrNull)\n  sed -i '' 's/readJsonOrNull</await readJsonOrNull</g' \"$f\"\n  sed -i '' 's/readFileOrNull</await readFileOrNull</g'  \"$f\"\ndone\necho \"Done\"","timeout":5},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data && for f in activity.ts agent-status.ts crons.ts incidents.ts memory.ts openclaw-status.ts projects.ts quick-actions.ts search.ts system.ts tasks.ts; do\\n  # Add await before readJsonOrNull and readFileOrNull calls (but not in import lines or the helpers.ts file itself)\\n  sed -i '' 's/= readJsonOrNull/= await readJsonOrNull/g' \\\"$f\\\"\\n  sed -i '' 's/= readFileOrNull/= await readFileOrNull/g'  \\\"$f\\\"\\n  # Also handle lines that don't start with = (e.g., const x = readJsonOrNull)\\n  sed -i '' 's/readJsonOrNull</await readJsonOrNull</g' \\\"$f\\\"\\n  sed -i '' 's/readFileOr