{"type":"message","id":"b626548f","parentId":"e8f4345c","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:13:11.254Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This is called from a client component's `useEffect`. It needs to be a `createServerFn` or called through the API. But that's a bigger refactor. For now, the immediate fix is to make `getIncidentTimeline` async and have it use the lazy import. But the caller also needs to handle the promise. This is getting complex.\n\nLet me take a different approach for `timeline-data.ts`: since this file has many plain functions that aren't wrapped in `createServerFn`, and some are called directly from client components, the safest fix is to ensure NO top-level `node:fs` imports exist. The lazy imports I've already added to `readTasks`, `readIncidents`, and `readCrons` handle the internal functions. For `getIncidentTimeline`, I need to either:\n\n1. Convert it to a `createServerFn`, or\n2. Have it use `readJsonOrNull` from helpers (which is now async and lazy-imports `node:fs`)\n\nOption 2 is simpler:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"3a7dd314-e4b9-4361-a9cc-77711b5296e2","name":"read","arguments":{"limit":15,"offset":287,"path":"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/timeline-data.ts"},"partialArgs":"{\"limit\": 15, \"offset\": 287, \"path\": \"/Users/spacemonkey/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard/src/lib/server-data/timeline-data.ts\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":242,"output":267,"cacheRead":145024,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":145533,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780531976728,"responseId":"gen-1780531977-N4s62eUDio31QWPPsIXD"}}
