{"type":"message","id":"e5a4d3b8","parentId":"00041ab3","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:22:11.432Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"MC is up and serving. Now let me commit all the fixes:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"8100d6c3-3e7c-4143-9cc5-551cd4322c79","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git add -A && git commit -m \"Fix node:fs client bundle leak — lazy-import fs in all server-data modules\n\nRoot cause: server-data barrel (server-data.ts) re-exports from modules that\nhave top-level node:fs imports. When client components import anything from the\nbarrel, Vite bundles the entire module graph including node:fs.\n\nFix: Removed all top-level node:fs imports from server-data modules.\n- helpers.ts: readJsonOrNull/readFileOrNull now lazy-import node:fs\n- activity.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for memory log reading\n- agent-status.ts: readJsonOrNull calls now awaited (helpers are async)\n- crons.ts: readJsonOrNull calls now awaited\n- docs.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for file reading\n- incidents.ts: internal helpers use lazy-imported node:fs\n- memory.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for MEMORY.md and daily logs\n- openclaw-status.ts: readJsonOrNull calls now awaited\n- projects.ts: readJsonOrNull calls now awaited\n- quick-actions.ts: removed unused top-level node:fs import\n- search.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for memory/doc file reading\n- system.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for workspace file count\n- tasks.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for atomic writes\n- timeline-data.ts: readTasks/readIncidents/readCrons now async with lazy fs\n- dreaming.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for flag file operations\n- Dashboard.tsx: removed getAwaitingReviewCount barrel import (use loader data)\n- IncidentDetailsDrawer.tsx: getIncidentTimeline now async with useState/useEffect\n\nAPI routes (routes/api/) are server-only and keep top-level node:fs imports.\n\nBuild verified clean. MC serving 200.\"","timeout":10},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace/mission-control-dashboard && git add -A && git commit -m \\\"Fix node:fs client bundle leak — lazy-import fs in all server-data modules\\n\\nRoot cause: server-data barrel (server-data.ts) re-exports from modules that\\nhave top-level node:fs imports. When client components import anything from the\\nbarrel, Vite bundles the entire module graph including node:fs.\\n\\nFix: Removed all top-level node:fs imports from server-data modules.\\n- helpers.ts: readJsonOrNull/readFileOrNull now lazy-import node:fs\\n- activity.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for memory log reading\\n- agent-status.ts: readJsonOrNull calls now awaited (helpers are async)\\n- crons.ts: readJsonOrNull calls now awaited\\n- docs.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for file reading\\n- incidents.ts: internal helpers use lazy-imported node:fs\\n- memory.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for MEMORY.md and daily logs\\n- openclaw-status.ts: readJsonOrNull calls now awaited\\n- projects.ts: readJsonOrNull calls now awaited\\n- quick-actions.ts: removed unused top-level node:fs import\\n- search.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for memory/doc file reading\\n- system.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for workspace file count\\n- tasks.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for atomic writes\\n- timeline-data.ts: readTasks/readIncidents/readCrons now async with lazy fs\\n- dreaming.ts: lazy-imports node:fs for flag file operations\\n- Dashboard.tsx: removed getAwaitingReviewCount barrel import (use loader data)\\n- IncidentDetailsDrawer.tsx: getIncidentTimeline now async with useState/useEffect\\n\\nAPI routes (routes/api/) are server-only and keep top-level node:fs imports.\\n\\nBuild verified clean. MC serving 200.\\\"\", \"timeout\": 10}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":92,"output":428,"cacheRead":159488,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":160008,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","tim