{"type":"message","id":"742517e7","parentId":"62de53e2","timestamp":"2026-06-04T00:22:44.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\n**Root cause:** The `server-data.ts` barrel re-exports from 12+ modules, many of which had top-level `import { readFileSync } from \"node:fs\"`. When any client component imported anything from the barrel (e.g., `getAwaitingReviewCount`), Vite bundled the entire module graph — including `node:fs` — into the client bundle. The browser then crashed trying to access `node:fs.readFileSync`.\n\n**Fix applied across 19 files:**\n\n| Layer | Change |\n|-------|--------|\n| `helpers.ts` | `readJsonOrNull`/`readFileOrNull` now lazy-import `node:fs` internally |\n| 10 server-data modules | Removed top-level `node:fs` imports; use `await import(\"node:fs\")` inside functions |\n| `Dashboard.tsx` | Removed barrel import; compute `awaitingReviewCount` from loader data |\n| `IncidentDetailsDrawer.tsx` | `getIncidentTimeline` now async with `useState`/`useEffect` |\n| `timeline-data.ts` | `readTasks`/`readIncidents`/`readCrons` now async with lazy `node:fs` |\n| `timeline.tsx` | `await` the now-async timeline functions |\n| API routes | Left unchanged — they're server-only, never bundled for client |\n\n**Key pattern:** All `node:fs` access in shared modules now uses `await import(\"node:fs\")` inside function bodies instead of top-level imports. This way the module can be imported by client code without pulling in `node:fs` — the fs code only executes when the function actually runs (which only happens on the server).\n\n**Build:** ✅ Clean. **MC:** ✅ 200."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/owl-alpha","usage":{"input":362,"output":373,"cacheRead":160000,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":0,"totalTokens":160735,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780532548201,"responseId":"gen-1780532548-dSNBEnBkKKjtXevdUAGI"}}
